obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (24822)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24822&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Customs Act, 1962.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1`
  line `[and, save as otherwise provided in this Act, it applies also to any`
  line `offence or contravention thereunder committed outside India by any person].`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^2`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 57 (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  line
  line `2. 1st February, 1963, vide notification No. G.S.R. 155, dated 23rd January, 1963, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3(i).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (24823)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24823&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(1) adjudicating authority means any authority competent to pass any order or decision under`
  line `this Act, but does not include the Board, ^2`
  line `[Commissioner (Appeals)] or Appellate Tribunal;`
  line
  line `(1A) aircraft has the same meaning as in the Aircraft Act, 1934 (22 of 1934);`
  line
  line `(1B) Appellate Tribunal means the Customs, Excise and ^3`
  line `[Service Tax] Appellate Tribunal`
  line `constituted under section 129;]`
  line
  line ^4
  line `[(2) assessment means determination of the dutiability of any goods and the amount of duty, tax,`
  line `cess or any other sum so payable, if any, under this Act or under the Customs Tariff Act, 1975`
  line `(51 of 1975) (hereinafter referred to as the Customs Tariff Act) or under any other law for the time being`
  line `in force, with reference to--`
  line
  line `(a) the tariff classification of such goods as determined in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `the Customs Tariff Act;`
  line
  line `(b) the value of such goods as determined in accordance with the provisions of this Act and`
  line `the Customs Tariff Act;`
  line
  line `(c) exemption or concession of duty, tax, cess or any other sum, consequent upon any notification`
  line `issued therefor under this Act or under the Customs Tariff Act or under any other law for the time`
  line `being in force;`
  line
  line `(d) the quantity, weight, volume, measurement or other specifics where such duty, tax, cess or`
  line `any other sum is leviable on the basis of the quantity, weight, volume, measurement or other`
  line `specifics of such goods;`
  line
  line `(e) the origin of such goods determined in accordance with the provisions of the Customs`
  line `Tariff Act or the rules made thereunder, if the amount of duty, tax, cess or any other sum is`
  line `affected by the origin of such goods;`
  line
  line `(f) any other specific factor which affects the duty, tax, cess or any other sum payable on such`
  line goods,
  line
  line `and includes provisional assessment, self-assessment, re-assessment and any assessment in which the`
  line `duty assessed is nil;]`
  line
  line `(3) baggage includes unaccompanied baggage but does not include motor vehicles;`
  line
  line ^5
  line `[(3A) beneficial owner means any person on whose behalf the goods are being imported or`
  line `exported or who exercises effective control over the goods being imported or exported;]`
  line
  line `(4) bill of entry means a bill of entry referred to in section 46;`
  line
  line `(5) bill of export means a bill of export referred to in section 50;`
  line
  line `(6) Board means the ^6`
  line [
  line ^7
  line `[Central Board of Indirect Taxes and Customs] constituted under the`
  line `Central Boards of Revenue Act, 1963 (54 of 1963)];`
  line
  line `(7) coastal goods means goods, other than imported goods, transported in a vessel from one port in`
  line `India to another;`
  line
  line ^8
  line `[(7A) Commissioner (Appeals) means a person appointed to be a Commissioner of Customs`
  line `(Appeals) under sub-section (1) of section 4;`
  line
  line `^9[(7B) common portal means the Common Customs Electronic Portal referred to in section 154C;].`
  line
  line `(8)`
  line ^10
  line `[Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs], except for the purposes of`
  line `Chapter XV, includes an Additional Commissioner of Customs;]`
  line
  line `(9) conveyance includes a vessel, an aircraft and a vehicle;`
  line
  line `(10) customs airport means any airport appointed under clause (a) of section 7 to be a customs`
  line `airport ^11`
  line `[and includes a place appointed under clause (aa) of that section to be an air freight station];`
  line
  line `(11) customs area means the area of a customs station ^12`
  line `[or a warehouse] and includes any area in`
  line `which imported goods or exported goods are ordinarily kept before clearance by Customs Authorities;`
  line
  line `(12) customs port means any port appointed under clause (a) of section 7 to be a customs port`
  line ^13
  line `[, and includes a place appointed under clause (aa) of that section to be an inland container depot];`
  line
  line `(13) customs station means any customs port, ^14`
  line `[customs airport, international courier terminal,`
  line `foreign post office] or land customs station;`
  line
  line `(14) dutiable goods means any goods which are chargeable to duty and on which duty has not been`
  line paid;
  line
  line `(15) duty means a duty of customs leviable under this Act;`
  line
  line `(16) entry in relation to goods means an entry made in a bill of entry, shipping bill or bill of export`
  line `and includes ^15`
  line `*** the entry made under the regulations made under section 84;`
  line
  line `(17) examination, in relation to any goods, includes measurement and weighment thereof;`
  line
  line `(18) export, with its grammatical variations and cognate expressions, means taking out of India to a`
  line `place outside India;`
  line
  line `(19) export goods means any goods which are to be taken out of India to a place outside India;`
  line
  line `(20) exporter, in relation to any goods at any time between their entry for export and the time when`
  line `they are exported, includes ^16`
  line `[any owner, beneficial owner] or any person holding himself out to be the`
  line exporter;
  line
  line ^17
  line `[(20A) foreign post office means any post office appointed under clause (e) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 7 to be a foreign post office;]`
  line
  line `(21) foreign-going vessel or aircraft means any vessel or aircraft for the time being engaged in the`
  line `carriage of goods or passengers between any port or airport in India and any port or airport outside India,`
  line `whether touching any intermediate port or airport in India or not, and includes--`
  line
  line `(i) any naval vessel of a foreign Government taking part in any naval exercises;`
  line
  line `(ii) any vessel engaged in fishing or any other operations outside the territorial waters of India;`
  line
  line `(iii) any vessel or aircraft proceeding to a place outside India for any purpose whatsoever;`
  line
  line ^18
  line `[(21A) Fund means the Consumer Welfare Fund established under section 12C of the Central`
  line `Excises and Salt Act, 1944 (1 of 1944);]`
  line
  line `(22) goods includes--`
  line
  line `(a) vessels, aircrafts and vehicles;`
  line
  line `(b) stores;`
  line
  line `(c) baggage;`
  line
  line `(d) currency and negotiable instruments; and`
  line
  line `(e) any other kind of movable property;`
  line
  line `(23) import, with its grammatical variations and cognate expressions, means bringing into India`
  line `from a place outside India;`
  line
  line `(24) ^19`
  line `[arrival manifest or import manifest] or import report means the manifest or report required`
  line `to be delivered under section 30;`
  line
  line `(25) imported goods means any goods brought into India from a place outside India but does not`
  line `include goods which have been cleared for home consumption;`
  line
  line `(26) importer, in relation to any goods at any time between their importation and the time when`
  line `they are cleared for home consumption, includes ^20`
  line `[any owner, beneficial owner] or any person holding`
  line `himself out to be the importer;`
  line
  line `(27) India includes the territorial waters of India;`
  line
  line `(28) Indian Customs Waters means the ^21`
  line `[waters extending into the sea up to the limit of ^22`
  line [Exclusive
  line `Economic zone under section 7] of the Territorial Waters, Continental Shelf, Exclusive Economic Zone`
  line `and other Maritime Zones Act, 1976 (80 of 1976),] and includes any bay, gulf, harbour, creek or tidal`
  line river;
  line
  line ^23
  line `[(28A) international courier terminal means any place appointed under clause (f) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 7 to be an international courier terminal;]`
  line
  line `(29) land customs station means any place appointed under clause (b) of section 7 to be a land`
  line `customs station;`
  line
  line `(30) market price, in relation to any goods, means the wholesale price of the goods in the ordinary`
  line `course of trade in India;`
  line
  line ^24
  line `[(30A) National Tax Tribunal means the National Tax Tribunal established under section 3 of the`
  line `National Tax Tribunal Act, 2005 (49 of 2005);]`
  line
  line ^25
  line `[(30AA) notification means notification published in the Official Gazette and the expression`
  line `notify with its cognate meaning and grammatical variation shall be construed accordingly;]`
  line
  line ^26
  line `[(30B) passenger name record information means the records prepared by an operator of any`
  line `aircraft or vessel or vehicle or his authorised agent for each journey booked by or on behalf of any`
  line passenger;]
  line
  line `(31) person-in-charge means,--`
  line
  line `(a) in relation to a vessel, the master of the vessel;`
  line
  line `(b) in relation to an aircraft, the commander or pilot-in-charge of the aircraft;`
  line
  line `(c) in relation to a railway train, the conductor, guard or other person having the chief direction of`
  line `the train;`
  line
  line `(d) in relation to any other conveyance, the driver or other person-in-charge of the conveyance;`
  line
  line `(32) prescribed means prescribed by regulations made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(33) prohibited goods means any goods the import or export of which is subject to any prohibition`
  line `under this Act or any other law for the time being in force but does not include any such goods in respect`
  line `of which the conditions subject to which the goods are permitted to be imported or exported have been`
  line `complied with;`
  line
  line `(34) proper office, in relation to any functions to be performed under this Act, means the officer of customs who is assigned those functions by the Board or the ^27`
  line `[Principal Commissioner of Customs or`
  line `Commissioner of Customs] ^28[under section 5];`
  line
  line `(35) regulations means the regulations made by the Board under any provision of this Act;`
  line
  line `(36) rules means the rules made by the Central Government under any provision of this Act;`
  line
  line `(37) shipping bill means a shipping bill referred to in section 50;`
  line
  line `(38) stores means goods for use in a vessel or aircraft and includes fuel and spare parts and other`
  line `articles of equipment, whether or not for immediate fitting;`
  line
  line `(39) smuggling, in relation to any goods, means any act or omission which will render such goods`
  line `liable to confiscation under section 111 or section 113;`
  line
  line `(40) tariff value, in relation to any goods, means the tariff value fixed in respect thereof under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 14;`
  line
  line `(41) value, in relation to any goods, means the value thereof determined in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of ^29`
  line `[sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) of section 14];`
  line
  line `(42) vehicle means conveyance of any kind used on land and includes a railway vehicle;`
  line
  line ^30
  line `[(43) warehouse means a public warehouse licensed under section 57 or a private warehouse`
  line `licensed under section 58 or a special warehouse licensed under section 58A;]`
  line
  line `(44) warehoused goods means goods deposited in a warehouse;`
  line
  line ^31
  line `* * * * *`
