obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (24824)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Classes of officers of customs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24824&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[3.^2[ Classes of officers of customs.--There shall be the following classes of officers of customs,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) Principal Chief Commissioner of Customs or Principal Chief Commissioner of Customs`
  line `(Preventive) or Principal Director General of Revenue Intelligence;`
  line
  line `(b) Chief Commissioner of Customs or Chief Commissioner of Customs (Preventive) or Director General of Revenue Intelligence;`
  line
  line `(c) Principal Commissioner of Customs or Principal Commissioner of Customs (Preventive) or Principal Additional Director General of Revenue Intelligence or Principal Commissioner of Customs (Audit);`
  line
  line `(d) Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs (Preventive) or Additional Director General of Revenue Intelligence or Commissioner of Customs (Audit);`
  line
  line `(e) Principal Commissioner of Customs (Appeals);`
  line
  line `(f) Commissioner of Customs (Appeals);`
  line
  line `(g) Additional Commissioner of Customs or Additional Commissioner of Customs (Preventive) or Additional Director of Revenue Intelligence or Additional Commissioner of Customs (Audit);`
  line
  line `(h) Joint Commissioner of Customs or Joint Commissioner of Customs (Preventive) or Joint Director of Revenue Intelligence or Joint Commissioner of Customs (Audit);`
  line
  line `(i) Deputy Commissioner of Customs or Deputy Commissioner of Customs (Preventive) or Deputy Director of Revenue Intelligence or Deputy Commissioner of Customs (Audit);`
  line
  line `(j) Assistant Commissioner of Customs or Assistant Commissioner of Customs (Preventive) or`
  line `Assistant Director of Revenue Intelligence or Assistant Commissioner of Customs (Audit);`
  line
  line `(k) such other class of officers of customs as may be appointed for the purposes of this Act;.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 52, for sections 3 and 4 (w.e.f. 26-5-1995).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 6 of 2022, s. 87 for section 3 (w.e.f. 30-3-2022), earlier it was subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 79, for clauses (a), (b), (c), (cc), (d), (e) and (f) (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (24825)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Appointment of officers of customs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24825&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The ^1`
  line `[Board] may appoint such persons as it thinks fit`
  line `to be officers of customs.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), ^2`
  line `[Board may authorise a ^3`
  line `[Principal Chief`
  line `Commissioner of Customs or Chief Commissioner of Customs] or] a ^4`
  line `[Principal Commissioner of`
  line `Customs or Commissioner of Customs] or a ^5[Joint] or ^6[Assistant Commissioner of Customs or Deputy`
  line `Commissioner of Customs] to appoint officers of customs below the rank of ^6[Assistant Commissioner of`
  line `Customs or Deputy Commissioner of Customs.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 117, for "Central Governement" (w.e.f. 11-5-2002).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 117, ibid., for "Central Government may authorise the Board" (w.e.f. 11-5-2002).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 78, for "Chief Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 78, ibid., for "Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 100, for "Deputy Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 11-5-1999).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 100, ibid., for "Assistant Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 11-5-1999).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (24826)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Powers of officers of customs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24826&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to such conditions and limitations as the Board may`
  line `impose, an officer of customs may exercise the powers and discharge the duties conferred or imposed on him under this Act.`
  line
  line `^1[(1A) Without prejudice to the provisions contained in sub-section (1), the Board may, by notification, assign such functions as it may deem fit, to an officer of customs, who shall be the proper officer in relation to such functions.`
  line
  line `(1B) Within their jurisdiction assigned by the Board, the Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs, as the case may be, may, by order, assign such functions, as he may deem fit, to an officer of customs, who shall be the proper officer in relation to such functions.]`
  line
  line `(2) An officer of customs may exercise the powers and discharge the duties conferred or imposed`
  line `under this Act on any other officer of customs who is subordinate to him.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, ^2`
  line `[a ^3`
  line `[Commissioner (Appeals)]] shall not`
  line `exercise the powers and discharge the duties conferred or imposed on an officer of customs other than`
  line `those specified ^4[Chapter XV, and section 108 and sub-section (1D) of section 110].`
  line
  line `^5[(4) In specifying the conditions and limitations referred to in sub-section (1), and in assigning functions under sub-section (1A), the Board may consider any one or more of the following criteria, including, but not limited to`
  line
  line `(a) territorial jurisdiction;`
  line
  line `(b) persons or class of persons;`
  line
  line `(c) goods or class of goods;`
  line
  line `(d) cases or class of cases;`
  line
  line `(e) computer assigned random assignment;`
  line
  line `(f) any other criterion as the Board may, by notification, specify.`
  line
  line `(5) The Board may, by notification, wherever necessary or appropriate, require two or more officers of customs (whether or not of the same class) to have concurrent powers and functions to be performed under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 6 of 2022, s. 88 (w.e.f. 30-3-2022).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 44 of 1980, s. 50 and the Fifth Schedule for, an Appellate Collector of Customs (w.e.f. 11-10-1982).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 50, for Collector (Appeals) (w.e.f. 26-5-1995).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 90, for "Chapter XV and section 108" (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
  line
  line `5.Ins. by Act 6 of 2022, s. 88 (w.e.f. 30-3-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (24827)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Entrustment of functions of Board and customs officers on certain other officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24827&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line The
  line `Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, entrust either conditionally or`
  line `unconditionally to any officer of the Central or the State Government or a local authority any functions of`
  line `the Board or any officer of customs under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (24828)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Appointment of customs ports, airports, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24828&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `^1[7. Appointment of customs ports, airports, etc.--^2`
  line `[(1)] The ^3`
  line `[Board] may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint--`
  line
  line `(a) the ports and airports which alone shall be customs ports or customs airports for the unloading`
  line `of imported goods and the loading of export goods or any class of such goods;`
  line
  line ^4
  line `[(aa) the places which alone shall be inland ^5`
  line `[container depots or air freight stations] for the`
  line `unloading of imported goods and the loading of export goods or any class of such goods;]`
  line
  line `(b) the places which alone shall be land customs stations for the clearance of goods imported or to`
  line `be exported by land or inland water or any class of such goods;`
  line
  line `(c) the routes by which alone goods or any class of goods specified in the notification may pass`
  line `by land or inland water into or out of India, or to or from any land customs station from or to any`
  line `land frontier;`
  line
  line `(d) the ports which alone shall be coastal ports for the carrying on of trade in coastal goods or any`
  line `class of such goods with all or any specified ports in India.`
  line
  line ^6
  line `[(e) the post offices which alone shall be foreign post offices for the clearance of imported goods`
  line `goods or export goods or any class of such goods;`
  line
  line `(f) the places which alone shall be international courier terminals for the clearance of imported`
  line `goods or export goods or any class of such goods.]`
  line
  line ^7
  line `[(2) Every notification issued under this section and in force immediately before the commencement`
  line `of the Finance Act, 2003 (32 of 2003) shall, on such commencement, be deemed to have been issued`
  line `under the provisions of this section as amended by section 105 of the Finance Act, 2003 and shall`
  line `continue to have the same force and effect after such commencement until it is amended, rescinded or`
  line `superseded under the provisions of this section.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 117, for the chapter heading (w.e.f. 14-5-2016).`
  line
  line `2. Section 7 numbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 32 of 2003, s. 105 (w.e.f. 14-5-2003).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 105, ibid., for "Central Government" (w.e.f. 14-5-2003).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 11 of 1983, s. 47 (w.e.f.13-5-1983).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 121, for "container depots" (w.e.f. 28-5-2012).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 90 (w.e.f. 31-3-2017).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 105 (w.e.f. 14-5-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (24829)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Power to approve landing places and specify limits of customs area.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 78, for "Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24829&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `The ^1`
  line [Principal
  line `Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs] may,--`
  line
  line `(a) approve proper places in any customs port or customs airport or coastal port for the unloading`
  line `and loading of goods or for any class of goods;`
  line
  line `(b) specify the limits of any customs area.`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (24830)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title [Omitted.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24830&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `[Powers to declare places to be warehousing stations].Omitted by The Finance Act, 2016 (28 of`
  line `2016), s. 118 (w.e.f. 14-5-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (24831)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Appointment of boarding stations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 78, for "Commissioner of Customs (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24831&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `The ^1`
  line `[Principal Commissioner of Customs or`
  line `Commissioner of Customs] may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint, in or near any customs`
  line `port, a boarding station for the purpose of boarding of, or disembarkation from, vessels by officers of`
  line customs.
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (24832)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Power to prohibit importation or exportation of goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24832&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Central Government is`
  line `satisfied that it is necessary so to do for any of the purposes specified in sub-section (2), it may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, prohibit either absolutely or subject to such conditions (to be fulfilled`
  line `before or after clearance) as may be specified in the notification, the import or export of goods of any`
  line `specified description.`
  line
  line `(2) The purposes referred to in sub-section (1) are the following:--`
  line
  line `(a) the maintenance of the security of India;`
  line
  line `(b) the maintenance of public order and standards of decency or morality;`
  line
  line `(c) the prevention of smuggling;`
  line
  line `(d) the prevention of shortage of goods of any description;`
  line
  line `(e) the conservation of foreign exchange and the safeguarding of balance of payments;`
  line
  line `(f) the prevention of injury to the economy of the country by the uncontrolled import or export of`
  line `^1[gold, silver or any other goods];`
  line
  line `(g) the prevention of surplus of any agricultural product or the product of fisheries;`
  line
  line `(h) the maintenance of standards for the classification, grading or marketing of goods`
  line `in international trade;`
  line
  line `(i) the establishment of any industry;`
  line
  line `(j) the prevention of serious injury to domestic production of goods of any description;`
  line
  line `(k) the protection of human, animal or plant life or health;`
  line
  line `(l) the protection of national treasures of artistic, historic or archaeological value;`
  line
  line `(m) the conservation of exhaustible natural resources;`
  line
  line `(n) the protection of patents, trademarks ^2[, copyrights, designs and geographical indications];`
  line
  line `(o) the prevention of deceptive practices;`
  line
  line `(p) the carrying on of foreign trade in any goods by the State, or by a Corporation owned`
  line `or controlled by the State to the exclusion, complete or partial, of citizens of India;`
  line
  line `(q) the fulfilment of obligations under the Charter of the United Nations for the maintenance`
  line `of international peace and security;`
  line
  line `(r) the implementation of any treaty, agreement or convention with any country;`
  line
  line `(s) the compliance of imported goods with any laws which are applicable to similar goods`
  line `produced or manufactured in India;`
  line
  line `(t) the prevention of dissemination of documents containing any matter which is likely to`
  line `prejudicially affect friendly relations with any foreign State or is derogatory to national prestige;`
  line
  line `(u) the prevention of the contravention of any law for the time being in force; and`
  line
  line `(v) any other purpose conducive to the interests of the general public.`
  line
  line `^3[(3) Any prohibition or restriction or obligation relating to import or export of any goods or class of`
  line `goods or clearance thereof provided in any other law for the time being in force, or any rule or regulation`
  line `made or any order or notification issued thereunder, shall be executed under the provisions of that Act`
  line `only if such prohibition or restriction or obligation is notified under the provisions of this Act, subject to`
  line `such exceptions, modifications or adaptations as the Central Government deems fit.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 12 of 2020, s. 107, for "gold or silver" (w.e.f. 27-3-2020).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 64, for and copyrights (w.e.f. 10-5-2013).`
  line
  line `3. Sub-section (3) shall stand inserted (date to be notified) by Act 13 of 2018, s. 59.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_a:
  sectionId (24833)
  sectionNo 11A
  orderNo 12
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_a_content
  footnotes `1. Chapters IVA, IVB and IVC ins. by Act 12 of 1969, s. 2 (w.e.f. 3-1-1969).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24833&sectionno=11A&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_11_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[11A. Definitions.--In this Chapter, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "illegal import" means the import of any goods in contravention of the provisions of this Act`
  line `or any other law for the time being in force;`
  line
  line `(b) "intimated place" means a place intimated under sub-section (1), sub-section (2) or`
  line `sub-section (3), as the case may be, of section 11C;`
  line
  line `(c) "notified date", in relation to goods of any description, means the date on which the`
  line `notification in relation to such goods is issued under section 11B;`
  line
  line `(d) "notified goods" means goods specified in the notification issued under section 11B.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11_b:
  sectionId (24834)
  sectionNo 11B
  orderNo 13
  title `Power of Central Government to notify goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_b_content
  footnotes `1. Chapters IVA, IVB and IVC ins. by Act 12 of 1969, s. 2 (w.e.f. 3-1-1969).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24834&sectionno=11B&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_11_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[11B. Power of Central Government to notify goods.--If, having regard to the magnitude of the`
  line `illegal import of goods of any class or description, the Central Government is satisfied that it is expedient`
  line `in the public interest to take special measures for the purpose of checking the illegal import, circulation or`
  line `disposal of such goods, or facilitating the detection of such goods, it may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, specify goods of such class or description.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11_c:
  sectionId (24835)
  sectionNo 11C
  orderNo 14
  title `Persons possessing notified goods to intimate the place of storage, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_c_content
  footnotes `1. Chapters IVA, IVB and IVC ins. by Act 12 of 1969, s. 2 (w.e.f. 3-1-1969).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24835&sectionno=11C&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_11_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[11C. Persons possessing notified goods to intimate the place of storage, etc.--(1) Every person`
  line `who owns, possesses or controls, on the notified date, any notified goods, shall, within seven days from`
  line `that date, deliver to the proper officer a statement (in such form, in such manner and containing such`
  line `particulars as may be specified by rules made in this behalf) in relation to the notified goods owned,`
  line `possessed or controlled by him and the place where such goods are kept or stored.`
  line
  line `(2) Every person who acquires, after the notified date, any notified goods, shall, before making such`
  line `acquisition, deliver to the proper officer an intimation containing the particulars of the place where such`
  line `goods are proposed to be kept or stored after such acquisition and shall, immediately on such acquisition,`
  line `deliver to the proper officer a statement (in such form, in such manner and containing such particulars as`
  line `may be specified by rules made in this behalf) in relation to the notified goods acquired by him:`
  line
  line `Provided that a person who has delivered a statement, whether under sub-section (1) or`
  line `sub-section (2), in relation to any notified goods, owned, possessed, controlled or acquired by him, shall`
  line `not be required to deliver any further statement in relation to any notified goods acquired by him, after the`
  line `date of delivery of the said statement, so long as the notified goods so acquired are kept or stored at the`
  line `intimated place.`
  line
  line `(3) If any person intends to shift any notified goods to any place other than the intimated place, he`
  line `shall, before taking out such goods from the intimated place, deliver to the proper officer an intimation`
  line `containing the particulars of the place to which such goods are proposed to be shifted.`
  line
  line `(4) No person shall, after the expiry of seven days from the notified date, keep or store any notified`
  line `goods at any place other than the intimated place.`
  line
  line `(5) Where any notified goods have been sold or transferred, such goods shall not be taken from one`
  line `place to another unless they are accompanied by the voucher referred to in section 11F.`
  line
  line `(6) No notified goods (other than those which have been sold or transferred) shall be taken from one`
  line `place to another unless they are accompanied by a transport voucher (in such form and containing such`
  line `particulars as may be specified by rules made in this behalf) prepared by the persons owning, possessing`
  line `or controlling such goods.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11_d:
  sectionId (24836)
  sectionNo 11D
  orderNo 15
  title `Precautions to be taken by persons acquiring notified goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_d_content
  footnotes `1. Chapters IVA, IVB and IVC ins. by Act 12 of 1969, s. 2 (w.e.f. 3-1-1969).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24836&sectionno=11D&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_11_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[11D. Precautions to be taken`
  line `by persons acquiring notified goods.--No person shall acquire`
  line `(except by gift or succession, from any other individual in India), after the notified date, any notified`
  line goods--
  line
  line `(i) unless such goods are accompanied by,--`
  line
  line `(a) the voucher referred to in section 11F or the memorandum referred to in sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 11G, as the case may be, or`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of a person who has himself imported any goods, any evidence showing`
  line `clearance of such goods by the Customs Authorities; and`
  line
  line `(ii) unless he has taken, before acquiring such goods from a person other than a dealer having a`
  line `fixed place of business, such reasonable steps as may be specified by rules made in this behalf, to`
  line `ensure that the goods so acquired by him are not goods which have been illegally imported.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11_e:
  sectionId (24837)
  sectionNo 11E
  orderNo 16
  title `Persons possessing notified goods to maintain accounts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_e_content
  footnotes `1. Chapters IVA, IVB and IVC ins. by Act 12 of 1969, s. 2 (w.e.f. 3-1-1969).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24837&sectionno=11E&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_11_e_content:
  string
  line `^1[11E. Persons possessing notified goods to maintain accounts.--(1) Every person who, on or after`
  line `the notified date, owns, possesses, controls or acquires any notified goods shall maintain (in such form`
  line `and in such manner as may be specified by rules made in this behalf) a true and complete account of such`
  line `goods and shall, as often as he acquires or parts with any notified goods, make an entry in the said`
  line `account in relation to such acquisition or parting with, and shall also state therein the particulars of the`
  line `person from whom such goods have been acquired or in whose favour such goods have been parted with,`
  line `as the case may be, and such account shall be kept, along with the goods, at the place of storage of the`
  line `notified goods to which such accounts relate:`
  line
  line `Provided that it shall not be necessary to maintain separately accounts in the form and manner`
  line `specified by rules made in this behalf in the case of a person who is already maintaining accounts which`
  line `contain the particulars specified by the said rules.`
  line
  line `(2) Every person who owns, possesses or controls any notified goods and who uses any such goods`
  line `for the manufacture of any other goods, shall maintain (in such form, in such manner and containing such`
  line `particulars as may be specified by rules made in this behalf) a true and complete account of the notified`
  line `goods so used by him and shall keep such account at the intimated place.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11_f:
  sectionId (24838)
  sectionNo 11F
  orderNo 17
  title `Sale, etc., of notified goods to be evidenced by vouchers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_f_content
  footnotes `1. Chapters IVA, IVB and IVC ins. by Act 12 of 1969, s. 2 (w.e.f. 3-1-1969).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24838&sectionno=11F&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_11_f_content:
  string
  line `^1[11F. Sale, etc., of notified goods to be evidenced by vouchers.--On and from the notified date, no`
  line `person shall sell or otherwise transfer any notified goods, unless every transaction in relation to the sale or`
  line `transfer of such goods is evidenced by a voucher in such form and containing such particulars as may be`
  line `specified by rules made in this behalf.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11_g:
  sectionId (24839)
  sectionNo 11G
  orderNo 18
  title `Sections 11C, 11E and 11F not to apply to goods in personal use.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_g_content
  footnotes `1. Chapters IVA, IVB and IVC ins. by Act 12 of 1969, s. 2 (w.e.f. 3-1-1969).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24839&sectionno=11G&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_11_g_content:
  string
  line `^1[11G. Sections 11C, 11E and 11F not to apply to goods in personal use.--(1) Nothing in sections`
  line `11C, 11E and 11F shall apply to any notified goods which are--`
  line
  line `(a) in personal use of the person by whom they are owned, possessed or controlled, or`
  line
  line `(b) kept in the residential premises of a person for his personal use.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person, who is in possession of any notified goods referred to in sub-section (1), sells, or`
  line `otherwise transfers for a valuable consideration, any such goods, he shall issue to the purchaser or`
  line `transferee, as the case may be, a memorandum containing such particulars as may be specified by rules`
  line `made in this behalf and no such goods shall be taken from one place to another unless they are`
  line `accompanied by the said memorandum.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11_h:
  sectionId (24840)
  sectionNo 11H
  orderNo 19
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_h_content
  footnotes `1. Chapters IVA, IVB and IVC ins. by Act 12 of 1969, s. 2 (w.e.f. 3-1-1969).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24840&sectionno=11H&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_11_h_content:
  string
  line `^1[11-H. Definitions.--In this Chapter, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "illegal export" means the export of any goods in contravention of the provisions of this`
  line `Act or any other law for the time being in force;`
  line
  line `(b) "intimated place" means a place intimated under sub-section (1), sub-section (2) or`
  line `sub-section (3), as the case may be, of section 11J;`
  line
  line `(c) "specified area" includes the Indian customs waters, and such inland area, not exceeding one`
  line `hundred kilometres in width from any coast or other border of India, as the Central Government may,`
  line `having regard to the vulnerability of that area to smuggling, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `specify in this behalf:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a part of any village, town or city falls within a specified area, the whole of`
  line `such village, town or city shall, notwithstanding that the whole of it is not within one hundred`
  line `kilometres from any coast or other border of India, be deemed to be included in such specified area;`
  line
  line `(d) "specified date", in relation to specified goods, means the date on which any notification is`
  line `issued under section 11-I in relation to those goods in any specified area;`
  line
  line `(e) "specified goods" means goods of any description specified in the notification issued under`
  line `section 11-I in relation to a specified area.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11_i:
  sectionId (24841)
  sectionNo 11I
  orderNo 20
  title `Power of Central Government to specify goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_i_content
  footnotes `1. Chapters IVA, IVB and IVC ins. by Act 12 of 1969, s. 2 (w.e.f. 3-1-1969).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24841&sectionno=11I&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_11_i_content:
  string
  line `^1[11-I. Power of Central Government to specify goods.--If, having regard to the magnitude of the`
  line `illegal export of goods of any class or description, the Central Government is satisfied that it is expedient`
  line `in the public interest to take special measures for the purpose of checking the illegal export or facilitating`
  line `the detection of goods which are likely to be illegally exported, it may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, specify goods of such class or description.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11_j:
  sectionId (24842)
  sectionNo 11J
  orderNo 21
  title `Persons possessing specified goods to intimate the place of storage, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_j_content
  footnotes `1. Chapters IVA, IVB and IVC ins. by Act 12 of 1969, s. 2 (w.e.f. 3-1-1969).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24842&sectionno=11J&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_11_j_content:
  string
  line `^1[11J. Persons possessing specified goods to intimate the place of storage, etc.--(1) Every person`
  line `who owns, possesses or controls, on the specified date, any specified goods, the market price of which`
  line `exceeds fifteen thousand rupees shall, within seven days from that date, deliver to the proper officer an`
  line `intimation containing the particulars of the place where such goods are kept or stored within the specified`
  line area.
  line
  line `(2) Every person who acquires (within the specified area), after the specified date, any specified`
  line goods,--
  line
  line `(i) the market price of which, or`
  line
  line `(ii) the market price of which together with the market price of any specified goods of the same`
  line `class or description, if any, owned, possessed or controlled by him on the date of such acquisition,`
  line
  line `exceeds fifteen thousand rupees shall, before making such acquisition, deliver to the proper officer an`
  line `intimation containing the particulars of the place where such goods are proposed to be kept or stored after`
  line `such acquisition:`
  line
  line `Provided that a person who has delivered an intimation, whether under sub-section (1) or`
  line `sub-section (2), in relation to any specified goods, owned, possessed, controlled or acquired by him, shall`
  line `not be required to deliver any further intimation so long as the specified goods are kept or stored at the`
  line `intimated place.`
  line
  line `(3) If any person intends to shift any specified goods to which sub-section (1) or sub-section (2)`
  line `applies, to any place other than the intimated place, he shall, before taking out such goods from the`
  line `intimated place, deliver to the proper officer an intimation containing the particulars of the place to which`
  line `such goods are proposed to be shifted.`
  line
  line `(4) No person shall, after the expiry of seven days from the specified date, keep or store any specified`
  line `goods to which sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) applies, at any place other than the intimated place.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11_k:
  sectionId (24843)
  sectionNo 11K
  orderNo 22
  title `Transport of specified goods to be covered by vouchers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_k_content
  footnotes `1. Chapters IVA, IVB and IVC ins. by Act 12 of 1969, s. 2 (w.e.f. 3-1-1969).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24843&sectionno=11K&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_11_k_content:
  string
  line `^1[11K. Transport of specified goods to be covered by vouchers.--(1) No specified goods shall be`
  line `transported from, into or within any specified area or loaded on any animal or conveyance in such area,`
  line `unless they are accompanied by a transport voucher (in such form and containing such particulars as may`
  line `be specified by rules made in this behalf) prepared by the person owning, possessing, controlling or`
  line `selling such goods:`
  line
  line `Provided that no transport voucher shall be necessary for the transport, within a village, town or`
  line `city, of any specified goods the market price of which, on the date of transport, does not exceed one`
  line `thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where the Central Government, after`
  line `considering the nature of any specified goods, the time, mode, route and the market price of the goods`
  line `intended to be transported, the purpose of the transportation and the vulnerability of the specified area`
  line `with regard to the illegal export of such goods, is satisfied that it is expedient in the public interest so to`
  line `do, it may, --`
  line
  line `(i) by notification in the Official Gazette, specify goods of such class or description and of a`
  line `market price exceeding such sum as that Government may notify; and different sums in relation to the`
  line `specified goods of the same class or description, or different classes or descriptions, may be notified`
  line `for the same specified area or for different specified areas, and`
  line
  line `(ii) direct that no person shall transport any goods so specified unless the transport voucher in`
  line `relation to them has been countersigned by the proper officer.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11_l:
  sectionId (24844)
  sectionNo 11L
  orderNo 23
  title `Persons possessing specified goods to maintain accounts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_l_content
  footnotes `1. Chapters IVA, IVB and IVC ins. by Act 12 of 1969, s. 2 (w.e.f. 3-1-1969).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24844&sectionno=11L&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_11_l_content:
  string
  line `^1[11L. Persons possessing specified goods to maintain accounts.--(1) Every person who, on or after`
  line `the specified date, owns, possesses or controls, within a specified area, any specified goods of a market`
  line `price exceeding fifteen thousand rupees, shall maintain (in such form and in such manner as may be`
  line `specified by rules made in this behalf) a true and complete account of such goods and shall, as often as he`
  line `acquires or parts with any specified goods, make an entry in the said account in relation to such`
  line `acquisition or parting with, and shall also state therein the particulars of the person from whom such`
  line `goods have been acquired or in whose favour such goods have been parted with, as the case may be, and`
  line `such account shall be kept, along with the goods, at the place of storage of the specified goods to which`
  line `such accounts relate:`
  line
  line `Provided that it shall not be necessary to maintain separately accounts in the form and manner`
  line `specified by rules made in this behalf in the case of a person who is already maintaining accounts which`
  line `contain the particulars specified by the said rules.`
  line
  line `(2) Every person who owns, possesses or controls any specified goods to which the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (1) apply, and who uses any such goods for the manufacture of any other goods, shall`
  line `maintain (in such form, in such manner and containing such particulars as may be specified by rules made`
  line `in this behalf) a true and complete account of the specified goods so used by him and shall keep such`
  line `account at the intimated place.`
  line
  line `(3) If at any time, on a verification made by a proper officer, it is found that any specified goods`
  line `owned, possessed or controlled by a person are lesser in quantity than the stock of such goods as shown,`
  line `at the time of such verification, in the accounts referred to in sub-section (1), read with the accounts`
  line `referred to in sub-section (2), it shall be presumed, unless the contrary is proved, that such goods, to the extent that they are lesser than the stock shown in the said accounts, have been illegally exported and that`
  line `the person owning, possessing or controlling such goods has been concerned with the illegal export`
  line thereof.]
obj_root_law_sections_11_m:
  sectionId (24845)
  sectionNo 11M
  orderNo 24
  title `Steps to be taken by persons selling or transferring any specified goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_m_content
  footnotes `1. Chapters IVA, IVB and IVC ins. by Act 12 of 1969, s. 2 (w.e.f. 3-1-1969).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24845&sectionno=11M&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_11_m_content:
  string
  line `^1[11M. Steps to be taken by persons selling or transferring any specified goods.--Except where he`
  line `receives payment by cheque drawn by the purchaser, every person who sells or otherwise transfers within`
  line `any specified area, any specified goods, shall obtain, on his copy of the sale or transfer voucher, the`
  line `signature and full postal address of the person to whom such sale or transfer is made and shall also take`
  line `such other reasonable steps as may be specified by rules made in this behalf to satisfy himself as to the`
  line `identity of the purchaser or the transferee, as the case may be, and if after an inquiry made by a proper`
  line `officer, it is found that the purchaser or the transferee, as the case may be, is not either readily traceable or`
  line `is a fictitious person, it shall be presumed, unless the contrary is proved, that such goods have been`
  line `illegally exported and the person who had sold or otherwise transferred such goods had been concerned in`
  line `such illegal export:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall apply to petty sales of any specified goods if the aggregate`
  line `market price obtained by such petty sales, made in the course of a day, does not exceed two thousand and`
  line `five hundred rupees.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this section "petty sale" means a sale at a price which does not exceed one thousand`
  line rupees.]
obj_root_law_sections_11_n:
  sectionId (24846)
  sectionNo 11N
  orderNo 25
  title `Power to exempt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_n_content
  footnotes `1. Chapters IVA, IVB and IVC ins. by Act 12 of 1969, s. 2 (w.e.f. 3-1-1969).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24846&sectionno=11N&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_11_n_content:
  string
  line `^1[11N. Power to exempt.--If the Central Government is satisfied that it is necessary in the public`
  line `interest so to do, it may, by notification in the Official Gazette, exempt generally, either absolutely or`
  line `subject to such conditions as may be specified in the notification, goods of any class or description from`
  line `all or any of the provisions of Chapter IVA or Chapter IVB.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (24847)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 26
  title `Dutiable goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24847&sectionno=12&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) Except as otherwise provided in this Act, or any other law for the time`
  line `being in force, duties of customs shall be levied at such rates as may be specified under the ^1[Customs`
  line `Tariff Act, 1975 (51 of 1975)], or any other law for the time being in force, on goods imported into, or`
  line `exported from, India.`
  line
  line `^2[(2) The provisions of sub-section (1) shall apply in respect of all goods belonging to Government`
  line `as they apply in respect of goods not belonging to Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 51 of 1975, s. 13, for "Indian Tariff Act, 1934 (32 of 1934)" (w.e.f. 2-8-1976).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 30 of 1963, s. 2, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 1-10-1963).`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (24848)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 27
  title `Duty on pilfered goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24848&sectionno=13&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `If any imported goods are pilfered after the unloading thereof and`
  line `before the proper officer has made an order for clearance for home consumption or deposit in a`
  line `warehouse, the importer shall not be liable to pay the duty leviable on such goods except where such`
  line `goods are restored to the importer after pilferage.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (24849)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 28
  title `Valuation of goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24849&sectionno=14&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `^1[14. Valuation of goods.(1) For the purposes of the Customs Tariff Act, 1975 (51 of 1975), or`
  line `any other law for the time being in force, the value of the imported goods and export goods shall be the`
  line `transaction value of such goods, that is to say, the price actually paid or payable for the goods when sold`
  line `for export to India for delivery at the time and place of importation, or as the case may be, for export from`
  line `India for delivery at the time and place of exportation, where the buyer and seller of the goods are not`
  line `related and price is the sole consideration for the sale subject to such other conditions as may be specified`
  line `in the rules made in this behalf:`
  line
  line `Provided that such transaction value in the case of imported goods shall include, in addition to the`
  line `price as aforesaid, any amount paid or payable for costs and services, including commissions and brokerage, engineering, design work, royalties and licence fees, costs of transportation to the place of`
  line `importation, insurance, loading, unloading and handling charges to the extent and in the manner specified`
  line `in the rules made in this behalf:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the rules made in this behalf may provide for,--`
  line
  line `(i) the circumstances in which the buyer and the seller shall be deemed to be related;`
  line
  line `(ii) the manner of determination of value in respect of goods when there is no sale, or the buyer`
  line `and the seller are related, or price is not the sole consideration for the sale or in any other case;`
  line
  line `(iii) the manner of acceptance or rejection of value declared by the importer or exporter, as`
  line `the case may be, where the proper officer has reason to doubt the truth or accuracy of such value, and`
  line `determination of value for the purposes of this section:`
  line
  line `^2[(iv) the additional obligations of the importer in respect of any class of imported goods and the checks to be exercised, including the circumstances and manner of exercising thereof, as the Board may specify, where, the Board has reason to believe that the value of such goods may not be declared truthfully or accurately, having regard to the trend of declared value of such goods or any other relevant criteria.]`
  line
  line `Provided also that such price shall be calculated with reference to the rate of exchange as in force on the date on which a bill of entry is presented under section 46, or a shipping bill of export, as the case may be, is presented under section 50.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), if the Board is satisfied that it is necessary or expedient so to do, it may, by notification in the Official Gazette, fix tariff values for any class of imported goods or export goods, having regard to the trend of value of such or like goods, and where any such tariff values are fixed, the duty shall be chargeable with reference to such tariff value.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section--`
  line
  line `(a) rate of exchange means the rate of exchange--`
  line
  line `(i) determined by the Board, or`
  line
  line `(ii) ascertained in such manner as the Board may direct,`
  line
  line `for the conversion of Indian currency into foreign currency or foreign currency into Indian currency;`
  line
  line `(b) foreign currency and Indian currency have the meanings respectively assigned to them`
  line `in clause (m) and clause (q) of section 2 of the Foreign Exchange Management Act, 1999`
  line `(42 of 1999).]`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 95, for section 14 (w.e.f. 10-10-2007).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 6 of 2022, s. 89, (w.e.f. 30-3-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (24850)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 29
  title `Date for determination of rate of duty and tariff valuation of imported goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24850&sectionno=15&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line ^1
  line `[The rate of duty ^2`
  line `***] and tariff valuation, if any, applicable to any imported goods, shall be the`
  line `rate and valuation in force,--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of goods entered for home consumption under section 46, on the date on which a`
  line `bill of entry in respect of such goods is presented under that section;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of goods cleared from a warehouse under section 68, on the date on which ^3`
  line `[a bill`
  line `of entry for home consumption in respect of such goods is presented under that section];`
  line
  line `(c) in the case of any other goods, on the date of payment of duty:`
  line
  line ^4
  line `[Provided that if a bill of entry has been presented before the date of entry inwards of the vessel or`
  line `the arrival of the aircraft ^5`
  line `[or the vehicle] by which the goods are imported, the bill of entry shall be`
  line `deemed to have been presented on the date of such entry inwards or the arrival, as the case may be.]`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of this section shall not apply to baggage and goods imported by post.`
  line
  line ^6
  line `* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 1966, s. 3, for "The rate of duty" (w.e.f. 31-8-1966).`
  line
  line `2. The words ", rate of exchange" omitted by Act 25 of 1978, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-7-1978).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 106, for "the goods are actually removed from the warehouse" (w.e.f. 14-5-2003).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 33 of 1996, s. 59, for the proviso (w.e.f. 28-9-1996).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 80 (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  line
  line `6 Sub-Section (3) omitted by Act 25 of 1978, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-7-1978). Earlier sub-section (3) inserted by Act 20 of 1966, s. 3`
  line `(w.e.f. 31-8-1966)`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (24851)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 30
  title `Date for determination of rate of duty and tariff valuation of export goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 1986, s. 50, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 13-5-1986).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24851&sectionno=16&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[(1) The rate`
  line `of duty and tariff valuation, if any, applicable to any export goods, shall be the rate and valuation in`
  line force,--
  line
  line `(a) in the case of goods entered for export under section 50, on the date on which the proper`
  line `officer makes an order permitting clearance and loading of the goods for exportation under`
  line `section 51;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of any other goods, on the date of payment of duty.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of this section shall not apply to baggage and goods exported by post.]`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (24852)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 31
  title `Assessment of duty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24852&sectionno=17&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `^1[17. Assessment of duty.--(1) An importer entering any imported goods under section 46, or an`
  line `exporter entering any export goods under section 50, shall, save as otherwise provided in section 85,`
  line `self-assess the duty, if any, leviable on such goods.`
  line
  line `(2) The proper officer may verify ^2[the entries made under section 46 or section 50 and the`
  line `self-assessment of goods referred to in sub-section (1)] and for this purpose, examine or test any imported`
  line `goods or export goods or such part thereof as may be necessary.`
  line
  line `^3[Provided that the selection of cases for verification shall primarily be on the basis of risk evaluation`
  line `through appropriate selection criteria.]`
  line
  line `^4[(3) For ^5[the purposes of verification] under sub-section (2), the proper officer may require the`
  line `importer, exporter or any other person to produce any document or information, whereby the duty`
  line `leviable on the imported goods or export goods, as the case may be, can be ascertained and thereupon, the`
  line `importer, exporter or such other person shall produce such document or furnish such information.]`
  line
  line `(4) Where it is found on verification, examination or testing of the goods or otherwise that the`
  line `self- assessment is not done correctly, the proper officer may, without prejudice to any other action which`
  line `may be taken under this Act, re-assess the duty leviable on such goods.`
  line
  line `(5) Where any re-assessment done under sub-section (4) is contrary to the self-assessment done by`
  line `the importer or exporter ^6*** and in cases other than those where the importer or exporter, as the case`
  line `may be, confirms his acceptance of the said re-assessment in writing, the proper officer shall pass a`
  line `speaking order on the re-assessment, within fifteen days from the date of`
  line `re-assessment of the bill of entry or the shipping bill, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `^7* * * * *`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that in cases where an importer has`
  line `entered any imported goods under section 46 or an exporter has entered any export goods under section`
  line `50 before the date on which the Finance Bill, 2011 receives the assent of the President, such imported`
  line `goods or export goods shall continue to be governed by the provisions of section 17 as it stood`
  line `immediately before the date on which such assent is received.]`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 8 of 2011, s. 38, for section 17 (w.e.f. 8-4-2011).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 60, for "the self-assessment of such goods" (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 60, ibid. (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 91, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 31-3-2017).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 60, for "verification of self-assessment" (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  line
  line `6. The words "regarding valuation of goods, classification, exemption or concessions of duty availed consequent to any`
  line `notification issued therefor under this Act" omitted by s. 60, ibid. (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  line
  line `7. Sub-section (6) omitted by s. 60, ibid. (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (24853)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 32
  title `Provisional assessment of duty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24853&sectionno=18&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act but`
  line `without prejudice to the provisions of section 46 ^2`
  line `[and section 50],--`
  line
  line `(a) where the importer or exporter is unable to make self-assessment under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 17 and makes a request in writing to the proper officer for assessment; or`
  line
  line `(b) where the proper officer deems it necessary to subject any imported goods or export goods to`
  line `any chemical or other test; or`
  line
  line `(c) where the importer or exporter has produced all the necessary documents and furnished full`
  line `information but the proper officer deems it necessary to make further enquiry; or`
  line
  line `(d) where necessary documents have not been produced or information has not been furnished`
  line `and the proper officer deems it necessary to make further enquiry,`
  line
  line `the proper officer may direct that the duty leviable on such goods be assessed provisionally if the importer`
  line `or the exporter, as the case may be, furnishes such security as the proper officer deems fit for the payment`
  line `of the deficiency, if any, between the duty as may be finally assessed or re-assessed as the case may be,`
  line `and the duty provisionally assessed.]`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(1A) Where, pursuant to the provisional assessment under sub-section (1), if any document or`
  line `information is required by the proper officer for final assessment, the importer or exporter, as the case`
  line `may be, shall submit such document or information within such time, and the proper officer shall finalise`
  line `the provisional assessment within such time and in such manner, as may be prescribed.]`
  line
  line `(2) When the duty leviable on such goods is assessed finally ^3`
  line `[or re-assessed by the proper officer] in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this Act, then--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of goods cleared for home consumption or exportation, the amount paid shall be`
  line `adjusted against the duty ^4`
  line `[finally assessed or re-assessed, as the case may be,] and if the amount so`
  line `paid falls short of, or is in excess of ^5`
  line `[the duty ^4`
  line `[finally assessed or re-assessed, as the case may`
  line `be,]], the importer or the exporter of the goods shall pay the deficiency or be entitled to a refund, as`
  line `the case may be;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of warehoused goods, the proper officer may, where the duty ^4`
  line `[finally assessed or`
  line `re-assessed, as the case may be,] is in excess of the duty provisionally assessed, require the importer`
  line `to execute a bond, binding himself in a sum equal to twice the amount of the excess duty.`
  line
  line ^6
  line `[(3) The importer or exporter shall be liable to pay interest, on any amount payable to the Central`
  line `Government, consequent to the final assessment order ^3`
  line `[or re-assessment order] under sub-section (2), at`
  line `the rate fixed by the Central Government under section ^7`
  line `[28AA] from the first day of the month in which`
  line `the duty is provisionally assessed till the date of payment thereof.]`
  line
  line `(4) Subject the sub-section (5), if any refundable amount referred to in clause (a) of sub-section (2)`
  line `is not refunded under that sub-section within three months from the date of assessment, of duty`
  line `finally ^3`
  line `[or re-assessment of duty, as the case may be,] there shall be paid an interest on such un-refunded`
  line `amount at such rate fixed by the Central Government under section 27A till the date of refund of such`
  line amount.]
  line
  line `(5) The amount of duty refundable under sub-section (2) and the interest under sub-section (4), if`
  line `any, shall, instead of being credited to the Fund, be paid to the importer or the exporter, as the case may`
  line `be, if such amount is relatable to--`
  line
  line `(a) the duty and interest, if any, paid on such duty paid by the importer, or the exporter, as the`
  line `case may be, if he had not passed on the incidence of such duty and interest, if any, paid on such duty`
  line `to any other person;`
  line
  line `(b) the duty and interest, if any, paid on such duty on imports made by an individual for his`
  line `personal use;`
  line
  line `(c) the duty and interest, if any, paid on such duty borne by the buyer, if he had not passed on the`
  line `incidence of such duty and interest, if any, paid on such duty to any other person;`
  line
  line `(d) the export duty as specified in section 26;`
  line
  line `(e) drawback of duty payable under sections 74 and 75.]`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 8 of 2011, s. 39, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 8-4-2011).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 61 (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 8 of 2011, s. 39 (w.e.f. 8-4-2011).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 39, ibid., for "finally assessed" (w.e.f. 8-4-2011).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 56 of 1974, s. 3 and the Second Schedule, for "the finally assessed" (w.e.f. 20-12-1974).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 29 of 2006, s. 21 (w.e.f. 13-7-2006).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 61, for "28AB" (w.e.f. 8-4-2011).`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (24854)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 33
  title `Determination of duty where goods consist of articles liable to different rates of duty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 8 of 2011, s. 40 (w.e.f. 8-4-2011).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24854&sectionno=19&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `Except as otherwise provided in any law for the time being in force, where goods consist of a set of`
  line `articles, duty shall be calculated as follows:--`
  line
  line `(a) articles liable to duty with reference to quantity shall be chargeable to that duty;`
  line
  line `(b) articles liable to duty with reference to value shall, if they are liable to duty at the same rate,`
  line `be chargeable to duty at that rate, and if they are liable to duty at different rates, be chargeable to duty`
  line `at the highest of such rates;`
  line
  line `(c) articles not liable to duty shall be chargeable to duty at the rate at which articles liable to duty`
  line `with reference to value are liable under clause (b):`
  line
  line `Provided that, --`
  line
  line `(a) accessories of, and spare parts or maintenance and repairing implements for, any article which`
  line `satisfy the conditions specified in the rules made in this behalf shall be chargeable at the same rate of`
  line `duty as that article;`
  line
  line `(b) if the importer produces evidence to the satisfaction of the proper officer ^1[or the evidence is`
  line `available] regarding the value of any of the articles liable to different rates of duty, such article shall`
  line `be chargeable to duty separately at the rate applicable to it.`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (24855)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 34
  title `Re-importation of goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24855&sectionno=20&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `^1[20. Re-importation of goods.--If goods are imported into India after exportation therefrom, such`
  line `goods shall be liable to duty and be subject to all the conditions and restrictions, if any, to which goods of`
  line `the like kind and value are liable or subject, on the importation thereof:]`
  line
  line `^2[* * * * *]`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 1994, s. 60, for section 20 (w.e.f. 13-5-1994).`
  line
  line `2. The provisos and the Explanations omitted by Act 22 of 1995, s. 53 (w.e.f. 26-5-1995)`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (24856)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 35
  title `Goods derelict, wreck, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24856&sectionno=21&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `All goods, derelict, jetsam, flotsam and wreck brought or coming`
  line `into India, shall be dealt with as if they were imported into India, unless it be shown to the satisfaction of`
  line `the proper officer that they are entitled to be admitted duty-free under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (24857)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 36
  title `Abatement of duty on damaged or deteriorated goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 100, for "Assistant Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 11-5-1999).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24857&sectionno=22&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where it is shown to the`
  line `satisfaction of the ^1[Assistant Commissioner of Customs or Deputy Commissioner of Customs]--`
  line
  line `(a) that any imported goods had been damaged or had deteriorated at any time before or during`
  line `the unloading of the goods in India; or`
  line
  line `(b) that any imported goods, other than warehoused goods, had been damaged at any time after`
  line `the unloading thereof in India but before their examination under section 17, on account of any`
  line `accident not due to any wilful act, negligence or default of the importer, his employee or agent; or`
  line
  line `(c) that any warehoused goods had been damaged at any time before clearance for home`
  line `consumption on account of any accident not due to any wilful act, negligence or default of the owner,`
  line `his employee or agent,`
  line
  line `such goods shall be chargeable to duty in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(2) The duty to be charged on the goods referred to in sub-section (1) shall bear the same proportion`
  line `to the duty chargeable on the goods before the damage or deterioration which the value of the damaged or`
  line `deteriorated goods bears to the value of the goods before the damage or deterioration.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of this section, the value of damaged or deteriorated goods may be ascertained`
  line `by either of the following methods at the option of the owner:--`
  line
  line `(a) the value of such goods may be ascertained by the proper officer, or`
  line
  line `(b) such goods may be sold by the proper officer by public auction or by tender, or with the`
  line `consent of the owner in any other manner, and the gross sale proceeds shall be deemed to be the value`
  line `of such goods.`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (24858)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 37
  title `Remission of duty on lost, destroyed or abandoned goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24858&sectionno=23&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `^1[Without prejudice to the`
  line `provisions of section 13, where it is shown] to the satisfaction of the ^2[Assistant Commissioner of`
  line `Customs or Deputy Commissioner of Customs] that any imported goods have been lost ^3`
  line `[(otherwise than`
  line `as a result of pilferage)] or destroyed, at any time before clearance for home consumption, the ^2[Assistant`
  line `Commissioner of Customs or Deputy Commissioner of Customs] shall remit the duty on such goods.`
  line
  line `^4[(2) The owner of any imported goods may, at any time before an order for clearance of goods for`
  line `home consumption under section 47 or an order for permitting the deposit of goods in a warehouse under`
  line `section 60 has been made, relinquish his title to the goods and thereupon he shall not be liable to pay the`
  line `duty thereon;]`
  line
  line `^5[Provided that the owner of any such imported goods shall not be allowed to relinquish his title to`
  line `such goods regarding which an offence appears to have been committed under this Act or any other law`
  line `for the time being in force.]`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 11 of 1983, s. 48, for "Where it is shown" (w.e.f. 13-5-1983).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 100, for "Assistant Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 11-5-1999).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 11 of 1983, s. 48 (w.e.f. 13-5-1983).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 32 of 1994, s. 60, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 13-5-1994).`
  line
  line `5. The proviso ins. by Act 21 of 2006, s. 58 (w.e.f. 18-4-2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (24859)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 38
  title `Power to make rules for denaturing or mutilation of goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24859&sectionno=24&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may`
  line `make rules for permitting at the request of the owner the denaturing or mutilation of imported goods`
  line `which are ordinarily used for more than one purpose so as to render them unfit for one or more of such`
  line `purposes; and where any goods are so denatured or mutilated they shall be chargeable to duty at such rate`
  line `as would be applicable if the goods had been imported in the denatured or mutilated form.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (24860)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 39
  title `Power to grant exemption from duty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24860&sectionno=25&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Central Government is satisfied that it is`
  line `necessary in the public interest so to do, it may, by notification in the Official Gazette, exempt generally`
  line `either absolutely or subject to such conditions (to be fulfilled before or after clearance) as may be`
  line `specified in the notification goods of any specified description from the whole or any part of duty of`
  line `customs leviable thereon.`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(2) If the Central Government is satisfied that it is necessary in the public interest so to do, it may,`
  line `may, by special order in each case, exempt from the payment of duty, under circumstances of an`
  line `exceptional nature to be stated in such order, any goods on which duty is leviable.]`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(2A) The Central Government may, if it considers it necessary or expedient so to do for the purpose`
  line `purpose of clarifying the scope or applicability of any notification issued under sub-section (1) or order`
  line `issued under sub-section (2), insert an explanation in such notification or order, as the case may be, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, at any time within one year of issue of the notification under sub-section (1) or order under sub-section (2), and every such explanation shall have effect as if it had`
  line `always been the part of the first such notification or order, as the case may be.]`
  line
  line ^3
  line `[(3) An exemption under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) in respect of any goods from any part of`
  line `the duty of customs leviable thereon (the duty of customs leviable thereon being hereinafter referred to as`
  line `the statutory duty) may be granted by providing for the levy of a duty on such goods at a rate expressed in`
  line `a form or method different from the form or method in which the statutory duty is leviable and any`
  line `exemption granted in relation to any goods in the manner provided in this sub-section shall have effect`
  line `subject to the condition that the duty of customs chargeable on such goods shall in no case exceed the`
  line `statutory duty.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--Form or method, in relation to a rate of duty of customs, means the basis, namely,`
  line `valuation, weight, number, length, area, volume or other measure with reference to which the duty`
  line `is leviable.]`
  line
  line ^4
  line `[(4) Every notification issued under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2A) shall, unless otherwise`
  line `provided, come into force on the date of its issue by the Central Government for publication in the`
  line `Official Gazette.]`
  line
  line `^5[(4A) Where any exemption is granted subject to any condition under sub-section (1), such exemption shall, unless otherwise specified or varied or rescinded, be valid up to 31st day of March falling immediately after two years from the date of such grant or variation:`
  line
  line `Provided that in respect of any such exemption in force as on the date on which the Finance Bill, 2021 receives the assent of the President, the said period of two years shall be reckoned from the 1st day of February, 2021.]`
  line
  line ^6
  line `* * * * *`
  line
  line ^7
  line `[(6) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, no duty shall be collected if the amount of`
  line `duty leviable is equal to, or less than, one hundred rupees.]`
  line
  line ^8
  line `[(7) The mineral oils (including petroleum and natural gas) extracted or produced in the continental`
  line `continental shelf of India or exclusive economic zone of India as referred to in section 6 and section 7,`
  line `respectively, of the Territorial Waters, Continental Shelf, Exclusive Economic Zone and Other Maritime`
  line Zones
  line
  line `Act, 1976 (80 of 1976), and imported prior to the 7th day of February, 2002 shall be deemed to be and`
  line `shall always be deemed to have been exempted from the whole of the duties of customs leviable on such`
  line `mineral oils and accordingly, notwithstanding anything contained in any judgment, decree or order of any`
  line `court, tribunal or other authority, no suit or other proceedings in respect of such mineral oils shall be`
  line `maintained or continued in any court, tribunal or other authority.`
  line
  line `(8) Notwithstanding the exemption provided under sub-section (7), no refund of duties of customs`
  line `paid in respect of the mineral oils specified therein shall be made.]`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 107, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 14-5-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 119 (w.e.f. 11-5-2002).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 11 of 1983, s. 49 (w.e.f. 13-5-1983).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 119, for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 14-5-2016).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 91 (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
  line
  line `6. Sub-section (5) omitted by, s. 119, ibid. (w.e.f. 14-5-2016).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 107, (w.e.f. 14-5-2003).`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 81, (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_25_a:
  sectionId (24861)
  sectionNo 25A
  orderNo 40
  title `Inward processing of goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 62 (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24861&sectionno=25A&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_25_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[25A. Inward processing of goods.--Where the Central Government is satisfied that it is necessary`
  line `in the public interest so to do, it may, by notification, exempt such of the goods which are imported for`
  line `the purposes of repair, further processing or manufacture, as may be specified therein, from the whole or`
  line `any part of duty of customs leviable thereon, subject to the following conditions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the goods shall be re-exported after such repair, further processing or manufacture, as the case`
  line `may be, within a period of one year from the date on which the order for clearance of the imported`
  line `goods is made;`
  line
  line `(b) the imported goods are identifiable in the export goods; and`
  line
  line `(c) such other conditions as may be specified in that notification.]`
obj_root_law_sections_25_b:
  sectionId (24862)
  sectionNo 25B
  orderNo 41
  title `Outward processing of goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 62 (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24862&sectionno=25B&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_25_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[25B. Outward processing of goods.--Notwithstanding anything contained in section 20, where the`
  line `Central Government is satisfied that it is necessary in the public interest so to do, it may, by notification,`
  line `exempt such of the goods which are re-imported after being exported for the purposes of repair, further`
  line `processing or manufacture, as may be specified therein, from the whole or any part of duty of customs`
  line `leviable thereon, subject to the following conditions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the goods shall be re-imported into India after such repair, further processing or manufacture,`
  line `as the case may be, within a period of one year from the date on which the order permitting clearance`
  line `for export is made;`
  line
  line `(b) the exported goods are identifiable in the re-imported goods; and`
  line
  line `(c) such other conditions as may be specified in that notification.]`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (24863)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 42
  title `Refund of export duty in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24863&sectionno=26&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `Where on the exportation of any goods any duty has`
  line `been paid, such duty shall be refunded to the person by whom or on whose behalf it was paid, if --`
  line
  line `(a) the goods are returned to such person otherwise than by way of re-sale;`
  line
  line `(b) the goods are re-imported within one year from the date of exportation; and`
  line
  line `(c) an application for refund of such duty is made before the expiry of six months from the date`
  line `on which the proper officer makes an order for the clearance of the goods.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26_a:
  sectionId (24864)
  sectionNo 26A
  orderNo 43
  title `Refund of import duty in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24864&sectionno=26A&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_26_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[26A. Refund of import duty in certain cases.--(1) Where on the importation of any goods`
  line `capable of being easily identified as such imported goods, any duty has been paid on clearance of such`
  line `goods for home consumption, such duty shall be refunded to the person by whom or on whose behalf it`
  line `was paid, if--`
  line
  line `(a) the goods are found to be defective or otherwise not in conformity with the specifications`
  line `agreed upon between the importer and the supplier of goods:`
  line
  line `Provided that the goods have not been worked, repaired or used after importation except where`
  line `such use was indispensable to discover the defects or non-conformity with the specifications;`
  line
  line `(b) the goods are identified to the satisfaction of the Assistant Commissioner of Customs or`
  line `Deputy Commissioner of Customs as the goods which were imported;`
  line
  line `(c) the importer does not claim drawback under any other provisions of this Act; and`
  line
  line `(d) (i) the goods are exported; or`
  line
  line `(ii) the importer relinquishes his title to the goods and abandons them to customs; or`
  line
  line `(iii) such goods are destroyed or rendered commercially valueless in the presence of the`
  line `proper officer,`
  line
  line `in such manner as may be prescribed and within a period not exceeding thirty days from the date on`
  line `which the proper officer makes an order for the clearance of imported goods for home consumption under`
  line `section 47:`
  line
  line `Provided that the period of thirty days may, on sufficient cause being shown, be extended by the`
  line ^2
  line `[Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs for a period not exceeding three`
  line `months:`
  line
  line `Provided further that nothing contained in this section shall apply to the goods regarding which an`
  line `offence appears to have been committed under this Act or any other law for the time being in force.`
  line
  line `(2) An application for refund of duty shall be made before the expiry of six months from the relevant`
  line `date in such form and in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, "relevant date" means, --`
  line
  line `(a) in cases where the goods are exported out of India, the date on which the proper officer`
  line `makes an order permitting clearance and loading of goods for exportation under section 51;`
  line
  line `(b) in cases where the title to the goods is relinquished, the date of such relinquishment;`
  line
  line `(c) in cases where the goods are destroyed or rendered commercially valueless, the date of such`
  line `destruction or rendering of goods commercially valueless.`
  line
  line `(3) No refund under sub-section (1) shall be allowed in respect of perishable goods and goods`
  line `which have exceeded their shelf life or their recommended storage-before-use period.`
  line
  line `(4) The Board may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify any other condition subject to`
  line `which the refund under sub-section (1) may be allowed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_26_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 85 (w.e.f. 19-8-2009).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 78, for "Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (24865)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 44
  title `Claim for refund of duty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24865&sectionno=27&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `^1[27. Claim for refund of duty.--^2[(1) Any person claiming refund of any duty or interest, --`
  line
  line `(a) paid by him; or`
  line
  line `(b) borne by him,`
  line
  line `may make an application in such form and manner as may be prescribed for such refund to the Assistant`
  line `Commissioner of Customs or Deputy Commissioner of Customs, before the expiry of one year, from the`
  line `date of payment of such duty or interest:`
  line
  line `Provided that where an application for refund has been made before the date on which the Finance`
  line `Bill, 2011 receives the assent of the President, such application shall be deemed to have been made under`
  line `sub-section (1), as it stood before the date on which the Finance Bill, 2011 receives the assent of the`
  line `President and the same shall be dealt with in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (2):`
  line
  line `Provided further that the limitation of one year shall not apply where any duty or interest has been`
  line `paid under protest.`
  line
  line `^3[Provided also that where the amount of refund claimed is less than rupees one hundred, the same`
  line `shall not be refunded.]`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, "the date of payment of duty or interest" in`
  line `relation to a person, other than the importer, shall be construed as "the date of purchase of goods" by such`
  line person.
  line
  line `(1A) The application under sub-section (1) shall be accompanied by such documentary or other`
  line `evidence (including the documents referred to in section 28C) as the applicant may furnish to establish`
  line `that the amount of duty or interest, in relation to which such refund is claimed was collected from, or paid`
  line `by him and the incidence of such duty or interest, has not been passed on by him to any other person.`
  line
  line `(1B) Save as otherwise provided in this section, the period of limitation of one year shall be`
  line `computed in the following manner, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of goods which are exempt from payment of duty by a special order issued under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 25, the limitation of one year shall be computed from the date of issue of`
  line `such order;`
  line
  line `(b) where the duty becomes refundable as a consequence of any judgment, decree, order or`
  line `direction of the appellate authority, Appellate Tribunal or any court, the limitation of one year shall`
  line `be computed from the date of such judgment, decree, order or direction;`
  line
  line `(c) where any duty is paid provisionally under section 18, the limitation of one year shall be`
  line `computed from the date of adjustment of duty after the final assessment thereof or in case of`
  line `re-assessment, from the date of such re-assessment.]`
  line
  line `(2) If, on receipt of any such application, the ^4[Assistant Commissioner of Customs or Deputy`
  line `Commissioner of Customs] is satisfied that the whole or any part of the ^5[duty and interest, if any, paid on`
  line `such duty] paid by the applicant is refundable, he may make an order accordingly and the amount so`
  line `determined shall be credited to the Fund:`
  line
  line `Provided that the amount of ^5[duty and interest, if any, paid on such duty] as determined by`
  line `the ^4[Assistant Commissioner of Customs or Deputy Commissioner of Customs] under the foregoing`
  line `provisions of this sub-section shall, instead of being credited to the Fund, be paid to the applicant, if such`
  line `amount is relatable to --`
  line
  line `(a) the ^5[duty and interest, if any, paid on such duty] paid by the importer, ^6[or the exporter, as the`
  line `case may be] if he had not passed on the incidence of such ^5[duty and interest, if any, paid on such duty]`
  line `to any other person;`
  line
  line `(b) the ^5[duty and interest, if any, paid on such duty] on imports made by an individual for his`
  line `personal use;`
  line
  line `(c) the ^7[duty and interest, if any, paid on such duty] borne by the buyer, if he had not passed on the`
  line `incidence of such ^7[duty and interest, if any, paid on such duty] to any other person;`
  line
  line `(d) the export duty as specified in section 26;`
  line
  line `(e) drawback of duty payable under sections 74 and 75;`
  line
  line `(f) the ^7[duty and interest, if any, paid on such duty] borne by any other such class of applicants as`
  line `the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify;`
  line
  line `^8[(g) the duty paid in excess by the importer before an order permitting clearance of goods for home`
  line `consumption is made where--`
  line
  line `(i) such excess payment of duty is evident from the bill of entry in the case of self-assessed bill of`
  line `entry; or`
  line
  line `(ii) the duty actually payable is reflected in the reassessed bill of entry in the case of`
  line `reassessment:]`
  line
  line `Provided further that no notification under clause (f) of the first proviso shall be issued unless in the`
  line `opinion of the Central Government the incidence of ^7[duty and interest, if any, paid on such duty] has not`
  line `been passed on by the persons concerned to any other person.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in any judgment, decree, order or direction of`
  line `the Appellate Tribunal, ^9[National Tax Tribunal] or any Court or in any other provision of this Act or the`
  line `regulations made thereunder or any other law for the time being in force, no refund shall be made except`
  line `as provided in sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(4) Every notification under clause (f) of the first proviso to sub-section (2) shall be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament, if it is sitting, as soon as may be after the issue of the notification, and, if it is not`
  line `sitting, within seven days of its re-assembly, and the Central Government shall seek the approval of`
  line `Parliament to the notification by a resolution moved within a period of fifteen days beginning with the`
  line `day on which the notification is so laid before the House of the People and if Parliament makes any`
  line `modification in the notification or directs that the notification should cease to have effect, the notification`
  line `shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be, but without`
  line `prejudice to the validity of anything previously done thereunder.`
  line
  line `(5) For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that any notification issued under clause (f) of`
  line `the first proviso to sub-section (2), including any such notification approved or modified under`
  line `sub-section (4), may be rescinded by the Central Government at any time by notification in the Official`
  line Gazette.]
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 40 of 1991, s. 10, for section 27 (w.e.f. 20-9-1991).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 8 of 2011, s. 41, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 8-4-2011).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 65 (w.e.f. 10-5-2013).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 100, for "Assistant Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 11-5-1999).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 55 of 1991, s. 2, for "duty" (w.e.f. 23-12-1991).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 108, (w.e.f. 14-5-2003).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 55 of 1991, s. 2, for "duty" (w.e.f. 23-12-1991).`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 92 (w.e.f. 31-3-2017).`
  line
  line `9. Ins. by Act 49 of 2005, s. 30 and the Schedule, Part VI (w.e.f. 28-12-2005). This amendment has been struck down by the`
  line `Supreme Court's order dated 25th September, 2014 in the Madras Bar Association Vs Union of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_a:
  sectionId (24866)
  sectionNo 27A
  orderNo 45
  title `Interest on delayed refunds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24866&sectionno=27A&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_27_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[27A. Interest on delayed refunds.--If any duty ordered to be refunded under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 27 to an applicant is not refunded within three months from the date of receipt of application`
  line `under sub-section (1) of that section, there shall be paid to that applicant interest at such rate, ^2[ not below`
  line `five per cent.] and not exceeding thirty per cent. per annum as is for the time being fixed ^3[by the Central Government by Notification in the Official Gazette], on such duty from the date immediately after the`
  line `expiry of three months from the date of receipt of such application till the date of refund of such duty:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any duty, ordered to be refunded under sub-section (2) of section 27 in respect of`
  line `an application under sub-section (1) of that section made before the date on which the Finance Bill, 1995`
  line `receives the assent of the President, is not refunded within three months from such date, there shall be`
  line `paid to the applicant interest under this section from the date immediately after three months from such`
  line `date, till the date of refund of such duty.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--Where any order of refund is made by the Commissioner (Appeals), Appellate`
  line `Tribunal ^4[, National Tax Tribunal] or any court against an order of the ^5[Assistant Commissioner of`
  line `Customs or Deputy Commissioner of Customs] under sub-section (2) of section 27, the order passed by`
  line `the Commissioner (Appeals), Appellate Tribunal ^4[, National Tax Tribunal] Tribunal or as the case may`
  line `be, by the court shall be deemed to be an order passed under that sub-section for the purposes of this`
  line section.]
obj_root_law_sections_27_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 55 (w.e.f. 26-5-1995).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 102, for "not below ten per cent." (w.e.f. 11-5-2001).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 78, for "by the Board" (w.e.f. 12-5-2000).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 49 of 2005, s. 30 and the Schedule, Part VI (w.e.f. 28-12-2005). This amendment has been struck down by the`
  line `Supreme Court's order dated 25th September, 2014 in the Madras Bar Association Vs Union of India.`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 100, for "Assistant Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 11-5-1999).`
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (24867)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 46
  title `Recovery of duties not levied or not paid or short-levied or short-paid or erroneously refunded.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24867&sectionno=28&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `^1[28. Recovery of ^2[duties not levied or not paid or short-levied or short-paid] or erroneously`
  line `refunded.--(1) Where any ^3[duty has not been levied or not paid or short-levied or short-paid] or`
  line `erroneously refunded, or any interest payable has not been paid, part-paid or erroneously refunded, for`
  line `any reason other than the reasons of collusion or any wilful mis-statement or suppression of facts, --`
  line
  line `(a) the proper officer shall, within ^4[two years] from the relevant date, serve notice on the person`
  line `chargeable with the duty or interest which has not been so levied ^5[or paid] or which has been`
  line `short-levied or short-paid or to whom the refund has erroneously been made, requiring him to show`
  line `cause why he should not pay the amount specified in the notice:`
  line
  line `^6[Provided that before issuing notice, the proper officer shall hold pre-notice consultation with the`
  line `the person chargeable with duty or interest in such manner as may be prescribed;]`
  line
  line `(b) the person chargeable with the duty or interest, may pay before service of notice under`
  line `clause (a) on the basis of, --`
  line
  line `(i) his own ascertainment of such duty; or`
  line
  line `(ii) the duty ascertained by the proper officer,`
  line
  line `the amount of duty along with the interest payable thereon under section 28AA or the amount of`
  line `interest which has not been so paid or part-paid.`
  line
  line `^7[Provided that the proper officer shall not serve such show cause notice, where the amount involved`
  line `is less than rupees one hundred.]`
  line
  line `(2) The person who has paid the duty along with interest or amount of interest under clause (b) of`
  line `sub-section (1) shall inform the proper officer of such payment in writing, who, on receipt of such`
  line `information, shall not serve any notice under clause (a) of that sub-section in respect of the duty or`
  line `interest so paid or any penalty leviable under the provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder in`
  line `respect of such duty or interest:`
  line
  line `^8[Provided that where notice under clause (a) of sub-section (1) has been served and the proper`
  line `officer is of the opinion that the amount of duty along with interest payable thereon under section 28AA`
  line `or the amount of interest, as the case may be, as specified in the notice, has been paid in full within thirty`
  line `days from the date of receipt of the notice, no penalty shall be levied and the proceedings against such`
  line `person or other persons to whom the said notice is served under clause (a) of sub-section (1) shall be`
  line `deemed to be concluded.]`
  line
  line `(3) Where the proper officer is of the opinion that the amount paid under clause (b) of sub-section (1)`
  line `falls short of the amount actually payable, then, he shall proceed to issue the notice as provided for in`
  line `clause (a) of that sub-section in respect of such amount which falls short of the amount actually payable`
  line `in the manner specified under that sub-section and the period of ^9[two years] shall be computed from the`
  line `date of receipt of information under sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(4) Where any duty has not been ^10[levied or not paid or has been short-levied or short-paid]`
  line `or erroneously refunded, or interest payable has not been paid, part-paid or erroneously refunded, by`
  line `reason of,--`
  line
  line `(a) collusion; or`
  line
  line `(b) any wilful mis-statement; or`
  line
  line `(c) suppression of facts,`
  line
  line `by the importer or the exporter or the agent or employee of the importer or exporter, the proper officer`
  line `shall, within five years from the relevant date, serve notice on the person chargeable with duty or interest`
  line `which has not been ^11[so levied or not paid] or which has been so short-levied or short-paid or to whom the`
  line `the refund has erroneously been made, requiring him to show cause why he should not pay the amount`
  line `specified in the notice.`
  line
  line `(5) Where any ^12[duty has not been levied or not paid or has been short-levied or short paid] or the`
  line `interest has not been charged or has been part-paid or the duty or interest has been erroneously refunded`
  line `by reason of collusion or any wilful mis-statement or suppression of facts by the importer or the exporter`
  line `or the agent or the employee of the importer or the exporter, to whom a notice has been served under`
  line `sub- section (4) by the proper officer, such person may pay the duty in full or in part, as may be accepted`
  line `by him, and the interest payable thereon under section 28AA and the penalty equal to ^13[fifteen per cent.]`
  line `of the duty specified in the notice or the duty so accepted by that person, within thirty days of the receipt`
  line `of the notice and inform the proper officer of such payment in writing.`
  line
  line `(6) Where the importer or the exporter or the agent or the employee of the importer or the exporter,`
  line `as the case may be, has paid duty with interest and penalty under sub-section (5), the proper officer shall`
  line `determine the amount of duty or interest and on determination, if the proper officer is of the opinion --`
  line
  line `(i) that the duty with interest and penalty has been paid in full, then, the proceedings in respect of`
  line `such person or other persons to whom the notice is served under sub-section (1) or sub- section (4),`
  line `shall, without prejudice to the provisions of sections 135, 135A and 140 be deemed to be conclusive`
  line `as to the matters stated therein; or`
  line
  line `(ii) that the duty with interest and penalty that has been paid falls short of the amount actually`
  line `payable, then, the proper officer shall proceed to issue the notice as provided for in clause (a) of`
  line `sub-section (1) in respect of such amount which falls short of the amount actually payable in the`
  line `manner specified under that sub-section and the period of ^14[two years] shall be computed from the`
  line `date of receipt of information under sub-section (5).`
  line
  line `(7) In computing the period of ^14[two years] referred to in clause (a) of sub-section (1) or five years`
  line `referred to in sub-section (4), the period during which there was any stay by an order of a court or`
  line `tribunal in respect of payment of such duty or interest shall be excluded.`
  line
  line `^15[(7A) Save as otherwise provided in clause (a) of sub-section (1) or in sub-section (4), the proper`
  line `officer may issue a supplementary notice under such circumstances and in such manner as may be`
  line `prescribed, and the provisions of this section shall apply to such supplementary notice as if it was issued`
  line `under the said sub-section (1) or sub-section (4).]`
  line
  line `(8) The proper officer shall, after allowing the concerned person an opportunity of being heard and`
  line `after considering the representation, if any, made by such person, determine the amount of duty or interest`
  line `due from such person not being in excess of the amount specified in the notice.`
  line
  line `(9) The proper officer shall determine the amount of duty or interest under sub-section (8),--`
  line
  line `(a) within six months from the date of notice, ^16*** in respect of cases falling under clause (a) of`
  line `sub- section (1);`
  line
  line `(b) within one year from the date of notice, ^16*** in respect of cases falling under sub-section (4).`
  line
  line `^15[Provided that where the proper officer fails to so determine within the specified period, any officer`
  line `senior in rank to the proper officer may, having regard to the circumstances under which the proper`
  line `officer was prevented from determining the amount of duty or interest under sub-section (8), extend the`
  line `period specified in clause (a) to a further period of six months and the period specified in clause (b) to a`
  line `further period of one year:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where the proper officer fails to determine within such extended period, such`
  line `proceeding shall be deemed to have concluded as if no notice had been issued;]`
  line
  line `^15[(9A) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (9), where the proper officer is unable to`
  line `determine the amount of duty or interest under sub-section (8) for the reason that--`
  line
  line `(a) an appeal in a similar matter of the same person or any other person is pending before the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal or the High Court or the Supreme Court; or`
  line
  line `(b) an interim order of stay has been issued by the Appellate Tribunal or the High Court or the`
  line `Supreme Court; or`
  line
  line `(c) the Board has, in a similar matter, issued specific direction or order to keep such matter`
  line `pending; or`
  line
  line `(d) the Settlement Commission has admitted an application made by the person concerned,`
  line
  line `the proper officer shall inform the person concerned the reason for non-determination of the amount of`
  line `duty or interest under sub-section (8) and in such case, the time specified in sub-section (9) shall apply`
  line `not from the date of notice, but from the date when such reason ceases to exist.]`
  line
  line `(10) Where an order determining the duty is passed by the proper officer under this section, the`
  line `person liable to pay the said duty shall pay the amount so determined along with the interest due on such`
  line `amount whether or not the amount of interest is specified separately.`
  line
  line `^17[(10A) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, where an order for refund under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 27 is modified in any appeal and the amount of refund so determined is less than the amount refunded`
  line `under said sub-section, the excess amount so refunded shall be recovered along with interest thereon at the rate`
  line `fixed by the Central Government under section 28AA, from the date of refund up to the date of recovery, as a`
  line `sum due to the Government.`
  line
  line `(10B) A notice issued under sub-section (4) shall be deemed to have been issued under sub-section (1), if`
  line `such notice demanding duty is held not sustainable in any proceeding under this Act, including at any stage of`
  line `appeal, for the reason that the charges of collusion or any wilful mis-statement or suppression of facts to evade`
  line `duty has not been established against the person to whom such notice was issued and the amount of duty and`
  line `the interest thereon shall be computed accordingly.]`
  line
  line `^18[(11) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in any judgment, decree or order of any`
  line `court of law, tribunal or other authority, all persons appointed as officers of Customs under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 4 before the 6th day of July, 2011 shall be deemed to have and always had the`
  line `power of assessment under section 17 and shall be deemed to have been and always had been the proper`
  line `officers for the purposes of this section.]`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.--For the purposes of this section, relevant date means, --`
  line
  line `(a) in a case where duty is ^19[not levied or not paid or short-levied or short-paid], or interest is not`
  line `charged, the date on which the proper officer makes an order for the clearance of goods;`
  line
  line `(b) in a case where duty is provisionally assessed under section 18, the date of adjustment of duty`
  line `after the final assessment thereof or re-assessment, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(c) in a case where duty or interest has been erroneously refunded, the date of refund;`
  line
  line `(d) in any other case, the date of payment of duty or interest.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.--For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that any non-levy, short-levy or`
  line `erroneous refund before the date on which the Finance Bill, 2011 receives the assent of the President,`
  line `shall continue to be governed by the provisions of section 28 as it stood immediately before the date on`
  line `which such assent is received.]`
  line
  line `^20[Explanation 3.--For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the proceedings in respect of`
  line `any case of non-levy, short-levy, non-payment, short-payment or erroneous refund where show cause`
  line `notice has been issued under sub-section (1) or sub-section (4), as the case may be, but an order`
  line `determining duty under sub-section (8) has not been passed before the date on which the Finance Bill,`
  line `2015 receives the assent of the President, shall, without prejudice to the provisions of sections 135, 135A`
  line `and 140, as may be applicable, be deemed to be concluded, if the payment of duty, interest and penalty`
  line `under the proviso to sub-section (2) or under sub-section (5), as the case may be, is made in full within`
  line `thirty days from the date on which such assent is received.]`
  line
  line `^21[Explanation 4.-- For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that notwithstanding anything to`
  line `the contrary contained in any judgment, decree or order of the Appellate Tribunal or any Court or in any`
  line `other provision of this Act or the rules or regulations made thereunder, or in any other law for the time`
  line `being in force, in cases where notice has been issued for non-levy, short-levy, non-payment, shortpayment or erroneous refund, prior to the 29th day of March, 2018, being the date of commencement of`
  line `the Finance Act, 2018 (13 of 2018), such notice shall continue to be governed by the provisions of section`
  line `28 as it stood immediately before such date.]`
