obj_root_law_sections_28_a:
  sectionId (24868)
  sectionNo 28A
  orderNo 47
  title `Power not to recover duties not levied or short-levied as a result of general practice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24868&sectionno=28A&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_28_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[28A. Power not to recover duties not levied or short-levied as a result of general`
  line `practice.--^2[(1)] Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, if the Central Government is`
  line satisfied--
  line
  line `(a) that a practice was, or is, generally prevalent regarding levy of duty (including non-levy`
  line `thereof) on any goods imported into, or exported from, India; and`
  line
  line `(b) that such goods were, or are, liable --`
  line
  line `(i) to duty, in cases where according to the said practice the duty was not, or is not being,`
  line `levied, or`
  line
  line `(ii) to a higher amount of duty than what was, or is being, levied, according to the said`
  line practice,
  line
  line `then, the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, direct that the whole of the`
  line `duty payable on such goods, or, as the case may be, the duty in excess of that payable on such goods, but`
  line `for the said practice, shall not be required to be paid in respect of the goods on which the duty was not, or`
  line `is not being, levied, or was, or is being, short-levied, in accordance with the said practice.]`
  line
  line `^3[(2) Where any notification under sub-section (1) in respect of any goods has been issued, the`
  line `whole of the duty paid on such goods, or, as the case may be, the duty paid in excess of that payable on`
  line `such goods, which would not have been paid if the said notification had been in force, shall be dealt with`
  line `in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (2) of section 27:`
  line
  line `Provided that the person claiming the refund of such duty or, as the case may be, excess duty, makes`
  line `an application in this behalf to the ^4[Assistant Commissioner of Customs or Deputy Commissioner of Customs], in the form referred to in sub-section (1) of section 27, before the expiry of six months from`
  line `the date of issue of the said notification.]`
obj_root_law_sections_28_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 25 of 1978 s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-7-1978).`
  line
  line `2. Section 28A renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof, by Act 29 of 1988, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-7-1988).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 40 of 1991, s. 11, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 20-9-1991).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 100, for "Assistant Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 11-5-1999).`
obj_root_law_sections_28_aa:
  sectionId (24869)
  sectionNo 28AA
  orderNo 48
  title `Interest on delayed payment of duty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_aa_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 8 of 2011, s. 43, for section 28AA and section 28AB (w.e.f. 8-4-2011).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24869&sectionno=28AA&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_28_aa_content:
  string
  line `^1[28AA. Interest on delayed payment of duty--[(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in any`
  line `judgment, decree, order or direction of any court, Appellate Tribunal or any authority or in any other`
  line `provision of this Act or the rules made thereunder, the person, who is liable to pay duty in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of section 28, shall, in addition to such duty, be liable to pay interest, if any, at the rate`
  line `fixed under sub-section (2), whether such payment is made voluntarily or after determination of the duty`
  line `under that section.`
  line
  line `(2) Interest at such rate not below ten per cent. and not exceeding thirty-six per cent. per annum, as`
  line `the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, fix, shall be paid by the person liable`
  line `to pay duty in terms of section 28 and such interest shall be calculated from the first day of the month`
  line `succeeding the month in which the duty ought to have been paid or from the date of such erroneous`
  line `refund, as the case may be, up to the date of payment of such duty.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), no interest shall be payable where,--`
  line
  line `(a) the duty becomes payable consequent to the issue of an order, instruction or direction by the`
  line `Board under section 151A; and`
  line
  line `(b) such amount of duty is voluntarily paid in full, within forty-five days from the date of issue of`
  line `such order, instruction or direction, without reserving any right to appeal against the said payment at`
  line `any subsequent stage of such payment.]`
obj_root_law_sections_28_aaa:
  sectionId (24870)
  sectionNo 28AAA
  orderNo 49
  title `Recovery of duties in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_aaa_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_aaa_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24870&sectionno=28AAA&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_28_aaa_content:
  string
  line `^1[28AAA. Recovery of duties in certain cases.--(1) Where an instrument issued to a person has`
  line `been obtained by him by means of --`
  line
  line `(a) collusion; or`
  line
  line `(b) wilful mis-statement; or`
  line
  line `(c) suppression of facts,`
  line
  line `for the purposes of this Act or the Foreign Trade (Development and Regulation) Act, 1992`
  line `(22 of 1992), ^2[or any other law, or any scheme of the Central Government, for the time being in force, by`
  line `such person] or his agent or employee and such instrument is utilised under the provisions of this Act or`
  line `the rules ^3[or regulations] made or notifications issued thereunder, by a person other than the person to`
  line `whom the instrument was issued, the duty relatable to such utilisation of instrument shall be deemed`
  line `never to have been exempted or debited and such duty shall be recovered from the person to whom the`
  line `said instrument was issued:`
  line
  line `Provided that the action relating to recovery of duty under this section against the person to whom the`
  line `instrument was issued shall be without prejudice to an action against the importer under section 28.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.-- For the purposes of this sub-section, "instrument" means any scrip or authorisation`
  line `or licence or certificate or such other document, by whatever name called, issued under the Foreign Trade`
  line `(Development and Regulation) Act, 1992 (22 of 1992), ^4[or duty credit issued under section 51B, with`
  line `respect to] a reward or incentive scheme or duty exemption scheme or duty remission scheme or such other scheme bestowing financial or fiscal benefits, which may be utilised under the provisions of this Act`
  line `or the rules made or notifications issued thereunder.`
  line .
  line
  line `Explanation 2.--The provisions of this sub-section shall apply to any utilisation of instrument so`
  line `obtained by the person referred to in this sub-section on or after the date on which the Finance Bill, 2012`
  line `receives the assent of the President, whether or not such instrument is issued to him prior to the date of`
  line `the assent.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the duty becomes recoverable in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (1), the`
  line `person from whom such duty is to be recovered, shall, in addition to such duty, be liable to pay interest at`
  line `the rate fixed by the Central Government under section 28AA and the amount of such interest shall be`
  line `calculated for the period beginning from the date of utilisation of the instrument till the date of recovery`
  line `of such duty.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of recovery under sub-section (2), the proper officer shall serve notice on the`
  line `person to whom the instrument was issued requiring him to show cause, within a period of thirty days`
  line `from the date of receipt of the notice, as to why the amount specified in the notice (excluding the interest)`
  line `should not be recovered from him, and after giving that person an opportunity of being heard, and after`
  line `considering the representation, if any, made by such person, determine the amount of duty or interest or`
  line `both to be recovered from such person, not being in excess of the amount specified in the notice, and pass`
  line `order to recover the amount of duty or interest or both and the person to whom the instrument was issued`
  line `shall repay the amount so specified in the notice within a period of thirty days from the date of receipt of`
  line `the said order, along with the interest due on such amount, whether or not the amount of interest is`
  line `specified separately.`
  line
  line `(4) Where an order determining the duty has been passed under section 28, no order to recover that`
  line `duty shall be passed under this section.`
  line
  line `(5) Where the person referred to in sub-section (3) fails to repay the amount within the period of`
  line `thirty days specified therein, it shall be recovered in the manner laid down in sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 142.]`
obj_root_law_sections_28_aaa_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 122 (w.e.f. 28-5-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 12 of 2020, s. 109, for "by such person" (w.e.f. 27-3-2020).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 109., ibid (w.e.f. 27-3-2020).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 12 of 2020, s. 109, for "with respect to" (w.e.f. 27-3-2020).`
obj_root_law_sections_28_b:
  sectionId (24871)
  sectionNo 28B
  orderNo 50
  title `Duties collected from the buyer to be deposited with the Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24871&sectionno=28B&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_28_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[28B. Duties collected from the buyer to be deposited with the Central Government.--(1)`
  line `Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in any order or direction of the Appellate Tribunal`
  line `^2[, National Tax Tribunal] or any Court or in any other provision of this Act or the regulations`
  line `made thereunder, ^3[every person who is liable to pay duty under this Act and has collected any amount in`
  line `excess of the duty assessed or determined or paid on any goods under this Act from the buyer of such`
  line `goods] in any manner as representing duty of customs, shall forthwith pay the amount so collected to the`
  line `credit of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `^4[(1A) Every person who has collected any amount in excess of the duty assessed or determined or`
  line `paid on any goods or has collected any amount as representing duty of customs on any goods which are`
  line `wholly exempt or are chargeable to nil rate of duty from any person in any manner, shall forthwith pay`
  line `the amount so collected to the credit of the Central Government.]`
  line
  line `^5[(2) Where any amount is required to be paid to the credit of the Central Government under`
  line `^6[sub-section (1) or sub-section (1A), as the case may be,] and which has not been so paid, the proper`
  line `officer may serve on the person liable to pay such amount, a notice requiring him to show cause why he`
  line `should not pay the amount, as specified in the notice to the credit of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The proper officer shall, after considering the representation, if any, made by the person on whom`
  line `the notice is served under sub-section (2), determine the amount due from such person (not being in`
  line `excess of the amount specified in the notice) and thereupon such person shall pay the amount so`
  line determined.
  line
  line `(4) The amount paid to the credit of the Central Government under ^7[sub-section (1) or`
  line `sub-section (1A) or sub-section (3) as the case may be,] shall be adjusted against the duty payable by the`
  line `person on finalisation of assessment or any other proceeding for determination of the duty relating to the`
  line `goods referred to in ^8[sub-section (1) and sub-section (1A).]`
  line
  line `(5) Where any surplus is left after the adjustment made under sub-section (4), the amount of such`
  line `surplus shall either be credited to the Fund or, as the case may be, refunded to the person who has borne`
  line `the incidence of such amount, in accordance with the provisions of section 27 and such person may make`
  line `an application under that section in such cases within six months from the date of the public notice to be`
  line `issued by the Assistant Commissioner of Customs for the refund of such surplus amount.]`
obj_root_law_sections_28_b_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 40 of 1991, s. 12 (w.e.f. 20-9-1991).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 49 of 2005, s. 30 and the Schedule, Part VI (w.e.f. 28-12-2005). This amendment has been struck down by the`
  line `Supreme Court's order dated 25th September, 2014 in the Madras Bar Association Vs Union of India.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 82 for "every person who has collected any amount from the buyer of any goods"`
  line `(w.e.f. 20-9-1991).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 68 (w.e.f. 10-5-2008)`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 82, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 20-9-1991).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. Act 18 of 2008, s. 68, for "sub-section (1)" ( w.e.f. 10-5-2008).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by s. 68, ibid., for "sub-section (1) or sub-section (3)" (w.e.f. 10-5-2008)`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by s. 68, ibid., for "sub-section (1)" (w.e.f. 10-5-2008).`
obj_root_law_sections_28_ba:
  sectionId (24872)
  sectionNo 28BA
  orderNo 51
  title `Provisional attachment to protect revenue in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_ba_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_ba_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24872&sectionno=28BA&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_28_ba_content:
  string
  line `^1[28BA. Provisional attachment to protect revenue in certain cases.--(1) Where, during the`
  line `pendency of any proceeding under section 28 ^2`
  line `[or section 28AAA or section 28B], the proper officer is of`
  line `of the opinion that for the purpose of protecting the interests of revenue, it is necessary so to do, he may,`
  line `with the previous approval of the ^3`
  line `[Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs], by`
  line `by order in writing, attach provisionally any property belonging to the person on whom notice is served`
  line `under ^4`
  line `[sub-section (1) or sub-section (4) of section 28] ^5`
  line `[or sub-section (3) of section 28AAA or`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 28B], as the case may be, in accordance with the rules made in this behalf under`
  line `section 142.`
  line
  line `(2) Every such provisional attachment shall cease to have effect after the expiry of a period of six`
  line `months from the date of the order made under sub-section (1):`
  line
  line `Provided that the ^6[Principal Chief Commissioner of Customs or Chief Commissioner of Customs]`
  line `may, for reasons to be recorded in writing, extend the aforesaid period by such further period or periods`
  line `as he thinks fit, so, however, that the total period of extension shall not in any case exceed two years:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where an application for settlement of case under section 127B is made to`
  line `the Settlement Commission, the period commencing from the date on which such application is made and ending with the date on which an order under sub-section (1) of section 127C is made shall be excluded`
  line `from the period specified in the preceding proviso.]`
obj_root_law_sections_28_ba_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2006, s. 23 (w.e.f. 13-7-2006).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 123, for "or section 28B" (w.e.f. 28-5-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 78, for "Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 6-08-2014).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 67, for "sub-section (1) of section 28" ( w.e.f. 10-5-2013).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 123, for "or sub-section (2) of section 28B" (w.e.f. 28-5-2012).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, section 78, for "Chief Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 6-8-2014)`
obj_root_law_sections_28_bb:
  sectionId (56412)
  sectionNo 28BB
  orderNo 52
  title `28BB. Time limit for completion of certain actions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_bb_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 92 (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=56412&sectionno=28BB&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_28_bb_content:
  string
  line `^1[28BB. Time limit for completion of certain actions.--(1) Any inquiry or investigation under this`
  line `Act, culminating in the issuance of a notice under sub-section (1) or sub-section (4) of section 28 shall be`
  line `completed by issuing such notice, within a period of two years from the date of initiation of audit, search,`
  line `seizure or summons, as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Principal Commissioner of Customs or the Commissioner of Customs may, on`
  line `sufficient cause being shown and for reasons to be recorded in writing, extend the said period to a further`
  line `period of one year.`
  line
  line `(2) For computing the period under sub-section (1), the period during which stay was granted by an`
  line `order of a court or tribunal, or the period for seeking information from an overseas authority through a`
  line `legal process, shall be excluded.`
  line
  line `Explanation.For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that nothing contained in this section`
  line `shall apply to any such proceeding initiated before the date on which the Finance Bill, 2021 receives the`
  line `assent of the President.]`
obj_root_law_sections_28_c:
  sectionId (24873)
  sectionNo 28C
  orderNo 53
  title `Price of goods to indicate the amount of duty paid thereon.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 40 of 1991, s. 13 (w.e.f. 20-9-1991).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24873&sectionno=28C&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_28_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[28C. Price of goods to indicate the amount of duty paid thereon.--Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in this Act or any other law for the time being in force, every person who is liable to pay duty`
  line `on any goods shall, at the time of clearance of the goods, prominently indicate in all the documents`
  line `relating to assessment, sales invoice, and other like documents, the amount of such duty which will form`
  line `part of the price at which such goods are to be sold.]`
obj_root_law_sections_28_d:
  sectionId (24874)
  sectionNo 28D
  orderNo 54
  title `Presumption that incidence of duty has been passed on to the buyer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_d_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 40 of 1991, s. 13 (w.e.f. 20-9-1991).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24874&sectionno=28D&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_28_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[28D. Presumption that incidence of duty has been passed on to the buyer.--Every person who`
  line `has paid the duty on any goods under this Act shall, unless the contrary is proved by him, be deemed to`
  line `have passed on the full incidence of such duty to the buyer of such goods.]`
obj_root_law_sections_28_e:
  sectionId (24875)
  sectionNo 28E
  orderNo 55
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_e_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_e_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24875&sectionno=28E&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_28_e_content:
  string
  line `^1[28E. Definitions.--In this Chapter, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line ^2*****;
  line
  line `^3[(b) "advance ruling" means a written decision on any of the questions referred to in section`
  line `28H raised by the applicant in his application in respect of any goods prior to its importation or`
  line exportation];
  line
  line ^4*****;
  line
  line `^5[(c) "applicant" means any person,--`
  line
  line `(i) holding a valid Importer-exporter Code Number granted under section 7 of the Foreign Trade (Development and Regulation) Act, 1992 (22 of 1992); or`
  line
  line `(ii) exporting any goods to India; or`
  line
  line `(iii) with a justifiable cause to the satisfaction of the Authority,`
  line
  line `who makes an application for advance ruling under section 28H;]`
  line
  line `^6[^7[** *]].`
  line
  line `(d)"application" means an application made to the Authority under sub-section (1) of section`
  line 28H;
  line
  line `^8[(e) "Authority" means the Customs Authority for Advance Rulings appointed under section`
  line 28EA;]
  line
  line ^9*****
  line
  line `^10**** *`
  line
  line `^11[^12[* **.]]`
obj_root_law_sections_28_e_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 103 (w.e.f. 11-5-1999).`
  line
  line `2. Clause (a) omitted by Act 13 of 2018, s. 64 (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 64, ibid., for clause (b) (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  line
  line `4.. Clause (ba) omitted by Act 33 of 2021, s. 12 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 64, ibid., for clause (c) (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 97 (w.e.f. 11-5-2007).`
  line
  line `7.The Explanation omitted by Act 6 of 2022, s. 90 (w.e.f. 30-3-2022).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 64, for clause (e) (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  line
  line `9. Clause (f) omitted by Act 33 of 2021, s. 12 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  line
  line `10. Clause (g) omitted by Act 33 of 2021, s. 12 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  line
  line `11. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 110, for clause (h) (w.e.f. 14-5-2003).`
  line
  line `12.Clause (h) omitted by Act 6 of 2022, s. 90 (w.e.f. 30-3-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_28_ea:
  sectionId (24876)
  sectionNo 28EA
  orderNo 56
  title `Customs Authority for Advance Rulings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_ea_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_ea_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24876&sectionno=28EA&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_28_ea_content:
  string
  line `^1[28EA. Customs Authority for Advance Rulings.--(1) The Board may, for the purposes of giving`
  line `advance rulings under this Act, by notification, appoint an officer of the rank of Principal Commissioner`
  line `of Customs or Commissioner of Customs to function as a Customs Authority for Advance Rulings:`
  line
  line ^2****.
  line
  line `(2) The offices of the Authority may be established in New Delhi and at such other places, as the`
  line `Board may deem fit.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Authority shall exercise the powers and authority`
  line `conferred on it by or under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_28_ea_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 65 (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  line
  line `2. The Proviso omitted by Act 33 of 2021, s. 12 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_28_f:
  sectionId (24877)
  sectionNo 28F
  orderNo 57
  title `Authority for advance rulings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_f_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_f_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24877&sectionno=28F&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_28_f_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[28F. Authority for advance rulings.--^2***:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Member from the Indian Revenue Service (Customs and Central Excise), who is`
  line `qualified to be a Member of the Board, shall be the revenue Member of the ^3`
  line `[Appellate Authority] for the`
  line `purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) On and from the date on which the Finance Bill, 2017 receives the assent of the President, every`
  line `application and proceeding pending before the erstwhile Authority for Advance Rulings (Central Excise,`
  line `Customs and Service Tax) shall stand transferred to the Authority from the stage at which such`
  line `application or proceeding stood as on the date of such assent.]`
  line
  line ^4
  line `[(3) On and from the date of appointment of the Customs Authority for Advance Rulings, every`
  line `application and proceeding pending before the erstwhile Authority for Advance Rulings shall stand`
  line `transferred to the Authority from the stage at which such application or proceeding stood as on the date of`
  line `such appointment.]`
obj_root_law_sections_28_f_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 94, for section 28F (w.e.f. 31-3-2017).`
  line
  line `2. Sub-section (1) omitted by Act 33 of 2021, s. 12 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 66, ibid., for Authority (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by s. 66, ibid (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
