  line `[Vacancies, etc., not to invalidate proceedings.]Omitted by the Finance Act, (7 of 2017),`
  line `s. 95 (w.e.f. 31-3-2017).`
obj_root_law_sections_28_g_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28_h:
  sectionId (24879)
  sectionNo 28H
  orderNo 59
  title `Application for advance ruling.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_h_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_h_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24879&sectionno=28H&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_28_h_content:
  string
  line `(1) An applicant desirous of obtaining an advance ruling`
  line `under this Chapter may make an application in such form and in such manner ^1[and accompanied by such fee] as may be prescribed, stating the question on which the advance ruling is sought..`
  line
  line `(2) The question on which the advance ruling is sought shall be in respect of, --`
  line
  line `(a) classification of goods under the Customs Tariff Act, 1975 (51 of 1975);`
  line
  line `(b) applicability of a notification issued under sub-section (1) of section 25, having a bearing on`
  line `the rate of duty;`
  line
  line `(c) the principles to be adopted for the purposes of determination of value of the goods under the`
  line `provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(d) applicability of notifications issued in respect of tax or duties under this Act or the Customs`
  line `Tariff Act, 1975 (51 of 1975) or any tax or duty chargeable under any other law for the time being in`
  line `force in the same manner as duty of customs leviable under this Act or the Customs Tariff Act;]`
  line
  line ^3
  line `[(e) determination of origin of the goods in terms of the rules notified under the Customs Tariff`
  line `Act, 1975 (51 of 1975) and matters relating thereto.]`
  line
  line ^4
  line `[(f) any other matter as the Central Government may, by notification, specify.]`
  line
  line ^5[*****].
  line
  line `(4) An applicant may withdraw his application ^6[at any time before an advance ruling is pronounced].`
  line .
  line
  line `^7[(5) The applicant may be represented by any person resident in India who is authorised in thisbehalf.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section resident shall have the same meaning as`
  line `assigned to it in clause (42) of section 2 of the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961).]`
obj_root_law_sections_28_h_footnotes:
  string
  line `1.Ins. by Act 6 of 2022, s. 91, (w.e.f. 30-3-2022).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 67, for clause (d) (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 67 (w.e.f. 13-5-2005).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 67 (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  line
  line `5. Sub-section 3 omitted by Act 6 of 2022, s. 91 (w.e.f. 30-3-2022).`
  line
  line `6. Subs by Act 6 of 2022, s. 91 for within thirty days from the date of the application (w.e.f. 30-3-2022).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 67 (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_28_i:
  sectionId (24880)
  sectionNo 28I
  orderNo 60
  title `Procedure on receipt of application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_i_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_i_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24880&sectionno=28I&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_28_i_content:
  string
  line `(1) On receipt of an application, the Authority shall`
  line `cause a copy thereof to be forwarded to the ^1`
  line `[Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of`
  line `Customs] and, if necessary, call upon him to furnish the relevant records:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any records have been called for by the Authority in any case, such records shall,`
  line `as soon as possible, be returned to the ^1`
  line `[Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of`
  line Customs].
  line
  line `(2) The Authority may, after examining the application and the records called for, by order, either`
  line `allow or reject the application:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Authority shall not allow the application ^2`
  line `*** where the question raised in the`
  line `application is --`
  line
  line `(a) already pending in the applicant's case before any officer of customs, the Appellate Tribunal`
  line `or any Court;`
  line
  line `(b) the same as in a matter already decided by the Appellate Tribunal or any Court:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no application shall be rejected under this sub-section unless an opportunity has`
  line `been given to the applicant of being heard:`
  line
  line `Provided also that where the application is rejected, reasons for such rejection shall be given in the`
  line order.
  line
  line `(3) A copy of every order made under sub-section (2) shall be sent to the applicant and to the`
  line ^3
  line `[Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs].`
  line
  line `(4) Where an application is allowed under sub-section (2), the Authority shall, after examining such`
  line `further material as may be placed before it by the applicant or obtained by the Authority, pronounce its`
  line `advance ruling on the question specified in the application.`
  line
  line `(5) On a request received from the applicant, the Authority shall, before pronouncing its advance`
  line `ruling, provide an opportunity to the applicant of being heard, either in person or through a`
  line `duly authorised representative.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, authorised representative shall have the`
  line `meaning assigned to it in sub-section (2) of section 146A.`
  line
  line `(6) The Authority shall pronounce its advance ruling in writing within ^4`
  line `[three months] of the receipt`
  line `of application.`
  line
  line `(7) A copy of the advance ruling pronounced by the Authority, duly signed ^5*** and certified in the prescribed manner shall be sent to the applicant and to the ^3`
  line `[Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs], as soon as may be, after such pronouncement.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_i_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 78 for Commissioner of Customs (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  line
  line `2. The words except in the case of a resident applicant omitted by Act 20 of 2002, s. 122 (w.e.f. 11-5-2002).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 78, for Commissioner of Customs (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 68, for six months (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  line
  line `5. The words “by the Members” omitted by Act 6 of 2022, s. 92 (w.e.f. 30-3-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_28_j:
  sectionId (24881)
  sectionNo 28J
  orderNo 61
  title `Applicability of advance ruling.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_j_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_j_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24881&sectionno=28J&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_28_j_content:
  string
  line `(1) The advance ruling pronounced by the Authority under`
  line `section 28-I shall be binding only--`
  line
  line `(a) on the applicant who had sought it;`
  line
  line `(b) in respect of any matter referred to in sub-section (2) of section 28H;`
  line
  line `(c) on the ^1[Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs], and the customs authorities subordinate to him, in respect of the applicant.`
  line
  line `^2[(2) The advance ruling referred to in sub-section (1) shall remain valid for three years or till there is a change in law or facts on the basis of which the advance ruling has been pronounced, whichever is earlier:`
  line
  line `Provided that in respect of any advance ruling in force on the date on which the Finance Bill, 2022 receives the assent of the President, the said period of three years shall be reckoned from the date on which the said Finance Bill receives the assent of the President.]`
obj_root_law_sections_28_j_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 78, for Commissioner of Customs (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 6 of 2022, s. 93, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 30-3-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_28_k:
  sectionId (24882)
  sectionNo 28K
  orderNo 62
  title `Advance ruling to be void in certain circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_k_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_k_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24882&sectionno=28K&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_28_k_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Authority finds, on a`
  line `representation made to it by the ^1`
  line `[Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs] or`
  line `otherwise, that an advance ruling pronounced by it under sub-section (6) of section 28-I has been obtained`
  line `by the applicant by fraud or misrepresentation of facts, it may, by order, declare such ruling to be`
  line `void ab initio and thereupon all the provisions of this Act shall apply ^2`
  line `*** to the applicant as if such`
  line `advance ruling had never been made.`
  line
  line `^3[Provided that in computing the period of two years referred to in clause (a) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 28, or five years referred to in sub-section (4) thereof, for service of notice for recovery of any`
  line `duty not levied, short-levied, not paid or short-paid on account of the advance ruling, the period beginning`
  line `with the date of such advance ruling and ending with the date of the order under this sub-section shall be`
  line excluded.]
  line
  line `(2) A copy of the order made under sub-section (1) shall be sent to the applicant and the ^4[Principal`
  line `Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs].`
obj_root_law_sections_28_k_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 78, for "Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  line
  line `2. The brackets and words "(after excluding the period beginning with the date of such advance ruling and ending with the date`
  line `of order under this sub-section)" omitted by Act 13 of 2018, s. 69 (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  line
  line `3. The proviso ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 69 (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 78, for "Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_28_ka:
  sectionId (24883)
  sectionNo 28KA
  orderNo 63
  title Appeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_ka_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_ka_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24883&sectionno=28KA&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_28_ka_content:
  string
  line `^1[28KA. Appeal.--(1) Any officer authorised by the Board, by notification, or the applicant may file an`
  line `appeal to the ^2[High Court] against any ruling or order passed by the Authority, within sixty days from`
  line `the date of the communication of such ruling or order, in such form and manner as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the ^2[High Court] is satisfied that the appellant was prevented by sufficient`
  line `cause from presenting the appeal within the period so specified, it may allow a further period of thirty`
  line `days for filing such appeal.`
  line
  line ^3****
obj_root_law_sections_28_ka_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 28KA shall stand inserted (date to be notified) by Act 13 of 2018, s. 70.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 33 of 2021, s. 12, for Appellate Authority (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  line
  line `3. Sub-section (2) omitted by Act 33 of 2021, s. 12 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_28_l:
  sectionId (24884)
  sectionNo 28L
  orderNo 64
  title `Powers of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_l_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 71, ibid., for "Authority" (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24884&sectionno=28L&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_28_l_content:
  string
  line `28L. Powers of ^1[Authority or Appellate Authority].--(1) The ^1[Authority or Appellate Authority]`
  line `shall, for the purpose of exercising its powers regarding discovery and inspection, enforcing the`
  line `attendance of any person and examining him on oath, issuing commissions and compelling production of`
  line `books of account and other records, have all the powers of a civil court under the Code of Civil`
  line `Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908).`
  line
  line `(2) The ^1[Authority or Appellate Authority] shall be deemed to be a civil court for the purposes of`
  line `section 195, but not for the purposes of Chapter XXVI of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973`
  line `(2 of 1974), and every proceeding before the ^1[Authority or Appellate Authority] shall be deemed to be a`
  line `judicial proceeding within the meaning of sections 193 and 228, and for the purpose of section 196, of the`
  line `Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_28_m:
  sectionId (24885)
  sectionNo 28M
  orderNo 65
  title `Procedure for Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_m_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_m_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24885&sectionno=28M&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_28_m_content:
  string
  line `^1[28M. Procedure for Authority ^2***.--(1) The Authority shall follow such`
  line `procedure as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line ^3****
obj_root_law_sections_28_m_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 72, ibid., for section 28M (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  line
  line `2. The words “and Appellate Authority” omitted by Act 33 of 2021, s. 12 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  line
  line `3. Sub-section (2) omitted by s. 12, ibid. (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (24886)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 66
  title `Arrival of vessels and aircrafts in India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 69 (w.e.f. 10-5-2013).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24886&sectionno=29&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) The person-in-charge of a vessel or an aircraft`
  line `entering India from any place outside India shall not cause or permit the vessel or aircraft to call or land--`
  line
  line `(a) for the first time after arrival in India; or`
  line
  line `(b) at any time while it is carrying passengers or cargo brought in that vessel or aircraft;`
  line
  line `at any place other than a customs port or a customs airport, as the case may be ^1`
  line `[unless permitted by the`
  line Board].
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sub-section (1) shall not apply in relation to any vessel or aircraft which is`
  line `compelled by accident, stress of weather or other unavoidable cause to call or land at a place other than a`
  line `customs port or customs airport but the person-in-charge of any such vessel or aircraft--`
  line
  line `(a) shall immediately report the arrival of the vessel or the landing of the aircraft to the nearest`
  line `customs officer or the officer-in-charge of a police station and shall on demand produce to him the`
  line `log book belonging to the vessel or the aircraft;`
  line
  line `(b) shall not without the consent of any such officer permit any goods carried in the vessel or the`
  line `aircraft to be unloaded from, or any of the crew or passengers to depart from the vicinity of, the`
  line `vessel or the aircraft; and`
  line
  line `(c) shall comply with any directions given by any such officer with respect to any such goods,`
  line
  line `and no passenger or member of the crew shall, without the consent of any such officer, leave the`
  line `immediate vicinity of the vessel or the aircraft:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall prohibit the departure of any crew or passengers from the`
  line `vicinity of, or the removal of goods from, the vessel or aircraft where the departure or removal is`
  line `necessary for reasons of health, safety or the preservation of life or property.`
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (24887)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 67
  title `Delivery of arrival manifest or import manifest or import report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24887&sectionno=30&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `30. Delivery of ^1`
  line `[arrival manifest or import manifest] or import report.--^2`
  line `[(1) The person-incharge of --`
  line
  line `(i) a vessel; or`
  line
  line `(ii) an aircraft; or`
  line
  line `(iii) a vehicle,`
  line
  line `carrying imported goods ^3`
  line `[or export goods] or any other person as may be specified by the Central`
  line `Government, by notification in the Official Gazette, in this behalf shall, in the case of a vessel or an`
  line `aircraft, deliver to the proper officer ^4`
  line `[an ^1`
  line `[arrival manifest or import manifest] by presenting`
  line `electronically prior to the arrival] of the vessel or the aircraft, as the case may be, and in the case of a`
  line `vehicle, an import report within twelve hours after its arrival in the customs station, in ^5`
  line `[such form and`
  line `manner as may be prescribed] and if the ^1`
  line `[arrival manifest or import manifest] or the import report or any`
  line `part thereof, is not delivered to the proper officer within the time specified in this sub-section and if the`
  line `proper officer is satisfied that there was no sufficient cause for such delay, the person-in-charge or any`
  line `other person referred to in this sub-section, who caused such delay, shall be liable to a penalty not`
  line `exceeding fifty thousand rupees:]`
  line
  line ^6
  line `[Provided that the ^7`
  line `[Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs] may, in cases`
  line `cases where it is not feasible to deliver ^1`
  line `[arrival manifest or import manifest] by presenting electronically,`
  line `allow the same to be delivered in any other manner.]`
  line
  line `(2) The person delivering the ^8`
  line `[arrival manifest or import manifest] or import report shall at the foot`
  line `thereof make and subscribe to a declaration as to the truth of its contents.`
  line
  line `(3) If the proper officer is satisfied that the ^8`
  line `[arrival manifest or import manifest] or import report is in`
  line `any way incorrect or incomplete, and that there was no fraudulent intention, he may permit it to be`
  line `amended or supplemented.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 56, for "import manifest" (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 112, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f 14-5-2003).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 73 (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 70, for "an import manifest prior to the arrival" (w.e.f. 10-5-2013).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 73, for "the prescribed form" (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 70 (w.e.f. 10-5-2013).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 78, for "Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 6-8-2014)`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 56, for "import manifest" (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_30_a:
  sectionId (24888)
  sectionNo 30A
  orderNo 68
  title `Passenger and crew arrival manifest and passenger name record information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 98 (w.e.f. 31-3-2017).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24888&sectionno=30A&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_30_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[30A. Passenger and crew arrival manifest and passenger name record information.--(1) The`
  line `person-in-charge of a conveyance that enters India from any place outside India or any other person as`
  line `may be specified by the Central Government by notification in the Official Gazette, shall deliver to the`
  line `proper officer--`
  line
  line `(i) the passenger and crew arrival manifest before arrival in the case of an aircraft or a vessel and`
  line `upon arrival in the case of a vehicle; and`
  line
  line `(ii) the passenger name record information of arriving passengers,`
  line
  line `in such form, containing such particulars, in such manner and within such time, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the passenger and crew arrival manifest or the passenger name record information or any`
  line `part thereof is not delivered to the proper officer within the prescribed time and if the proper officer is`
  line `satisfied that there was no sufficient cause for such delay, the person-in-charge or the other person`
  line `referred to in sub-section (1) shall be liable to such penalty, not exceeding fifty thousand rupees, as may`
  line `be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (24889)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 69
  title `Imported goods not to be unloaded from vessel until entry inwards granted.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 56, for "import manifest" (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24889&sectionno=31&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) The master of a vessel shall not permit the unloading of any imported goods until an order has been`
  line `given by the proper officer granting entry inwards to such vessel.`
  line
  line `(2) No order under sub-section (1) shall be given until an ^1`
  line `[arrival manifest or import manifest] has`
  line `been delivered or the proper officer is satisfied that there was sufficient cause for not delivering it.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing in this section shall apply to the unloading of baggage accompanying a passenger or a`
  line `member of the crew, mail bags, animals, perishable goods and hazardous goods.`
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (24890)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 70
  title `Imported goods not to be unloaded unless mentioned in arrival manifest or import manifest or import report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 56, for "import manifest" (w.e.f. 28-3-2018)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24890&sectionno=32&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `32. Imported goods not to be unloaded unless mentioned in ^1`
  line `[arrival manifest or import`
  line `manifest] or import report.--No imported goods required to be mentioned under the regulations in an`
  line ^1
  line `[arrival manifest or import manifest] or import report shall, except with the permission of the proper`
  line `officer, be unloaded at any customs station unless they are specified in such manifest or report for being`
  line `unloaded at that customs station.`
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (24891)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 71
  title `Unloading and loading of goods at approved places only.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24891&sectionno=33&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `Except with the permission of the`
  line `proper officer, no imported goods shall be unloaded, and no export goods shall be loaded, at any place`
  line `other than a place approved under clause (a) of section 8 for the unloading or loading of such goods.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (24892)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 72
  title `Goods not to be unloaded or loaded except under supervision of customs officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24892&sectionno=34&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line Imported
  line `goods shall not be unloaded from, and export goods shall not be loaded on, any conveyance except under`
  line `the supervision of the proper officer:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Board may, by notification in the Official Gazette, give general permission and the`
  line `proper officer may in any particular case give special permission, for any goods or class of goods to be`
  line `unloaded or loaded without the supervision of the proper officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (24893)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 73
  title `Restrictions on goods being water-borne.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24893&sectionno=35&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `No imported goods shall be water-borne for being`
  line `landed from any vessel, and no export goods which are not accompanied by a shipping bill, shall be`
  line `water-borne for being shipped, unless the goods are accompanied by a boat-note in the prescribed form:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Board may, by notification in the Official Gazette, give general permission, and the`
  line `proper officer may in any particular case give special permission, for any goods or any class of goods to`
  line `be water-borne without being accompanied by a boat-note.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (24894)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 74
  title `Restrictions on unloading and loading of goods on holidays, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24894&sectionno=36&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `No imported goods shall be`
  line `unloaded from, and no export goods shall be loaded on, any conveyance on any Sunday or on any holiday`
  line `observed by the Customs Department or on any other day after the working hours, except after giving the`
  line `prescribed notice and on payment of the prescribed fees, if any:`
  line
  line `Provided that no fees shall be levied for the unloading and loading of baggage accompanying a`
  line `passenger or a member of the crew, and mail bags.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (24895)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 75
  title `Power to board conveyances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24895&sectionno=37&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `The proper officer may, at any time, board any conveyance`
  line `carrying imported goods or export goods and may remain on such conveyance for such period as he`
  line `considers necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (24896)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 76
  title `Power to require production of documents and ask questions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24896&sectionno=38&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of carrying`
  line `out the provisions of this Act, the proper officer may require the person-in-charge of any conveyance or`
  line `animal carrying imported goods or export goods to produce any document and to answer any questions`
  line `and thereupon such person shall produce such documents and answer such questions.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (24897)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 77
  title `Export goods not to be loaded on vessel until entry-outwards granted.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24897&sectionno=39&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `The master of a`
  line `vessel shall not permit the loading of any export goods, other than baggage and mail bags, until an order`
  line `has been given by the proper officer granting entry-outwards to such vessel.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (24898)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 78
  title `Export goods not to be loaded unless duly passed by proper officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24898&sectionno=40&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `The person-in-charge of`
  line `a conveyance shall not permit the loading at a customs station--`
  line
  line `(a) of export goods, other than baggage and mail bags, unless a shipping bill or bill of export or a`
  line `bill of transhipment, as the case may be, duly passed by the proper officer, has been handed over to`
  line `him by the exporter;`
  line
  line `(b) of baggage and mail bags, unless their export has been duly permitted by the proper officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (24899)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 79
  title `Delivery of departure manifest or export manifest or export report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24899&sectionno=41&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `41. Delivery of ^1[departure manifest or export manifest] or export report.--(1) ^2[The person-in-charge of a conveyance carrying export goods or imported goods or any other person as may be specified`
  line `by the Central Government, by notification, shall, before departure of the conveyance from a customs`
  line `station, deliver to the proper officer in the case of a vessel or aircraft, a departure manifest or an export`
  line `manifest by presenting electronically, and in the case of a vehicle, an export report, in such form and`
  line `manner as may be prescribed and in case, such person-in-charge or other person fails to deliver the`
  line `departure manifest or export manifest or the export report or any part thereof within such time, and the`
  line `proper officer is satisfied that there is no sufficient cause for such delay, such person-in-charge or other`
  line `person shall be liable to pay penalty not exceeding fifty thousand rupees.]`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
  line
  line `^4[Provided that the ^5[Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs may, in cases`
  line `where it is not feasible to deliver the ^6[departure manifest or export manifest] by presenting electronically,`
  line `allow the same to be delivered in any other manner.]`
  line
  line `(2) The person delivering the ^6[departure manifest or export manifest] or export report shall at the`
  line `foot thereof make and subscribe to a declaration as to the truth of its contents.`
  line
  line `(3) If the proper officer is satisfied that the ^6[departure manifest or export manifest] or export report is`
  line `in any way incorrect or incomplete and that there was no fraudulent intention, he may permit such`
  line `manifest or report to be amended or supplemented.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 56, for "export manifest" (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 70, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-8-2019).`
  line
  line `3. Proviso omitted by Act of 23 of 2004, s. 66 (w.e.f. 10-9-2004).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 71 (w.e.f. 10-5-2013).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 78, for "Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 56, for "export manifest" (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_41_a:
  sectionId (24900)
  sectionNo 41A
  orderNo 80
  title `Passenger and crew departure manifest and passenger name record information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 99 (w.e.f. 31-3-2017).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24900&sectionno=41A&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_41_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[41A. Passenger and crew departure manifest and passenger name record information.--(1)`
  line `The person-in-charge of a conveyance that departs from India to a place outside India or any other person`
  line `as may be specified by the Central Government by notification in the Official Gazette, shall deliver to the`
  line `proper officer--`
  line
  line `(i) the passenger and crew departure manifest; and`
  line
  line `(ii) the passenger name record information of departing passengers,`
  line
  line `in such form, containing such particulars, in such manner and within such time, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the passenger and crew departure manifest or the passenger name record information or`
  line `any part thereof is not delivered to the proper officer within the prescribed time and if the proper officer is`
  line `satisfied that there was no sufficient cause for such delay, the person-in-charge or the other person`
  line `referred to in sub-section (1) shall be liable to such penalty, not exceeding fifty thousand rupees, as may`
  line `be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (24901)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 81
  title `No conveyance to leave without written order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 100, for "Assistant Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 11-5-1999).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24901&sectionno=42&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `(1) The person-in-charge of a conveyance`
  line `which has brought any imported goods or has loaded any export goods at a customs station shall not`
  line `cause or permit the conveyance to depart from that customs station until a written order to that effect has`
  line `been given by the proper officer.`
  line
  line `(2) No such order shall be given until,--`
  line
  line `(a) the person-in-charge of the conveyance has answered the questions put to him under`
  line `section 38;`
  line
  line `(b) the provisions of section 41 have been complied with;`
  line
  line `(c) the shipping bills or bills of export, the bills of transhipment, if any, and such other`
  line `documents as the proper officer may require have been delivered to him;`
  line
  line `(d) all duties leviable on any stores consumed in such conveyance, and all charges and penalties`
  line `due in respect of such conveyance or from the person-in-charge thereof have been paid or the`
  line `payment secured by such guarantee or deposit of such amount as the proper officer may direct;`
  line
  line `(e) the person-in-charge of the conveyance has satisfied the proper officer that no penalty`
  line `is leviable on him under section 116 or the payment of any penalty that may be levied upon him`
  line `under that section has been secured by such guarantee or deposit of such amount as the proper officer`
  line `may direct;`
  line
  line `(f) in any case where any export goods have been loaded without payment of export duty or in`
  line `contravention of any provision of this Act or any other law for the time being in force relating to`
  line `export of goods,--`
  line
  line `(i) such goods have been unloaded, or`
  line
  line `(ii) where the ^1[Assistant Commissioner of Customs or Deputy Commissioner of Customs] is`
  line `satisfied that it is not practicable to unload such goods, the person-in-charge of the conveyance`
  line `has given an undertaking, secured by such guarantee or deposit of such amount as the proper`
  line `officer may direct, for bringing back the goods to India.`
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (24902)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 82
  title `Exemption of certain classes of conveyances from certain provisions of this Chapter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24902&sectionno=43&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions of sections 30, 41 and 42 shall not apply to a vehicle which carries no goods other than`
  line `the luggage of its occupants.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, exempt the following`
  line `classes of conveyances from all or any of the provisions of this Chapter--`
  line
  line `(a) conveyances belonging to the Government or any foreign Government;`
  line
  line `(b) vessels and aircraft which temporarily enter India by reason of any emergency.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (24903)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 83
  title `Chapter not to apply to baggage and postal articles.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24903&sectionno=44&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Chapter shall not`
  line `apply to (a) baggage, and (b) goods imported or to be exported by post.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (24904)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 84
  title `Restrictions on custody and removal of imported goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24904&sectionno=45&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided in`
  line `any law for the time being in force, all imported goods unloaded in a customs area shall remain in the`
  line `custody of such person as may be approved by the ^1[Principal Commissioner of Customs or`
  line `Commissioner of Customs] until they are cleared for home consumption or are warehoused or are`
  line `transhipped in accordance with the provisions of Chapter VIII.`
  line
  line `(2) The person having custody of any imported goods in a customs area, whether under the provisions`
  line `of sub-section (1) or under any law for the time being in force,--`
  line
  line `(a) shall keep a record of such goods and send a copy thereof to the proper officer;`
  line
  line `(b) shall not permit such goods to be removed from the customs area or otherwise dealt with,`
  line `except under and in accordance with the permission in writing of the proper officer ^2[or in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed].`
  line
  line `^3[(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in any law for the time being in force, if any imported`
  line `goods are pilferred after unloading thereof in a customs area while in the custody of a person referred to`
  line `in sub-section (1), that person shall be liable to pay duty on such goods at the rate prevailing on the date`
  line `of delivery of an ^4[arrival manifest or import manifest] or, as the case may be, an import report to the`
  line `proper officer under section 30 for the arrival of the conveyance in which the said goods were carried.]`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 78, for "Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 75 (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 58 (w.e.f. 26-5-1995).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 56, for "import manifest" (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (24905)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 85
  title `Entry of goods on importation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24905&sectionno=46&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1) The importer of any goods, other than goods intended for`
  line `transit or transhipment, shall make entry thereof by presenting`
  line ^1
  line `[electronically] ^2`
  line `[on the customs`
  line `automated system] to the proper officer a bill of entry for home consumption or warehousing ^3`
  line `[pin such`
  line `form and manner as may be prescribed]:`
  line
  line ^4
  line `[Provided that the ^5`
  line `[Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs] may, in cases`
  line `cases where it is not feasible to make entry by presenting electronically ^2`
  line `[on the customs automated`
  line `system], allow an entry to be presented in any other manner:`
  line
  line `Provided further that] if the importer makes and subscribes to a declaration before the proper officer,`
  line `to the effect that he is unable for want of full information to furnish all the particulars of the goods`
  line `required under this sub-section, the proper officer may, pending the production of such information,`
  line `permit him, previous to the entry thereof (a) to examine the goods in the presence of an officer of`
  line `customs, or (b) to deposit the goods in a public warehouse appointed under section 57 without`
  line `warehousing the same.`
  line
  line `(2) Save as otherwise permitted by the proper officer, a bill of entry shall include all the goods`
  line `mentioned in the bill of lading or other receipt given by the carrier to the consignor.`
  line
  line ^6
  line `[(3) The importer shall present the bill of entry under sub-section (1) ^7[before the end of the day (including holidays) preceding the day] on which the aircraft or vessel or vehicle carrying the goods`
  line `arrives at a customs station at which such goods are to be cleared for home consumption or warehousing:`
  line
  line `^8[Provided that the Board may, in such cases as it may deem fit, prescribe different time limits for presentation of the bill of entry, which shall not be later than the end of the day of such arrival:`
  line
  line `Provided further that] a bill of entry may be presented ^9[at any time not exceeding thirty days prior to] the`
  line `expected arrival of the aircraft or vessel or vehicle by which the goods have been shipped for importation`
  line `into India:`
  line
  line `^10[Provided also that] where the bill of entry is not presented within the time so specified and the`
  line `proper officer is satisfied that there was no sufficient cause for such delay, the importer shall pay such`
  line `charges for late presentation of the bill of entry as may be prescribed.]`
  line
  line `(4) The importer while presenting a bill of entry shall ^11*** make and subscribe to a declaration as to`
  line `the truth of the contents of such bill of entry and shall, in support of such declaration, produce to the proper officer the invoice, if any, ^12`
  line `[and such other documents relating to the imported goods as may be`
  line prescribed].
  line
  line ^13
  line `[(4A) The importer who presents a bill of entry shall ensure the following, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the accuracy and completeness of the information given therein;`
  line
  line `(b) the authenticity and validity of any document supporting it; and`
  line
  line `(c) compliance with the restriction or prohibition, if any, relating to the goods under this Act or`
  line `under any other law for the time being in force.]`
  line
  line `(5) If the proper officer is satisfied that the interests of revenue are not prejudicially affected and that`
  line `there was no fraudulent intention, he may permit substitution of a bill of entry for home consumption for`
  line `a bill of entry for warehousing or vice versa.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 8 of 2011, s. 44 (w.e.f. 8-4-2011).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 76 (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 76, ibid., for "in the prescribed form" (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 8 of 2011, s. 44, for Provided that (w.e.f. 8-4-2011).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 78, for "Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 100 for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 31-3-2017).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 93, for "before the end of the next day following the day (excluding holidays)" (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by s. 93, ibid., for Provided that (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 76, for "within thirty days of" (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  line
  line `10. The words "at the foot thereof" omitted by Act 8 of 2011, s. 44 (w.e.f. 8-4-2011)`
  line
  line `11. Subs. by 13 of 2021, s. 93, for "Provided further that" (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
  line `12. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 76, for "relating to the imported goods" (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  line
  line `13. Ins. by s. 76, ibid. (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (24906)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 86
  title `Clearance of goods for home consumption.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24906&sectionno=47&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] Where the proper officer is satisfied that`
  line `any goods entered for home consumption are not prohibited goods and the importer has paid the import`
  line `duty, if any, assessed thereon and any charges payable under this Act in respect of the same, the proper`
  line `officer may make an order permitting clearance of the goods for home consumption:`
  line
  line ^2[
  line `^3[Provided that such order may also be made electronically through the customs automated system`
  line `system on the basis or risk evaluation through appropriate selection criteria:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, permit`
  line `certain class of importers to make deferred payment of said duty or any charges in such manner as may be`
  line `provided by rules.]`
  line
  line `^4[(2)`
  line `^5[The importer shall pay the import duty--`
  line
  line `(a) on the date of presentation of the bill of entry in the case of self assessment; or`
  line
  line `(b) within one day (excluding holidays) from the date on which the bill of entry is returned to him`
  line `by the proper officer for payment of duty in the case of assessment, reassessment or provisional`
  line `assessment; or`
  line
  line `(c) in the case of deferred payment under the proviso to sub-section (1), from such due date as`
  line `may be specified by rules made in this behalf,`
  line
  line `and if he fails to pay the duty within the time so specified, he shall pay interest on the duty not paid or`
  line `short-paid till the date of its payment, at such rate, not less than ten per cent. but not exceeding thirty-six`
  line `per cent. per annum, as may be fixed by the Central Government, by notification in the Official Gazette.]`
  line
  line `^6[Provided that the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify the class`
  line `or classes of importers who shall pay such duty electronically:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where the bill of entry is returned for payment of duty before the`
  line `commencement of the Customs (Amendment) Act, 1991 (55 of 1991) and the importer has not paid such`
  line `duty before such commencement, the date of return of such bill of entry to him shall be deemed to be the`
  line `date of such commencement for the purpose of this section:]`
  line
  line `^7[^8[Provided also that if the Board is satisfied that it is necessary in the public interest so to do, it`
  line `may, by order for reasons to be recorded, waive the whole or part of any interest payable under this`
  line section.]
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 47 renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 55 of 1991, s. 3, (w.e.f. 23-12-1991).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 121 (w.e.f. 14-5-2016).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 77, for "Provided that" (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 55 of 1991, s. 3 (w.e.f. 23-12-1991).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 101, for certain words, brackets, letters and figure (w.e.f. 31-3-2017). Earlier certain words,`
  line
  line `brackets, letters and figure were substituted by Act 28 of 2016, s. 121 (w.e.f. 14-5-2016).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 124, for "Provided that" (w.e.f. 28-5-2012).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 59 (w.e.f. 26-5-1995).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 124, for "Provided further that" (w.e.f. 28-5-2012).`
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (24907)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 87
  title `Procedure in case of goods not cleared, warehoused, or transhipped within thirty days after unloading.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24907&sectionno=48&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `48. Procedure in case of goods not cleared, warehoused, or transhipped within ^1[thirty days]`
  line `after unloading.--If any goods brought into India from a place outside India are not cleared for home`
  line `consumption or warehoused or transhipped ^2[within ^3[thirty days]] from the date of the unloading thereof`
  line `thereof at a customs station or within such further time as the proper officer may allow or if the title to`
  line `any imported goods is relinquished, such goods may, after notice to the importer and with the permission`
  line `of the proper officer be sold by the person having the custody thereof:`
  line
  line `Provided that --`
  line
  line `(a) animals, perishable goods and hazardous goods, may, with the permission of the proper`
  line `officer, be sold at any time;`
  line
  line `(b) arms and ammunition may be sold at such time and place and in such manner as the Central`
  line `Government may direct.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- In this section, "arms" and "ammunition" have the meanings respectively assigned to`
  line `them in the Arms Act, 1959 (54 of 1959).`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 55 of 1991, s. 4, for "two months" (w.e.f. 21-12-1991).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 80 of 1985 s. 4, for "within two months" (w.e.f. 27-12-1985).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 55 of 1991, s. 4, for "forty-five days" (w.e.f. 21-12-1991).`
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (24908)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 88
  title `Storage of imported goods in warehouse pending clearance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 102, for section 49 (w.e.f. 31-3-2017).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24908&sectionno=49&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `^1[49. Storage of imported goods in warehouse pending clearance or removal.--Where,--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of any imported goods, whether dutiable or not, entered for home consumption, the`
  line `Assistant Commissioner of Customs or Deputy Commissioner of Customs is satisfied on the`
  line `application of the importer that the goods cannot be cleared within a reasonable time;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of any imported dutiable goods, entered for warehousing, the Assistant`
  line `Commissioner of Customs or Deputy Commissioner of Customs is satisfied on the application of the`
  line `importer that the goods cannot be removed for deposit in a warehouse within a reasonable time,`
  line
  line `the goods may pending clearance or removal, as the case may be, be permitted to be stored in a public`
  line `warehouse for a period not exceeding thirty days:`
  line
  line `Provided that the provisions of Chapter IX shall not apply to goods permitted to be stored in a public`
  line `warehouse under this section:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs may`
  line `extend the period of storage for a further period not exceeding thirty days at a time.]`
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (24909)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 89
  title `Entry of goods for exportation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24909&sectionno=50&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `(1) The exporter of any goods shall make entry thereof by`
  line `presenting ^1[electronically] ^2[on the customs automated system] to the proper officer in the case of goods`
  line `to be exported in a vessel or aircraft, a shipping bill, and in the case of goods to be exported by land, a bill`
  line `of export ^3[in such form and manner as may be prescribed].`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that the ^4[Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs] may, in cases`
  line `cases where it is not feasible to make entry by presenting electronically ^2[on the customs automated`
  line `system] , allow an entry to be presented in any other manner.]`
  line
  line `(2) The exporter of any goods, while presenting a shipping bill or bill of export, shall ^5*** make and`
  line `subscribe to a declaration as to the truth of its contents.`
  line
  line `^2[(3) The exporter who presents a shipping bill or bill of export under this section shall ensure the`
  line `following, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the accuracy and completeness of the information given therein;`
  line
  line `(b) the authenticity and validity of any document supporting it; and`
  line
  line `(c) compliance with the restriction or prohibition, if any, relating to the goods under this Act or`
  line `under any other law for the time being in force.]`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 8 of 2011, s. 45 (w.e.f 8-4-2011).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 78 (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 78, ibid., for "in the prescribed form" (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 78, for "Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  line
  line `5. The words "at the foot thereof" omitted by Act 8 of 2011, s. 45 (w.e.f. 8-4-2011).`
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (24910)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 90
  title `Clearance of goods for exportation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24910&sectionno=51&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] Where the proper officer is satisfied that any goods`
  line `goods entered for export are not prohibited goods and the exporter has paid the duty, if any, assessed`
  line `thereon and any charges payable under this Act in respect of the same, the proper officer may make an`
  line `order permitting clearance and loading of the goods for exportation:`
  line
  line `^2[^3[Provided that such order may also be made electronically through the customs automated system`
  line `system on the basis of risk evaluation through appropriate selection criteria:`
  line
  line `Provided further that] the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, permit`
  line `certain class of exporters to make deferred payment of said duty or any charges in such manner as may be`
  line `provided by rules.]`
  line
  line `^2[(2) Where the exporter fails to pay the export duty, either in full or in part, under the proviso to`
  line `sub-section (1) by such due date as may be specified by rules, he shall pay interest on said duty not paid or short-paid till the date of its payment at such rate, not below five per cent and not exceeding thirty-six`
  line `per cent per annum, as may be fixed by the Central Government, by notification in the Official Gazette.]`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 51 renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 28 of 2016, s. 122, (w.e.f. 14-5-2016).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 122, ibid, (w.e.f. 14-5-2016).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 79, for "Provided that" (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_51_a:
  sectionId (24911)
  sectionNo 51A
  orderNo 91
  title `Payment of duty, interest, penalty, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 80 (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24911&sectionno=51A&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_51_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[51A. Payment of duty, interest, penalty, etc.--(1) Every deposit made towards duty, interest,`
  line `penalty, fee or any other sum payable by a person under the provisions of this Act or under the Customs`
  line `Tariff Act, 1975 (51 of 1975) or under any other law for the time being in force or the rules and`
  line `regulations made thereunder, using authorised mode of payment shall, subject to such conditions and`
  line `restrictions, be credited to the electronic cash ledger of such person, to be maintained in such manner, as`
  line `may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The amount available in the electronic cash ledger may be used for making any payment towards`
  line `duty, interest, penalty, fees or any other sum payable under the provisions of this Act or under the Customs`
  line `Tariff Act, 1975 (51 of 1975) or under any other law for the time being in force or the rules and regulations`
  line `made thereunder in such manner and subject to such conditions and within such time as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The balance in the electronic cash ledger, after payment of duty, interest, penalty, fee or any other`
  line `amount payable, may be refunded in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, if the Board is satisfied that it is necessary or`
  line `expedient so to do, it may, by notification, exempt the deposits made by such class of persons or with`
  line `respect to such categories of goods, as may be specified in the notification, from all or any of the provisions`
  line `of this section.]`
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (24912)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 92
  title `Chapter not to apply to baggage, postal articles and stores.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24912&sectionno=52&orderno=92&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Chapter`
  line `shall not apply to (a) baggage, (b) goods imported by post, and (c) stores.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (24913)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 93
  title `Transit of certain goods without payment of duty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24913&sectionno=53&orderno=93&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `^1[ ^2[53. Transit of certain goods without payment of duty.--Subject to the provisions of section`
  line `11, where any goods imported in a conveyance and mentioned in the ^3[arrival manifest or import`
  line `manifest] or the import report, as the case may be, as for transit in the same conveyance to any place`
  line `outside India or to any customs station, the proper officer may allow the goods and the conveyance to`
  line `transit without payment of duty, subject to such conditions, as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 101, for section 53 to 55 (w.e.f. 1-8-1998).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 123, for section 53 (w.e.f. 14-5-2016).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 56, for "import manifest" (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (24914)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 94
  title `Transhipment of certain goods without payment of duty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24914&sectionno=54&orderno=94&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any goods imported`
  line `into a customs station are intended for transhipment, a bill of transhipment shall be presented to the`
  line `proper officer in ^1[such form and manner as may be prescribed]:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that where the goods are being transhipped under an international treaty or bilateral`
  line `agreement between the Government of India and Government of a foreign country, a declaration`
  line `for transhipment instead of a bill of transhipment shall be presented to the proper officer in ^1[such form`
  line `and manner as may be prescribed].]`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of section 11, where any goods imported into a customs station are`
  line `mentioned in the ^3[arrival manifest or import manifest] or the import report, as the case may be, as`
  line `for transhipment to any place outside India, such goods may be allowed to be so transhipped without`
  line `payment of duty.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any goods imported into a customs station are mentioned in the ^3[arrival manifest or`
  line `import manifest] or the import report, as the case may be, as for transhipment--`
  line
  line `(a) to any major port as defined in the Indian Ports Act, 1908 (15 of 1908), or the customs airport`
  line `at Mumbai, Calcutta, Delhi or Chennai or any other customs port or customs airport which the Board`
  line `may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this behalf, or`
  line
  line `(b) to any other customs station and the proper officer is satisfied that the goods are bona`
  line `fide intended for transhipment to such customs station,`
  line
  line `the proper officer may allow the goods to be transhipped, without payment of duty, subject to such`
  line `conditions as may be prescribed for the due arrival of such goods at the customs station to`
  line `which transhipment is allowed.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 81, ibid., for "the prescribed form" (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 106 (w.e.f. 11-5-1999).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 56, for "import manifest" (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (24915)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 95
  title `Liability of duty on goods transited under section 53 or transhipped under section 54.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24915&sectionno=55&orderno=95&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `Where any goods are allowed to be transited under section 53 or transhipped under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 54 to any customs station, they shall, on their arrival at such station, be liable to duty and shall be`
  line `entered in like manner as goods are entered on the first importation thereof and the provisions of this Act`
  line `and any rules and regulations shall, so far as may be, apply in relation to such goods.]`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (24916)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 96
  title `Transport of certain classes of goods subject to prescribed conditions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24916&sectionno=56&orderno=96&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `Imported goods may`
  line `be transported without payment of duty from one land customs station to another, and any goods may be`
  line `transported from one part of India to another part through any foreign territory, subject to such conditions`
  line `as may be prescribed for the due arrival of such goods at the place of destination.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (24917)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 97
  title `Licensing of public warehouses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 124, for section 57 (w.e.f. 14-5-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24917&sectionno=57&orderno=97&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `^1[57. Licensing of public warehouses.--The Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner`
  line `of Customs may, subject to such conditions as may be prescribed, licence a public warehouse wherein`
  line `dutiable goods may be deposited.]`
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (24918)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 98
  title `Licensing of private warehouses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 125, ibid., for section 58 (w.e.f. 14-5-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24918&sectionno=58&orderno=98&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `^1[58. Licensing of private warehouses.--The Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner`
  line `of Customs may, subject to such conditions as may be prescribed, licence a private warehouse wherein`
  line `dutiable goods imported by or on behalf of the licensee may be deposited.]`
obj_root_law_sections_58_a:
  sectionId (24919)
  sectionNo 58A
  orderNo 99
  title `Licensing of special warehouses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_a_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 125, ibid., for section 58 (w.e.f. 14-5-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24919&sectionno=58A&orderno=99&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_58_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[58A. Licensing of Special warehouses.--(1) The Principal Commissioner of Customs or`
  line `Commissioner of Customs may, subject to such conditions as may be prescribed, licence a special`
  line `warehouse wherein dutiable goods may be deposited and such warehouse shall be caused to be locked by`
  line `the proper officer and no person shall enter the warehouse or remove any goods therefrom without the`
  line `permission of the proper officer.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify the class of goods which shall be`
  line `deposited in the special warehouse licensed under sub-section (1).]`
obj_root_law_sections_58_b:
  sectionId (24920)
  sectionNo 58B
  orderNo 100
  title `Cancellation of licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_b_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 125, ibid., for section 58 (w.e.f. 14-5-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24920&sectionno=58B&orderno=100&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_58_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[58B. Cancellation of licence.--(1) Where a licensee contravenes any of the provisions of this Act or`
  line `the rules or regulations made thereunder or breaches any of the conditions of the licence, the Principal`
  line `Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs may cancel the licence granted under section 57`
  line `or section 58 or section 58A:`
  line
  line `Provided that before any licence is cancelled, the licensee shall be given a reasonable opportunity of`
  line `being heard.`
  line
  line `(2) The Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs may, without prejudice to`
  line `any other action that may be taken against the licensee and the goods under this Act or any other law for the`
  line `time being in force, suspend operation of the warehouse during the pendency of an enquiry under`
  line `sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) Where the operation of a warehouse is suspended under sub-section (2), no goods shall be`
  line `deposited in such warehouse during the period of suspension:`
  line
  line `Provided that the provisions of this Chapter shall continue to apply to the goods already deposited in`
  line `the warehouse.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the licence issued under section 57 or section 58 or section 58A is cancelled, the goods`
  line `warehoused shall, within seven days from the date on which order of such cancellation is served on the`
  line `licensee or within such extended period as the proper officer may allow, be removed from such`
  line `warehouse to another warehouse or be cleared for home consumption or export:`
  line
  line `Provided that the provisions of this Chapter shall continue to apply to the goods already deposited in`
  line `the warehouse till they are removed to another warehouse or cleared for home consumption or for export,`
  line `during such period.]`
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (24921)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 101
  title `Warehousing bond.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 126, for section 59 (w.e.f. 14-5-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24921&sectionno=59&orderno=101&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `^1[59. Warehousing bond.--The importer of any goods in respect of which a bill of entry for`
  line `warehousing has been presented under section 46 and assessed to duty under section 17 or section 18`
  line `shall execute a bond in a sum equal to thrice the amount of the duty assessed on such goods, binding`
  line himself--
  line
  line `(a) to comply with all the provisions of the Act and the rules and regulations made thereunder in`
  line `respect of such goods;`
  line
  line `(b) to pay, on or before the date specified in the notice of demand, all duties and interest payable`
  line `under sub-section (2) of section 61; and`
  line
  line `(c) to pay all penalties and fines incurred for the contravention of the provisions of this Act or the`
  line `rules or regulations, in respect of such goods.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of sub-section (1), the Assistant Commissioner of Customs or Deputy`
  line `Commissioner of Customs may permit an importer to execute a general bond in such amount as the`
  line `Assistant Commissioner of Customs or Deputy Commissioner of Customs may approve in respect of the`
  line `warehousing of goods to be imported by him within a specified period.`
  line
  line `(3) The importer shall, in addition to the execution of a bond under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2),`
  line `furnish such security as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) Any bond executed under this section by an importer in respect of any goods shall continue to be`
  line `in force notwithstanding the transfer of the goods to another warehouse.`
  line
  line `(5) Where the whole of the goods or any part thereof are transferred to another person, the transferee`
  line `shall execute a bond in the manner specified in sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) and furnish security as`
  line `specified under sub-section (3).]`
obj_root_law_sections_59_a:
  sectionId (24922)
  sectionNo 59A
  orderNo 102
  title [Omitted.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24922&sectionno=59A&orderno=102&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_59_a_content:
  string
  line `[Conditions for warehousing of certain goods.] Omitted by The Finance Act, 1994 (32 of 1994),`
  line `s. 60 (w.e.f. 13-5-1994).`
obj_root_law_sections_59_a_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (24923)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 103
  title `Permission for removal of goods for deposit in warehouse.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24923&sectionno=60&orderno=103&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `^1[60. Permission for removal of goods for deposit in warehouse.--(1) When the provisions of`
  line `section 59 have been complied with in respect of any goods, the proper officer may make an order`
  line `permitting removal of the goods from a customs station for the purpose of deposit in a warehouse.`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that such order may also be made electronically through the customs automated system on`
  line `the basis of risk evaluation through appropriate selection criteria.]`
  line
  line `(2) Where an order is made under sub-section (1), the goods shall be deposited in a warehouse in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 127, for section 60 (w.e.f. 14-5-2016).`
  line
  line `2. The proviso ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 82 (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (24924)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 104
  title `Period for which goods may remain warehoused.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 128, for section 61 (w.e.f. 14-5-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24924&sectionno=61&orderno=104&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `^1[61. Period for which goods may remain warehoused.--(1) Any warehoused goods may remain`
  line `in the warehouse in which they are deposited or in any warehouse to which they may be removed,--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of capital goods intended for use in any hundred per cent. export oriented`
  line `undertaking, till the in the case of capital goods intended for use in any hundred per cent. export`
  line `oriented undertaking or electronic hardware technology park unit or software technology park unit or`
  line `any warehouse wherein manufacture or other operations have been permitted under section 65, till`
  line `their clearance from the warehouse;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of goods other than capital goods intended for use in any hundred per cent. export`
  line `oriented undertaking or electronic hardware technology park unit or software technology park unit or any`
  line `warehouse wherein manufacture or other operations have been permitted under section 65, till their`
  line `consumption or clearance from the warehouse; and`
  line
  line `(c) in the case of any other goods, till the expiry of one year from the date on which the proper`
  line `officer has made an order under sub-section (1) of section 60:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of any goods referred to in this clause, the Principal Commissioner of`
  line `Customs or Commissioner of Customs may, on sufficient cause being shown, extend the period for which`
  line `the goods may remain in the warehouse, by not more than one year at a time:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where such goods are likely to deteriorate, the period referred to in the first`
  line `proviso may be reduced by the Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs to such`
  line `shorter period as he may deem fit.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any warehoused goods specified in clause (c) of sub-section (1) remain in a warehouse`
  line `beyond a period of ninety days from the date on which the proper officer has made an order under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 60, interest shall be payable at such rate as may be fixed by the Central`
  line `Government under section 47, on the amount of duty payable at the time of clearance of the goods, for the`
  line `period from the expiry of the said ninety days till the date of payment of duty on the warehoused goods:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the Board considers it necessary so to do, in the public interest, it may,--`
  line
  line `(a) by order, and under the circumstances of an exceptional nature, to be specified in such order,`
  line `waive the whole or any part of the interest payable under this section in respect of any warehoused`
  line goods;
  line
  line `(b) by notification in the Official Gazette, specify the class of goods in respect of which no`
  line `interest shall be charged under this section;`
  line
  line `(c) by notification in the Official Gazette, specify the class of goods in respect of which the`
  line `interest shall be chargeable from the date on which the proper officer has made an order under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 60.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(i) "electronic hardware technology park unit" means a unit established under the Electronic`
  line `Hardware Technology Park Scheme notified by the Government of India;`
  line
  line `(ii) "hundred per cent. export oriented undertaking" has the same meaning as in clause (ii) of`
  line `Explanation 2 to sub-section (1) of section 3 of the Central Excise Act, 1944 (1 of 1944); and`
  line
  line `(iii) "software technology park unit" means a unit established under the Software Technology`
  line `Park Scheme notified by the Government of India.]`
obj_root_law_sections_62:
