obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (24927)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 107
  title `Owner’s right to deal with warehoused goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 130, for section 64 (w.e.f. 14-5-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24927&sectionno=64&orderno=107&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `^1[64. Owner's right to deal with warehoused goods.--The owner of any warehoused goods may,`
  line `after warehousing the same,--`
  line
  line `(a) inspect the goods;`
  line
  line `(b) deal with their containers in such manner as may be necessary to prevent loss or deterioration`
  line `or damage to the goods;`
  line
  line `(c) sort the goods; or`
  line
  line `(d) show the goods for sale.]`
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (24928)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 108
  title `Manufacture and other operations in relation to goods in a warehouse.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 131, ibid., for certain words (w.e.f. 14-5-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24928&sectionno=65&orderno=108&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `(1) ^1[With the`
  line `permission of the Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs and subject to such`
  line `conditions] as may be prescribed, the owner of any warehoused goods may carry on any manufacturing`
  line `process or other operations in the warehouse in relation to such goods.`
  line
  line `(2) Where in the course of any operations permissible in relation to any warehoused goods under`
  line `sub-section (1), there is any waste or refuse, the following provisions shall apply:--`
  line
  line `(a) if the whole or any part of the goods resulting from such operations are exported, import duty`
  line `shall be remitted on the quantity of the warehoused goods contained in so much of the waste or refuse`
  line `as has arisen from the operations carried on in relation to the goods exported:`
  line
  line `Provided that such waste or refuse is either destroyed or duty is paid on such waste or refuse as if`
  line `it had been imported into India in that form;`
  line
  line `(b) if the whole or any part of the goods resulting from such operations are cleared from the`
  line `warehouse for home consumption, import duty shall be charged on the quantity of the warehoused`
  line `goods contained in so much of the waste or refuse as has arisen from the operations carried on in`
  line `relation to the goods cleared for home consumption.`
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (24929)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 109
  title `Power to exempt imported materials used in the manufacture of goods in warehouse.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24929&sectionno=66&orderno=109&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line If
  line `any imported materials are used in accordance with the provisions of section 65 for the manufacture of`
  line `any goods and the rate of duty leviable on the imported materials exceeds the rate of duty leviable on such`
  line `goods, the Central Government, if satisfied that in the interests of the establishment or development of any domestic industry it is necessary so to do, may, by notification in the Official Gazette, exempt the`
  line `imported materials from the whole or part of the excess rate of duty.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (24930)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 110
  title `Removal of goods from one warehouse to another.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes `1. The words "without payment of duty" omitted by Act 55 of 1991, s. 5 (we.f. 23-12-1991).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24930&sectionno=67&orderno=110&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `The owner of any warehoused goods`
  line `may, with the permission of the proper officer, remove them from one warehouse to another, ^1*** subject`
  line `to such conditions as may be prescribed for the due arrival of the warehoused goods at the warehouse to`
  line `which removal is permitted.`
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (24931)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 111
  title `Clearance of warehoused goods for home consumption.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24931&sectionno=68&orderno=111&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `^1[Any warehoused goods may be`
  line `cleared from the warehouse] for home consumption, if--`
  line
  line `(a) a bill of entry for home consumption in respect of such goods has been presented in the`
  line `prescribed form;`
  line
  line `^2[(b) the import duty, interest, fine and penalties payable in respect of such goods have been paid;`
  line and]
  line
  line `(c) an order for clearance of such goods for home consumption has been made by the proper`
  line officer.
  line
  line ^3[
  line `^4[Provided that the order referred to in clause (c) may also be made electronically through the`
  line `customs automated system on the basis of risk evaluation through appropriate selection criteria:`
  line
  line `Provided further that] the owner of any warehoused goods may, at any time before an order for`
  line `clearance of goods for home consumption has been made in respect of such goods, relinquish his title to`
  line `the goods upon payment of ^5*** penalties that may be payable in respect of the goods and upon such`
  line `relinquishment, he shall not be liable to pay duty thereon:]`
  line
  line `^6[^7[Provided also that] the owner of any such warehoused goods shall not be allowed to relinquish his`
  line `title to such goods regarding which an offence appears to have been committed under this Act or any`
  line `other law for the time being in force.]`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 132, for "The importer of any warehoused goods may clear them" (w.e.f. 14-5-2016).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 132, ibid., for clause (b) (w.e.f. 14-5-2016).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 114 (w.e.f. 14-5-2003).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 83, for "Provided that" (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  line
  line `5. The words "rent, interest, other charges and" omitted by Act 28 of 2016, s. 132 (w.e.f. 14-5-2016).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 21 of 2006, s. 59 (w.e.f. 18-4-2006).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 83, for "Provided further that" (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (24932)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 112
  title `Clearance of warehoused goods for export.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24932&sectionno=69&orderno=112&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `69. Clearance of warehoused goods for ^1[export].--(1) Any warehoused goods may be exported`
  line `to a place outside India without payment of import duty if--`
  line
  line `^2[(a) a shipping bill or a bill of export or the form as prescribed under section 84 has been`
  line `presented in respect of such goods;]`
  line
  line `^3[(b) the export duty, fine and penalties payable in respect of such goods have been paid; and]`
  line
  line `(c) an order for clearance of such goods for ^1[export] has been made by the proper officer.`
  line
  line `^4[Provided that the order referred to in clause (c) may also be made electronically through the`
  line `customs automated system on the basis or risk evaluation through appropriate selection criteria.]`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), if the Central Government is of opinion`
  line `that warehoused goods of any specified description are likely to be smuggled back into India, it may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, direct that such goods shall not be exported to any place outside India`
  line `without payment of duty or may be allowed to be so exported subject to such restrictions and conditions`
  line `as may be specified in the notification`
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 133, for "exportation" (w.e.f. 14-5-2016).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 103, for clause (a) (w.e.f. 31-3-2017).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 133, for clause (b) (w.e.f. 14-5-2016).`
  line
  line `4. The proviso ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 84 (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (24933)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 113
  title `Allowance in case of volatile goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 100, for "Assistant Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 11-5-1999)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24933&sectionno=70&orderno=113&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `(1) When any warehoused goods to which this section`
  line `applies are at the time of delivery from a warehouse found to be deficient in quantity on account of`
  line `natural loss, the ^1[Assistant Commissioner of Customs or Deputy Commissioner of Customs] may remit`
  line `the duty on such deficiency.`
  line
  line `(2) This section applies to such warehoused goods as the Central Government, having regard to the`
  line `volatility of the goods and the manner of their storage, may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line specify.
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (24934)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 114
  title `Goods not to be taken out of warehouse except as provided by this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 134, for "re-exportation" (w.e.f. 14-5-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24934&sectionno=71&orderno=114&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `No warehoused`
  line `goods shall be taken out of a warehouse except on`
  line `clearance for home consumption or ^1[export], or for`
  line `removal to another warehouse, or as otherwise provided by this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (24935)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 115
  title `Goods improperly removed from warehouse, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24935&sectionno=72&orderno=115&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `(1) In any of the following cases, that is to`
  line say,--
  line
  line `(a) where any warehoused goods are removed from a warehouse in contravention of section 71;`
  line
  line `(b) where any warehoused goods have not been removed from a warehouse at the expiration of`
  line `the period during which such goods are permitted under section 61 to remain in a warehouse;`
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
  line
  line `(d) where any goods in respect of which a bond has been executed under ^2[section 59 ^3*** ] and`
  line `which have not been cleared for home consumption or ^4[export or] are not duly accounted for to the`
  line `satisfaction of the proper officer,`
  line
  line `the proper officer may demand, and the owner of such goods shall forthwith pay, the full amount of duty`
  line `chargeable on account of such goods together with ^5[interest, fine and penalties] payable in respect of`
  line `such goods`
  line
  line `(2) If any owner fails to pay any amount demanded under sub-section (1), the proper officer may,`
  line `without prejudice to any other remedy, cause to be detained and sold, after notice to the owner (any`
  line `transfer of the goods notwithstanding) such sufficient portion of his goods, if any, in the warehouse, as`
  line `the said officer may ^6[deem fit].`
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Clause (c) omitted by s. 135, ibid. (w.e.f. 14-5-2016).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 55 of 1991, s. 9, for "section 59" (w.e.f. 23-12-1991).`
  line
  line `3. The words, figures and letter "or section 59A" omitted by Act 32 of 1994, s. 60 (w.e.f. 13-5-1994).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 135, for "exportation" (w.e.f. 14-5-2016).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 135, ibid., for "all penalties, rent, interest and other charges" (w.e.f. 14-5-2016).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 135, ibid., for "select" (w.e.f. 14-5-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (24936)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 116
  title `Cancellation and return of warehousing bond.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24936&sectionno=73&orderno=116&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `When the whole of the goods covered by any`
  line `bond executed under ^1[section 59 ^2***] have been cleared for home consumption or exported or`
  line `^3[transferred or] are otherwise duly accounted for, and when all amounts due on account of such goods`
  line `have been paid, the proper officer shall cancel the bond as discharged in full, and shall on demand deliver`
  line `it, so cancelled, to the person who has executed or is entitled to receive it.`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 55 of 1991, s. 9, for "section 59" (w.e.f. 23-12-1991).`
  line
  line `2. The words, figures and letter "or section 59A" omitted by Act 32 of 1994, s. 60 (w.e.f. 13-5-1994).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 136, ibid. (w.e.f. 14-5-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_73_a:
  sectionId (24937)
  sectionNo 73A
  orderNo 117
  title `Custody and removal of warehoused goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 137, ibid. (w.e.f. 14-5-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24937&sectionno=73A&orderno=117&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_73_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[73A. Custody and removal of warehoused goods.--(1) All warehoused goods shall remain in the`
  line `custody of the person who has been granted a licence under section 57 or section 58 or section 58A until they`
  line `are cleared for home consumption or are transferred to another warehouse or are exported or removed as`
  line `otherwise provided under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The responsibilities of the person referred to in sub-section (1) who has custody of the`
  line `warehoused goods shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any warehoused goods are removed in contravention of section 71, the licensee shall be`
  line `liable to pay duty, interest, fine and penalties without prejudice to any other action that may be taken`
  line `against him under this Act or any other law for the time being in force.]`
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (24938)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 118
  title `Drawback allowable on re-export of duty-paid goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24938&sectionno=74&orderno=118&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `(1) When any goods capable of being`
  line `easily identified which have been imported into India and upon which ^1[any duty has been paid on`
  line importation,--
  line
  line `(i) are entered for export and the proper officer makes an order permitting clearance and loading`
  line `of the goods for exportation under section 51; or`
  line
  line `(ii) are to be exported as baggage and the owner of such baggage, for the purpose of clearing it,`
  line `makes a declaration of its contents to the proper officer under section 77 (which declaration shall be`
  line `deemed to be an entry for export for the purposes of this section) and such officer makes an order`
  line `permitting clearance of the goods for exportation; or`
  line
  line `(iii) are entered for export by post under ^2[clause (a) of section 84] and the proper officer makes`
  line `an order permitting clearance of the goods for exportation,`
  line
  line `ninety-eight per cent. of such duty shall, except as otherwise hereinafter provided, be re-paid as`
  line `drawback, if--]`
  line
  line `(a) the goods are identified to the satisfaction of the ^3[Assistant Commissioner of Customs or`
  line `Deputy Commissioner of Customs] as the goods which were imported; and`
  line
  line `(b) the goods are entered for export within two years from the date of payment of duty on the`
  line `importation thereof:`
  line
  line `Provided that in any particular case the aforesaid period of two years may, on sufficient cause`
  line `being shown, be extended by the Board by such further period as it may deem fit.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the rate of drawback in the case of goods`
  line `which have been used after the importation thereof shall be such as the Central Government, having`
  line `regard to the duration of use, depreciation in value and other relevant circumstances, may, by notification`
  line `in the Official Gazette, fix.`
  line
  line `^4[(3) The Central Government may make rules for the purpose of carrying out the provisions of this`
  line `section and, in particular, such rules may--`
  line
  line `(a) provide for the manner in which the identity of goods imported in different consignments`
  line `which are ordinarily stored together in bulk, may be established;`
  line
  line `(b) specify the goods which shall be deemed to be not capable of being easily identified; and`
  line
  line `(c) provide for the manner and the time within which a claim for payment of drawback is to be`
  line filed.]
  line
  line `(4) For the purposes of this section--`
  line
  line `(a) goods shall be deemed to have been entered for export on the date with reference to which the`
  line `rate of duty is calculated under section 16;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of goods assessed to duty provisionally under section 18, the date of payment of`
  line `the provisional duty shall be deemed to be the date of payment of duty.`
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 80 of 1985, s. 6, for certain words (w.e.f. 27-12-1985).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 85, for "section 82" (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 100, for "Assistant Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 11-5-1999).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 60, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 26-5-1995).`
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (24939)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 119
  title `Drawback on imported materials used in the manufacture of goods which are exported.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=24939&sectionno=75&orderno=119&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where it appears to the Central Government that in respect of goods of any class or`
  line `description ^1[manufactured, processed or on which any operation has been carried out in India] ^2[, being`
  line `goods which have been entered for export and in respect of which an order permitting the clearance and loading thereof for exportation has been made under section 51 by the proper officer], ^3[or being goods`
  line `entered for export by post under ^4[clause (a) of section 84] and in respect of which an order permitting`
  line `clearance for exportation has been made by the proper officer], a drawback should be allowed of duties of`
  line `customs chargeable under this Act on any imported materials of a class or description used in the`
  line `^5[manufacture or processing of such goods or carrying out any operation on such goods], the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, direct that drawback shall be allowed in respect`
  line `of such goods in accordance with, and subject to, the rules made under sub-section (2):`
  line
  line `^6[Provided that no drawback shall be allowed under this sub-section in respect of any of the aforesaid`
  line `goods which the Central Government may, by rules made under sub-section (2), specify, if the export`
  line `value of such goods or class of goods is less than the value of the imported materials used in`
  line `the ^5[manufacture or processing of such goods or carrying out any operation on such goods] or class of`
  line `goods, or is not more than such percentage of the value of the imported materials used in`
  line `the ^5[manufacture or processing of such goods or carrying out any operation on such goods] or class of`
  line `goods as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this behalf:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where any drawback has been allowed on any goods under this sub-section and`
  line `the sale proceeds in respect of such goods are not received by or on behalf of the exporter in India within`
  line `the time allowed under the ^7[Foreign Exchange Management Act, 1999 (42 of 1999)], such drawback`
  line `shall ^8[except under such circumstances or such conditions as the Central Government may, by rule,`
  line `specify,] be deemed never to have been allowed and the Central Government may, by rules made under`
  line `sub-section (2), specify the procedure for the recovery or adjustment of the amount of such drawback.`
  line
  line `^9[(1A) Where it appears to the Central Government that the quantity of a particular material imported`
  line `into India is more than the total quantity of like material that has been used in the goods ^10[manufactured,`
  line `processed or on which any operation has been carried out in India] and exported outside India, then, the`
  line `Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, declare that so much of the material as is`
  line `contained in the goods exported shall, for the purpose of sub-section (1), be deemed to be imported`
  line material.]
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may make rules for the purpose of carrying out the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (1) and, in particular, such rules may provide--`
  line
  line `^11[(a) for the payment of drawback equal to the amount of duty actually paid on the imported`
  line `materials used in the manufacture or processing of the goods or carrying out any operation on the`
  line `goods or as is specified in the rules as the average amount of duty paid on the materials of that class`
  line `or description used in the manufacture or processing of export goods or carrying out any operation on`
  line `export goods of that class or description either by manufacturers generally or by persons processing`
  line `or carrying on any operation generally or by any particular manufacturer or particular person carrying`
  line `on any process or other operation, and interest if any payable thereon;]`
  line
  line `^6[(aa) for specifying the goods in respect of which no drawback shall be allowed;`
  line
  line `(ab) for specifying the procedure for recovery or adjustment of the amount of any drawback`
  line `which had been allowed under sub-section (1)`
  line `^12[or interest chargeable thereon];]`
  line
  line `(b) for the production of such certificates, documents and other evidence in support of each claim`
  line `of drawback as may be necessary;`
  line
  line `(c) for requiring the ^13[manufacturer or the person carrying out any process or other operation] to`
  line `give access to every part of his manufactory to any officer of customs specially authorised in this`
  line `behalf by the ^14[Assistant Commissioner of Customs or Deputy Commissioner of Customs] to enable`
  line `such authorised officer to inspect the processes of ^15[manufacture, process or any other operation`
  line `carried out] and to verify by actual check or otherwise the statements made in support of the claim for`
  line drawback.
  line
  line `^16[(d) for the manner and the time within which the claim for payment of drawback may be filed;]`
  line
  line `^16[(3) The power to make rules conferred by sub-section (2) shall include the power to give drawback`
  line `with retrospective effect from a date not earlier than the date of changes in the rates of duty on inputs`
  line `used in the export goods.]`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 61, ibid., for "manufactured in India" (w.e.f. 26-5-1995).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 11 of 1983, s. 52, for "and exported to any place outside India," (w.e.f. 13-5-1983).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 80 of 1985, s. 7 (w.e.f. 13-5-1983).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 86, for "section 82" (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 61, for "manufacture of such goods" (w.e.f. 26-5-1995).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 120 (w.e.f. 27-9-1991).`
  line
  line `75. Subs. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 125, for "Foreign Exchange Regulation Act, 1973 (46 of 1973)" (w.e.f. 11-5-2002).`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by Act 8 of 2011, s. 46 (w.e.f. 8-4-2011).`
  line
  line `9. Ins. by Act 25 of 1978, s. 10 (w.e.f. 1-7-1978).`
  line
  line `10. Subs. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 61, for "manufactured in India" (w.e.f. 26-5-1995).`
  line
  line `11. Subs. by s. 61, ibid., for clause (a) (w.e.f. 26-5-1995).`
  line
  line `12. Ins. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 61 (w.e.f. 26-5-1995).`
  line
  line `13. Subs. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 61, for "manufacturer" (w.e.f. 26-5-1995).`
