obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (30971)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 136
  title `Declaration by owner of baggage.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=30971&sectionno=77&orderno=136&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `The owner of any baggage shall, for the purpose of clearing`
  line `it, make a declaration of its contents to the proper officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (30972)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 137
  title `Determination of rate of duty and tariff valuation in respect of beggage.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=30972&sectionno=78&orderno=137&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `The rate of duty`
  line `and tariff valuation, if any, applicable to baggage shall be the rate and valuation in force on the date on`
  line `which a declaration is made in respect of such baggage under section 77.`
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (30973)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 138
  title `Bona fide baggage exempted from duty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=30973&sectionno=79&orderno=138&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `(1) The proper officer may, subject to any rules made`
  line `under sub-section (2), pass free of duty--`
  line
  line `(a) any article in the baggage of a passenger or a member of the crew in respect of which the said`
  line `officer is satisfied that it has been in his use for such minimum period as may be specified in the`
  line rules;
  line
  line `(b) any article in the baggage of a passenger in respect of which the said officer is satisfied that it`
  line `is for the use of the passenger or his family or is a bona fide gift or souvenir; provided that the value`
  line `of each such article and the total value of all such articles does not exceed such limits as may be`
  line `specified in the rules.`
  line
  line `(2) the Central Government may make rules for the purpose of carrying out the provisions of this`
  line `section and, in particular, such rules may specify--`
  line
  line `(a) the minimum period for which any article has been used by a passenger or a member of the`
  line `crew for the purpose of clause (a) of sub-section (1);`
  line
  line `(b) the maximum value of any individual article and the maximum total value of all the articles`
  line `which may be passed free of duty under clause (b) of sub-section (1);`
  line
  line `(c) the conditions (to be fulfilled before or after clearance) subject to which any baggage may be`
  line `passed free of duty.`
  line
  line `(3) Different rules may be made under sub-section (2) for different classes of persons.`
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_79_2:
  sectionId (30974)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 139
  title `Bona fide baggage exempted from duty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content_2
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes_2
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=30974&sectionno=79&orderno=139&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
