  line
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (30978)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 143
  title `Rate of duty and tariff valuation in respect of goods imported or exported by post or courier.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=30978&sectionno=83&orderno=143&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line `83. Rate of duty and tariff valuation in respect of goods imported or exported by ^1[post or`
  line `courier].--(1) The rate of duty and tariff value, if any, applicable to any goods imported by ^1[post or`
  line `courier] shall be the rate and valuation in force on the date on which the ^2[postal authorities or the`
  line `authorised courier] present to the proper officer a list containing the particulars of such goods for the`
  line `purpose of assessing the duty thereon:`
  line
  line `Provided that if such goods are imported by a vessel and the list of the goods containing the`
  line `particulars was presented before the date of the arrival of the vessel, it shall be deemed to have been`
  line `presented on the date of such arrival.`
  line
  line `(2) The rate of duty and tariff value, if any, applicable to any goods exported by ^1[post or courier]`
  line `shall be the rate and valuation in force on the date on which the exporter delivers such goods to the`
  line `^2[postal authorities or the authorised courier] for exportation.`
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 88, for "post" (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 88, ibid., for "postal authorities" (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (30979)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 144
  title `Regulations regarding goods imported or to be exported by post or courier.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=30979&sectionno=84&orderno=144&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `Regulations regarding goods imported or to be exported by ^1[post or courier].--The Board`
  line `may make regulations providing for--`
  line
  line `^2[(a) the form and manner in which an entry may be made in respect of goods imported or to be`
  line `exported by ^1[post or courier];]`
  line
  line `(b) the examination, assessment to duty, and clearance of goods imported or to be exported by`
  line `^1[post or courier];`
  line
  line `(c) the transit or transhipment of goods imported by ^1[post or courier], from one customs station`
  line `to another or to a place outside India.`
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 89, ibid., for "post" (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 105, for clause (a) (w.e.f. 31-3-2017).`
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (30980)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 145
  title `Stores may be allowed to be warehoused without assessment to duty`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=30980&sectionno=85&orderno=145&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `Where any imported`
  line `goods are entered for warehousing and the importer makes and subscribes to a declaration that the goods`
  line `are to be supplied as stores to vessels or aircrafts without payment of import duty under this Chapter, the`
  line `proper officer may permit the goods to be warehoused without the goods being assessed to duty.`
obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (30981)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 146
  title `Transit and transhipment of stores.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_86_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=30981&sectionno=86&orderno=146&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any stores imported in a vessel or aircraft may,`
  line `without payment of duty, remain on board such vessel or aircraft while it is in India.`
  line
  line `(2) Any stores imported in a vessel or aircraft may, with the permission of the proper officer, be`
  line `transferred to any vessel or aircraft as stores for consumption therein as provided in section 87 or`
  line `section 90.`
obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  sectionId (30982)
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 147
  title `Imported stores may be consumed on board a foreign-going vessel or aircraft.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=30982&sectionno=87&orderno=147&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line Any
  line `imported stores on board a vessel or aircraft (other than stores to which section 90 applies) may, without`
  line `payment of duty, be consumed thereon as stores during the period such vessel or aircraft is a foreigngoing vessel or aircraft.`
obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_88:
  sectionId (30983)
  sectionNo (88)
  orderNo 148
  title `Application of section 69 and Chapter X to stores.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_88_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=30983&sectionno=88&orderno=148&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_88_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of section 69 and Chapter`
  line `X shall apply to stores (other than those to which section 90 applies) as they apply to other goods, subject`
  line `to the modifications that--`
  line
  line `(a) for the words "exported to any place outside India" or the word "exported", wherever they`
  line `occur, the words "taken on board any foreign-going vessel or aircraft as stores" shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of drawback on fuel and lubricating oil taken on board any foreign-going aircraft`
  line `as stores, sub-section (1) of section 74 shall have effect as if for the words "ninety-eight per cent", the`
  line `words "the whole" were substituted.`
obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_89:
  sectionId (30984)
  sectionNo (89)
  orderNo 149
  title `Stores to be free of export duty`
  content obj_root_law_sections_89_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=30984&sectionno=89&orderno=149&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_89_content:
  string
  line `Goods produced or manufactured in India and required as`
  line `stores on any foreign-going vessel or aircraft may be exported free of duty in such quantities as the proper`
  line `officer may determine, having regard to the size of the vessel or aircraft, the number of passengers and`
  line `crew and the length of the voyage or journey on which the vessel or aircraft is about to depart.`
obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_90:
  sectionId (30985)
  sectionNo (90)
  orderNo 150
  title `Concessions in respect of imported stores for the Navy`
  content obj_root_law_sections_90_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=30985&sectionno=90&orderno=150&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_90_content:
  string
  line `(1) Imported stores specified in`
  line `sub-section (3) may without payment of duty be consumed on board a ship of the Indian Navy.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of section 69 and Chapter X shall apply to stores specified in sub-section (3) as`
  line `they apply to other goods, subject to the modifications that--`
  line
  line `(a) for the words "exported to any place outside India" or the word "exported" wherever they`
  line `occur, the words "taken on board a ship of the Indian Navy" shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(b) for the words "ninety-eight per cent". in sub-section (1) of section 74, the words "the whole"`
  line `shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `(3) The stores referred to in sub-sections (1) and (2) are the following:--`
  line
  line `(a) stores for the use of a ship of the Indian Navy;`
  line
  line `(b) stores supplied free by the Government for the use of the crew of a ship of the Indian Navy in`
  line `accordance with their conditions of service.`
obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_91:
  sectionId (30986)
  sectionNo (91)
  orderNo 151
  title `Chapter not to apply to baggage and stores.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_91_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=30986&sectionno=91&orderno=151&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_91_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Chapter shall not apply to`
  line `baggage and stores.`
obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_92:
  sectionId (30987)
  sectionNo (92)
  orderNo 152
  title `Entry of coastal goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_92_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=30987&sectionno=92&orderno=152&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_92_content:
  string
  line `(1) The consignor of any coastal goods shall make an entry thereof by`
  line `presenting to the proper officer a bill of coastal goods in the prescribed form.`
  line
  line `(2) Every such consignor while presenting a bill of coastal goods shall, at the foot thereof, make and`
  line `subscribe to a declaration as to the truth of the contents of such bill.`
obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_93:
  sectionId (30988)
  sectionNo (93)
  orderNo 153
  title `Coastal goods not to be loaded until bill relating thereto is passed, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_93_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=30988&sectionno=93&orderno=153&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_93_content:
  string
  line `The master of a`
  line `vessel shall not permit the loading of any coastal goods on the vessel until a bill relating to such goods`
  line `presented under section 92 has been passed by the proper officer and has been delivered to the master by`
  line `the consignor.`
obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_94:
  sectionId (30989)
  sectionNo (94)
  orderNo 154
  title `Clearance of coastal goods at destination.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_94_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=30989&sectionno=94&orderno=154&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_94_content:
  string
  line `(1) The master of a vessel carrying any coastal`
  line `goods shall carry on board the vessel all bills relating to such goods delivered to him under section 93 and`
  line `shall, immediately on arrival of the vessel at any customs or coastal port, deliver to the proper officer of`
  line `that port all bills relating to the goods which are to be unloaded at that port.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any coastal goods are unloaded at any port, the proper officer shall permit clearance`
  line `thereof if he is satisfied that they are entered in a bill of coastal goods delivered to him under`
  line `sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_95:
  sectionId (30990)
  sectionNo (95)
  orderNo 155
  title `Master of a coasting vessel to carry an advice book.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_95_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=30990&sectionno=95&orderno=155&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_95_content:
  string
  line `(1) The master of every vessel carrying`
  line `coastal goods shall be supplied by the Customs`
  line `authorities with a book to be called the "advice book".`
  line
  line `(2) The proper officer at each port of call by such vessel shall make such entries in the advice book`
  line `as he deems fit, relating to the goods loaded on the vessel at that port.`
  line
  line `(3) The master of every such vessel shall carry the advice book on board the vessel and shall on`
  line `arrival at each port of call deliver it to the proper officer at that port for his inspection.`
obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_96:
  sectionId (30991)
  sectionNo (96)
  orderNo 156
  title `Loading and unloading of coastal goods at customs port or coastal port only.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_96_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=30991&sectionno=96&orderno=156&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_96_content:
  string
  line `No coastal`
  line `goods shall be loaded on, or unloaded from, any vessel at any port other than a customs port or a coastal`
  line `port appointed under section 7 for the loading or unloading of such goods.`
obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_97:
  sectionId (30992)
  sectionNo (97)
  orderNo 157
  title `No coasting vessel to leave without written order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_97_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=30992&sectionno=97&orderno=157&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_97_content:
  string
  line `(1) The master of a vessel which has`
  line `brought or loaded any coastal goods at a customs or coastal port shall not cause or permit the vessel to`
  line `depart from such port until a written order to that effect has been given by the proper officer.`
  line
  line `(2) No such order shall be given until--`
  line
  line `(a) the master of the vessel has answered the questions put to him under section 38;`
  line
  line `(b) all charges and penalties due in respect of that vessel or from the master thereof have been`
  line `paid or the payment secured by such guarantee or deposit of such amount as the proper officer may`
  line direct;
  line
  line `(c) the master of the vessel has satisfied the proper officer that no penalty is leviable on him`
  line `under section 116 or the payment of any penalty that may be levied upon him under that section has`
  line `been secured by such guarantee or deposit of such amount as the proper officer may direct;`
  line
  line `(d) the provisions of this Chapter and any rules and regulations relating to coastal goods and`
  line `vessels carrying coastal goods have been complied with.`
obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_98:
  sectionId (30993)
  sectionNo (98)
  orderNo 158
  title `Application of certain provisions of this Act to coastal goods, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_98_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=30993&sectionno=98&orderno=158&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_98_content:
  string
  line `(1) Sections 33, 34 and 36`
  line `shall, so far as may be, apply to coastal goods as they apply to imported goods or export goods.`
  line
  line `(2) Sections 37 and 38 shall, so far as may be, apply to vessels carrying coastal goods as they apply to`
  line `vessels carrying imported goods or export goods.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, direct that all or any of the`
  line `other provisions of Chapter VI and the provisions of section 45 shall apply to coastal goods or vessels`
  line `carrying coastal goods subject to such exceptions and modifications as may be specified in the`
  line notification.
obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_98_a:
  sectionId (30994)
  sectionNo 98A
  orderNo 159
  title `Power to relax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_98_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 64 (w.e.f. 26-5-1995).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=30994&sectionno=98A&orderno=159&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_98_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[98A. Power to relax.--If the Central Government is satisfied that it is necessary in the public`
  line `interest so to do it may, by notification in the Official Gazette, exempt generally, either absolutely or`
  line `subject to such conditions as may be specified in the notification, coastal goods or vessels carrying coastal`
  line `goods from all or any of the provisions of this Chapter.]`
obj_root_law_sections_99:
  sectionId (30995)
  sectionNo (99)
  orderNo 160
  title `Power to make rules in respect of coastal goods and coasting vessels.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_99_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=30995&sectionno=99&orderno=160&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_99_content:
  string
  line `The Central`
  line `Government may make rules for--`
  line
  line `(a) preventing the taking out of India of any coastal goods the export of which is dutiable or`
  line `prohibited under this Act or any other law for the time being in force;`
  line
  line `(b) preventing, in the case of a vessel carrying coastal goods as well as imported or export goods,`
  line `the substitution of imported or export goods by coastal goods.`
obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_99_a:
  sectionId (30996)
  sectionNo 99A
  orderNo 161
  title Audit.
  content obj_root_law_sections_99_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 90 (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=30996&sectionno=99A&orderno=161&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_99_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[99A. Audit.--The proper officer may carry out the audit of assessment of imported goods or export`
  line `goods or of an auditee under this Act either in his office or in the premises of the auditee in such manner`
  line `as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, "auditee" means a person who is subject to an audit`
  line `under this section and includes an importer or exporter or custodian approved under section 45 or licensee`
  line `of a warehouse and any other person concerned directly or indirectly in clearing, forwarding, stocking,`
  line `carrying, selling or purchasing of imported goods or export goods or dutiable goods.]`
obj_root_law_sections_99_b:
  sectionId (50252)
  sectionNo 99B
  orderNo 162
  title `Verification of identity and compliance thereof`
  content obj_root_law_sections_99_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 71 (w.e.f. 1-8-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=50252&sectionno=99B&orderno=162&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_99_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[99B. Verification of identity and compliance thereof.--(1) The proper officer, authorised in this`
  line `behalf by the Principal Commissioner of Customs or the Commissioner of Customs, as the case may be,`
  line `may, for the purposes of ascertaining compliance of the provisions of this Act or any other law for the`
  line `time being in force, require a person, whose verification he considers necessary for protecting the interest`
  line `of revenue or for preventing smuggling, to do all or any of the following, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) undergo authentication, or furnish proof of possession of Aadhaar number, in such manner`
  line `and within such time as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(b) submit such other document or information, in such manner and within such time as may be`
  line `prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that where such person has not been assigned the Aadhaar number, or where so assigned,`
  line `but authentication of such person has failed due to technical reasons or for reasons beyond his control,`
  line `then, he shall be provided an opportunity to furnish such other alternative and viable means of`
  line `identification in such form and manner and within such time as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sub-section (1) shall not apply to such person or class of persons as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other provisions of this Act, where the Principal`
  line `Commissioner of Customs or the Commissioner of Customs comes to the conclusion, based on reasons to`
  line `be recorded in writing, that the person referred to in sub-section (1) has--`
  line
  line `(i) failed to comply with the requirements of the said sub-section or submitted incorrect`
  line `documents or information under the said sub-section, he may, by order, suspend--`
  line
  line `(a) clearance of imported goods or export goods;`
  line
  line `(b) sanction of refund;`
  line
  line `(c) sanction of drawback;`
  line
  line `(d) exemption from duty;`
  line
  line `(e) licence or registration granted under this Act; or`
  line
  line `(f) any benefit, monetary or otherwise, arising out of import or export,`
  line
  line `relating to such person, subject to such conditions as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(ii) failed authentication as required under the said sub-section, he may, by order, direct that such`
  line `person shall not have the benefit of any of the items specified in sub-clauses (a) to (f) of clause (i).`
  line
  line `(4) The order of suspension under sub-section (3) shall remain in force until the person concerned`
  line `complies with the requirements of sub-section (1) or furnishes correct document or information there`
  line under.
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, the expression "Aadhaar number" shall have the same`
  line `meaning as assigned to it in clause (a) of section 2 of the Aadhaar (Targeted Delivery of Financial and`
  line `Other Subsidies, Benefits and Services) Act, 2016 (18 of 2016).]`
obj_root_law_sections_100:
  sectionId (30997)
  sectionNo (100)
  orderNo 163
  title `Power to search suspected persons entering or leaving India, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_100_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=30997&sectionno=100&orderno=163&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_100_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the proper officer`
  line `has reason to believe that any person to whom this section applies has secreted about his person, any`
  line `goods liable to confiscation or any documents relating thereto, he may search that person.`
  line
  line `(2) This section applies to the following persons, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) any person who has landed from or is about to board, or is on board any vessel within the`
  line `Indian customs waters;`
  line
  line `(b) any person who has landed from or is about to board, or is on board a foreign-going aircraft;`
  line
  line `(c) any person who has got out of, or is about to get into, or is in, a vehicle, which has arrived`
  line `from, or is to proceed to any place outside India;`
  line
  line `(d) any person not included in clauses (a), (b) or (c) who has entered or is about to leave India;`
  line
  line `(e) any person in a customs area.`
obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_101:
  sectionId (30998)
  sectionNo (101)
  orderNo 164
  title `Power to search suspected persons in certain other cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_101_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 78, for "Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=30998&sectionno=101&orderno=164&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_101_content:
  string
  line `(1) Without prejudice to the`
  line `provisions of section 100, if an officer of customs empowered in this behalf by general or special order of`
  line `the ^1[Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs], has reason to believe that any`
  line `person has secreted about his person any goods of the description specified in sub-section (2) which are`
  line `liable to confiscation, or documents relating thereto, he may search that person.`
  line
  line `(2) The goods referred to in sub-section (1) are the following:--`
  line
  line `(a) gold;`
  line
  line `(b) diamonds;`
  line
  line `(c) manufactures of gold or diamonds;`
  line
  line `(d) watches;`
  line
  line `(e) any other class of goods which the Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, specify.`
obj_root_law_sections_102:
  sectionId (30999)
  sectionNo (102)
  orderNo 165
  title `Persons to be searched may require to be taken before gazetted officer of customs or magistrate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_102_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=30999&sectionno=102&orderno=165&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_102_content:
  string
  line `(1) When any officer of customs is about to search any person under the provisions of`
  line `section 100 or section 101, the officer of customs shall, if such person so requires, take him without`
  line `unnecessary delay to the nearest gazetted officer of customs or magistrate.`
  line
  line `(2) If such requisition is made, the officer of customs may detain the person making it until he can`
  line `bring him before the gazetted officer of customs or the magistrate.`
  line
  line `(3) The gazetted officer of customs or the magistrate before whom any such person is brought shall, if`
  line `he sees no reasonable ground for search, forthwith discharge the person but otherwise shall direct that`
  line `search be made.`
  line
  line `(4) Before making a search under the provisions of section 100 or section 101, the officer of customs`
  line `shall call upon two or more persons to attend and witness the search and may issue an order in writing to`
  line `them or any of them so to do; and the search shall be made in the presence of such persons and a list of all`
  line `things seized in the course of such search shall be prepared by such officer or other person and signed by`
  line `such witness.`
  line
  line `(5) No female shall be searched by any one excepting a female.`
obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_103:
  sectionId (31000)
  sectionNo (103)
  orderNo 166
  title `Power to screen or X-ray bodies of suspected persons for detecting secreted goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_103_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31000&sectionno=103&orderno=166&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_103_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) Where the proper officer has reason to believe that any person referred to in sub-section (2) of section 100`
  line `has any goods liable to confiscation secreted inside his body, he may detain such person and shall,--`
  line
  line `(a) with the prior approval of the Deputy Commissioner of Customs or Assistant Commissioner`
  line `of Customs, as soon as practicable, screen or scan such person using such equipment as may be`
  line `available at the customs station, but without prejudice to any of the rights available to such person`
  line `under any other law for the time being in force, including his consent for such screening or scanning,`
  line `and forward a report of such screening or scanning to the nearest magistrate if such goods appear to`
  line `be secreted inside his body; or`
  line
  line `(b) produce him without unnecessary delay before the nearest magistrate.]`
  line
  line `(2) A magistrate before whom any person is brought under sub-section (1) shall, if he sees no`
  line `reasonable ground for believing that such person has any such goods secreted inside his body, forthwith`
  line `discharge such person.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any such magistrate has reasonable ground for believing that such person has any such`
  line `goods secreted inside his body and the magistrate is satisfied that for the purpose of discovering such`
  line `goods it is necessary to have the body of such person screened or X-rayed, he may make an order to that`
  line effect.
  line
  line `(4) Where a magistrate has made any order under sub-section (3), in relation to any person, the proper`
  line `officer shall, as soon as practicable, take such person before a radiologist possessing qualifications`
  line `recognized by the Central Government for the purpose of this section, and such person shall allow the`
  line `radiologist to screen or X-ray his body.`
  line
  line `(5) A radiologist before whom any person is brought under sub-section (4) shall, after screening or`
  line `X-raying the body of such person, forward his report, together with any X-ray pictures taken by him, to`
  line `the magistrate without unnecessary delay.`
  line
  line `(6) Where on receipt of a report ^2[from the proper officer under clause (a) of sub-section (1) or]`
  line `from a radiologist under sub-section (5) or otherwise, the magistrate is satisfied that any person has any`
  line `goods liable to confiscation secreted inside his body, he may direct that suitable action for bringing out`
  line `such goods be taken on the advice and under the supervision of a registered medical practitioner and such`
  line `person shall be bound to comply with such direction:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of a female no such action shall be taken except on the advice and under the`
  line `supervision of a female registered medical practitioner.`
  line
  line `(7) Where any person is brought before a magistrate under this section, such magistrate may for the`
  line `purpose of enforcing the provisions of this section order such person to be kept in such custody and for`
  line `such period as he may direct.`
  line
  line `(8) Nothing in this section shall apply to any person referred to in sub-section (1), who admits that`
  line `goods liable to confiscation are secreted inside his body, and who voluntarily submits himself for suitable`
  line `action being taken for bringing out such goods.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, the expression "registered medical practitioner"`
  line `means any person who holds a qualification granted by an authority specified in the Schedule to the`
  line `Indian Medical Degrees Act, 1916 (7 of 1916), or notified under section 3 of that Act, or by an authority`
  line `specified in any of the Schedules to the Indian Medical Council Act, 1956 (102 of 1956).`
obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 72, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 1-8-2019).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 72, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-8-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_104:
  sectionId (31001)
  sectionNo (104)
  orderNo 167
  title `Power to arrest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_104_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31001&sectionno=104&orderno=167&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_104_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) If an officer of customs empowered in this behalf by general or special`
  line `order of the ^2[Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs] has reason to believe`
  line `that any person ^3*** has committed an offence punishable under section 132 or section 133 or section 135`
  line `or section 135A or section 136, he may arrest such person and shall, as soon as may be, inform him of the`
  line `grounds for such arrest.]`
  line
  line `(2) Every person arrested under sub-section (1) shall, without unnecessary delay, be taken to a`
  line magistrate.
  line
  line `(3) Where an officer of customs has arrested any person under sub-section (1), he shall, for the`
  line `purpose of releasing such person on bail or otherwise, have the same powers and be subject to the same`
  line `provisions as the officer-in-charge of a police-station has and is subject to under the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898).`
  line
  line `^4[(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), any`
  line `offence relating to--`
  line
  line `(a) prohibited goods; or`
  line
  line `(b) evasion or attempted evasion of duty exceeding fifty lakh ^5[rupees; or],`
  line
  line `shall be cognizable.`
  line
  line `^6[(c) fraudulently availing of or attempting to avail drawback or any exemption from duty`
  line `provided under this Act, where the amount of drawback or exemption from duty exceeds fifty lakh`
  line `rupees; or`
  line
  line `(d) fraudulently obtaining an instrument for the purposes of this Act or the Foreign Trade`
  line `(Development and Regulation) Act, 1992 (22 of 1992), and such instrument is utilised under this Act,`
  line `where duty relatable to such utilisation of instrument exceeds fifty lakh rupees.]`
  line
  line `(5) Save as otherwise provided in sub-section (4), all other offences under the Act shall be`
  line non-cognizable.
  line
  line `^7[(6) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973, (2 of 1974) an`
  line `offence punishable under section 135 relating to--`
  line
  line `(a) evasion or attempted evasion of duty exceeding fifty lakh rupees; or`
  line
  line `(b) prohibited goods notified under section 11 which are also notified under sub-clause (c) of`
  line `clause (i) of sub-section (1) of section 135; or`
  line
  line `(c) import or export of any goods which have not been declared in accordance with the provisions`
  line `of this Act and the market price of which exceeds one crore rupees; or`
  line
  line `(d) fraudulently availing of or attempt to avail of drawback or any exemption from duty provided`
  line `under this Act, if the amount of drawback or exemption from duty exceeds fifty lakh ^5[rupees; or],`
  line `shall be non-bailable.`
  line
  line `^6[(e) fraudulently obtaining an instrument for the purposes of this Act or the Foreign Trade`
  line `(Development and Regulation) Act, 1992 (22 of 1992), and such instrument is utilised under this Act,`
  line `where duty relatable to such utilisation of instrument exceeds fifty lakh rupees.]`
  line
  line `(7) Save as otherwise provided in sub-section (6), all other offences under this Act shall be bailable.]`
  line
  line `^6[Explanation.--For the purposes of this Section, the expression "instrument" shall have the same`
  line `meaning as assigned to it in Explanation 1 to section 28AAA.]`
obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 29 of 2006, s. 24, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 13-7-2006).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 78, for "Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  line
  line `3. The words "in India or within the Indian customs waters" omitted by Act 23 of 2019, s. 73 (w.e.f. 1-8-2019).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 126, for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 28-5-2012).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 73, for "rupees," (w.e.f. 1-8-2019).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by s. 73, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-8-2019).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 75, for sub-section (6) (w.e.f. 10-5-2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_105:
  sectionId (31002)
  sectionNo (105)
  orderNo 168
  title `Power to search premises.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_105_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31002&sectionno=105&orderno=168&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_105_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the ^1[Assistant Commissioner of Customs or Deputy`
  line `Commissioner of Customs], or in any area adjoining the land frontier or the coast of India an officer of`
  line `customs specially empowered by name in this behalf by the Board, has reason to believe that any goods`
  line `liable to confiscation, or any documents or things which in his opinion will be useful for or relevant to`
  line `any proceeding under this Act, are secreted in any place, he may authorise any officer of customs to`
  line `search or may himself search for such goods, documents or things.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898), relating to searches shall, so`
  line `far as may be, apply to searches under this section subject to the modification that sub-section (5) of`
  line `section 165 of the said Code shall have effect as if for the word "Magistrate", wherever it occurs, the`
  line `words ^2[Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs] were substituted.`
obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 100, for "Assistant Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 11-5-1999).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 78, for "Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_106:
  sectionId (31003)
  sectionNo (106)
  orderNo 169
  title `Power to stop and search conveyances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_106_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31003&sectionno=106&orderno=169&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_106_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the proper officer has reason to believe`
  line `that any aircraft, vehicle or animal in India or any vessel in India or within the Indian customs waters has`
  line `been, is being, or is about to be, used in the smuggling of any goods or in the carriage of any goods which`
  line `have been smuggled, he may at any time stop any such vehicle, animal or vessel or, in the case of an`
  line `aircraft, compel it to land, and--`
  line
  line `(a) rummage and search any part of the aircraft, vehicle or vessel;`
  line
  line `(b) examine and search any goods in the aircraft, vehicle or vessel or on the animal;`
  line
  line `(c) break open the lock of any door or package for exercising the powers conferred by clauses (a)`
  line `and (b), if the keys are withheld.`
  line
  line `(2) Where for the purposes of sub-section (1)--`
  line
  line `(a) it becomes necessary to stop any vessel or compel any aircraft to land, it shall be lawful for`
  line `any vessel or aircraft in the service of the Government while flying her proper flag and any authority`
  line `authorised in this behalf by the Central Government to summon such vessel to stop or the aircraft to`
  line `land, by means of an international signal, code or other recognized means, and thereupon, such vessel`
  line `shall forthwith stop or such aircraft shall forthwith land; and if it fails to do so, chase may be given`
  line `thereto by any vessel or aircraft as aforesaid and if after a gun is fired as a signal the vessel fails to`
  line `stop or the aircraft fails to land, it may be fired upon;`
  line
  line `(b) it becomes necessary to stop any vehicle or animal, the proper officer may use all lawful`
  line `means for stopping it, and where such means fail, the vehicle or animal may be fired upon.`
obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_106_a:
  sectionId (31004)
  sectionNo 106A
  orderNo 170
  title `Power to inspect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_106_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_106_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31004&sectionno=106A&orderno=170&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_106_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[106A. Power to inspect.--Any proper officer authorised in this behalf by the ^2[Principal`
  line `Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs] may, for the purpose of ascertaining whether or`
  line `not the requirements of this Act have been complied with, at any reasonable time, enter any place`
  line `intimated under Chapter IVA or Chapter IVB, as the case may be, and inspect the goods kept or stored`
  line `therein and require any person found therein, who is for the time being in charge thereof, to produce to`
  line `him for his inspection the accounts maintained under the said Chapter IVA or Chapter IVB, as the case`
  line `may be, and to furnish to him such other information as he may reasonably require for the purpose of`
  line `ascertaining whether or not such goods have been illegally imported, exported or are likely to be illegally`
  line exported.]
obj_root_law_sections_106_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 12 of 1969, s. 3 (w.e.f. 3-1-1969).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 78, for "Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_107:
  sectionId (31005)
  sectionNo (107)
  orderNo 171
  title `Power to examine persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_107_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 78, for "Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31005&sectionno=107&orderno=171&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_107_content:
  string
  line `Any officer of customs empowered in this behalf by general or`
  line `special order of the ^1[Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs] may, during the`
  line `course of any enquiry in connection with the smuggling of any goods,--`
  line
  line `(a) require any person to produce or deliver any document or thing relevant to the enquiry;`
  line
  line `(b) examine any person acquainted with the facts and circumstances of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_108:
  sectionId (31006)
  sectionNo (108)
  orderNo 172
  title `Power to summon persons to give evidence and produce documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_108_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31006&sectionno=108&orderno=172&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_108_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) Any Gazetted`
  line `Officer of customs ^2*** shall have power to summon any person whose attendance he considers`
  line `necessary either to give evidence or to produce a document or any other thing in any inquiry which such`
  line `officer is making under this Act.]`
  line
  line `(2) A summons to produce documents or other things may be for the production of certain specified`
  line `documents or things or for the production of all documents or things of a certain description in the`
  line `possession or under the control of the person summoned.`
  line
  line `(3) All persons so summoned shall be bound to attend either in person or by an authorised agent, as`
  line `such officer may direct; and all persons so summoned shall be bound to state the truth upon any subject`
  line `respecting which they are examined or make statements and produce such documents and other things as`
  line `may be required:`
  line
  line `Provided that the exemption under section 132 of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), shall`
  line `be applicable to any requisition for attendance under this section.`
  line
  line `(4) Every such inquiry as aforesaid shall be deemed to be a judicial proceeding within the meaning of`
  line `section 193 and section 228 of the Indian Penal Code, 1860 (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 29 of 2006, s. 25, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 13-7-2006).`
  line
  line `2. The words "duly empowered by the Central Government in this behalf", omitted by Act 18 of 2008, s. 69 (w.e.f. 13-7-2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_108_a:
  sectionId (31007)
  sectionNo 108A
  orderNo 173
  title `Obligation to furnish information`
  content obj_root_law_sections_108_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 2017, s. 3 (w.e.f. 4-5-2017).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31007&sectionno=108A&orderno=173&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_108_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[108A. Obligation to furnish information.--(1) Any person, being--`
  line
  line `(a) a local authority or other public body or association; or`
  line
  line `(b) any authority of the State Government responsible for the collection of value added tax or`
  line `sales tax or any other tax relating to the goods or services; or`
  line
  line `(c) an income-tax authority appointed under the provisions of the Income tax Act, 1961 (43 of`
  line `1961); or`
  line
  line `(d) a Banking company within the meaning of clause (a) of section 45A of the Reserve Bank of`
  line `India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934); or`
  line
  line `(e) a co-operative bank within the meaning of clause (dd) of section 2 of the Deposit Insurance`
  line `and Credit Guarantee Corporation Act,1961 (45 of 1961); or`
  line
  line `(f) a financial institution within the meaning of clause (c), or a non-banking financial company`
  line `within the meaning of clause (f), of section 45-I of the Reserve Bank of India Act,1934 (2 of 1934);`
  line or
  line
  line `(g) a State Electricity Board; or an electricity distribution or transmission licensee under the`
  line `Electricity Act, 2003 (36 of 2003), or any other entity entrusted, as the case may be, with such`
  line `functions by the Central Government or the State Government; or`
  line
  line `(h) the Registrar or Sub-Registrar appointed under section 6 of the Registration Act, 1908 (16 of`
  line `1908); or`
  line
  line `(i) a Registrar within the meaning of the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013); or`
  line
  line `(j) the registering authority empowered to register motor vehicles under Chapter IV of the Motor`
  line `Vehicles Act, 1988 (59 of 1988); or`
  line
  line `(k) the Collector referred to in clause (c) of section 3 of the Right to Fair Compensation and`
  line `Transparency in Land Acquisition, Rehabilitation and Resettlement Act, 2013 (30 of 2013); or`
  line
  line `(l) the recognised stock exchange referred to in clause (f) of section 2 of the Securities Contracts`
  line `(Regulation) Act, 1956 (42 of 1956); or`
  line
  line `(m) a depository referred to in clause (e) of sub-section (1) of section 2 of the Depositories`
  line `Act, 1996 (22 of 1996); or`
  line
  line `(n) the Post Master General within the meaning of clause (j) of section 2 of the Indian Post Office`
  line `Act, 1898 (6 of 1898); or`
  line
  line `(o) the Director General of Foreign Trade within the meaning of clause (d) of section 2 of the`
  line `Foreign Trade (Development and Regulation) Act,1992 (22 of 1992); or`
  line
  line `(p) the General Manager of a Zonal Railway within the meaning of clause (18) of section 2 of the`
  line `Railways Act,1989 (24 of 1989); or`
  line
  line `(q) an officer of the Reserve Bank of India constituted under section 3 of the Reserve Bank of`
  line `India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934),`
  line
  line `who is responsible for maintaining record of registration or statement of accounts or holding any other`
  line `information under any of the Acts specified above or under any other law for the time being in force,`
  line `which is considered relevant for the purposes of this Act, shall furnish such information to the proper`
  line `officer in such manner as may be prescribed by rules made under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the proper officer considers that the information furnished under sub-section (1) is`
  line `defective, he may intimate the defect to the person who has furnished such information and give him an`
  line `opportunity of rectifying the defect within a period of seven days from the date of such intimation or`
  line `within such further period which, on an application made in this behalf, the proper officer may allow and`
  line `if the defect is not rectified within the said period of seven days or, further period, as the case may be, so allowed, then, notwithstanding anything contained in any other provision of this Act, such information`
  line `shall be deemed as not furnished and the provisions of this Act shall apply.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a person who is required to furnish information has not furnished the same within the time`
  line `specified in sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), the proper officer may serve upon him a notice requiring`
  line `him to furnish such information within a period not exceeding thirty days from the date of service of the`
  line `notice and such person shall furnish such information.]`
obj_root_law_sections_108_b:
  sectionId (31008)
  sectionNo 108B
  orderNo 174
  title `Penalty for failure to furnish information return.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_108_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 2017, s. 3 (w.e.f. 4-5-2017).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31008&sectionno=108B&orderno=174&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_108_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[108B. Penalty for failure to furnish information return.--Where the person who is required to`
  line `furnish information under section 108A fails to do so within the period specified in the notice issued`
  line `under sub-section (3) thereof, the proper officer may direct such person to pay, by way of penalty, a sum`
  line `of one hundred rupees for each day of the period during which the failure to furnish such information`
  line continue.]
obj_root_law_sections_109:
  sectionId (31009)
  sectionNo (109)
  orderNo 175
  title `Power to require production of order permitting clearance of goods imported by land.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_109_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31009&sectionno=109&orderno=175&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_109_content:
  string
  line `Any officer of customs appointed for any area adjoining the land frontier of India and empowered in this`
  line `behalf by general or special order of the Board, may require any person in possession of any goods which`
  line `such officer has reason to believe to have been imported into India by land, to produce the order made`
  line `under section 47 permitting clearance of the goods:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall apply to any imported goods passing from a land frontier to`
  line `a land customs station by a route appointed under clause (c) of section 7.`
obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_109_a:
  sectionId (31010)
  sectionNo 109A
  orderNo 176
  title `Power to undertake controlled delivery.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_109_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 91 (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31010&sectionno=109A&orderno=176&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_109_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[109A. Power to undertake controlled delivery.--Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act,`
  line `the proper officer or any other officer authorised by him in this behalf, may undertake controlled delivery`
  line `of any consignment of such goods and in such manner as may be prescribed, to--`
  line
  line `(a) any destination in India; or`
  line
  line `(b) a foreign country, in consultation with the competent authority of such country to which such`
  line `consignment is destined.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section "controlled delivery" means the procedure of allowing`
  line `consignment of such goods to pass out of, or into, the territory of India with the knowledge and under the`
  line `supervision of proper officer for identifying the persons involved in the commission of an offence or`
  line `contravention under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_110:
  sectionId (31011)
  sectionNo (110)
  orderNo 177
  title `Seizure of goods, documents and things.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_110_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31011&sectionno=110&orderno=177&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_110_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the proper officer has reason to believe that`
  line `any goods are liable to confiscation under this Act, he may seize such goods:`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that where it is not practicable to remove, transport, store or take physical possession of`
  line `the seized goods for any reason, the proper officer may give custody of the seized goods to the owner of`
  line `the goods or the beneficial owner or any person holding himself out to be the importer, or any other`
  line `person from whose custody such goods have been seized, on execution of an undertaking by such person`
  line `that he shall not remove, part with, or otherwise deal with the goods except with the previous permission`
  line `of such officer:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where it is not practicable to seize any such goods, the proper officer may serve`
  line `an order on the owner of the goods or the beneficial owner or any person holding himself out to be`
  line `importer, or any other person from whose custody such goods have been found, directing that such person`
  line `shall not remove, part with, or otherwise deal with such goods except with the previous permission of`
  line `such officer.]`
  line
  line `^2[(1A) The Central Government may, having regard to the perishable or hazardous nature of any`
  line `goods, depreciation in the value of the goods with the passage of time, constraints of storage space for the`
  line `goods or any other relevant considerations, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify the goods or`
  line `class of goods which shall, as soon as may be after its seizure under sub-section (1), be disposed of by the`
  line `proper officer in such manner as the Central Government may, from time to time, determine after`
  line `following the procedure hereinafter specified.`
  line
  line `(1B) Where any goods, being goods specified under sub-section (1A), have been seized by a proper`
  line `officer under sub-section (1), he shall prepare an inventory of such goods containing such details relating`
  line `to their description, quality, quantity, mark, numbers, country of origin and other particulars as the proper`
  line `officer may consider relevant to the identity of the goods in any proceedings under this Act and shall`
  line `make an application to a Magistrate for the purpose of--`
  line
  line `(a) certifying the correctness of the inventory so prepared; or`
  line
  line `(b) taking, in the presence of the Magistrate, photographs of such goods, and certifying such`
  line `photographs as true; or`
  line
  line `(c) allowing to draw representative samples of such goods, in the presence of the Magistrate, and`
  line `certifying the correctness of any list of samples so drawn.`
  line
  line `(1C) Where an application is made under sub-section (1B), the Magistrate shall, as soon as may be,`
  line `allow the application.]`
  line
  line `^3[(1D) Where the goods seized under sub-section (1) is gold in any form as notified under sub-section (1A), then, the proper officer shall, instead of making an application under sub-section (1B) to the Magistrate, make such application to the Commissioner (Appeals) having jurisdiction, who shall, as soon as may be, allow the application and thereafter, the proper officer shall dispose of such goods in such manner as the Central Government may determine.]`
  line
  line `(2) Where any goods are seized under sub-section (1) and no notice in respect thereof is given under`
  line `clause (a) of section 124 within six months of the seizure of the goods, the goods shall be returned to the`
  line `person from whose possession they were seized:`
  line
  line `^4[Provided that the Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs may, for`
  line `reasons to be recorded in writing, extend such period to a further period not exceeding six months and`
  line `inform the person from whom such goods were seized before the expiry of the period so specified:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where any order for provisional release of the seized goods has been passed`
  line `under section 110A, the specified period of six months shall not apply.]`
  line
  line `(3) The proper officer may seize any documents or things which, in his opinion, will be useful for, or`
  line `relevant to, any proceeding under this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) The person from whose custody any documents are seized under sub-section (3) shall be entitled`
  line `to make copies thereof or take extracts therefrom in the presence of an officer of customs.`
  line
  line `^5[(5) Where the proper officer, during any proceedings under the Act, is of the opinion that for the`
  line `purposes of protecting the interest of revenue or preventing smuggling, it is necessary so to do, he may,`
  line `with the approval of the Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs, by order in`
  line `writing, provisionally attach any bank account for a period not exceeding six months:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs may, for reasons`
  line `to be recorded in writing, extend such period to a further period not exceeding six months and inform`
  line `such extension of time to the person whose bank account is provisionally attached, before the expiry of`
  line `the period so specified.]`
obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 74, for the Proviso (w.e.f. 1-8-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 80 of 1985, s. 8 (w.e.f. 27-12-1985).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 94 (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 92, for the proviso (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 74 (w.e.f. 1-8-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_110_a:
  sectionId (31013)
  sectionNo 110A
  orderNo 178
  title `Provisional release of goods, documents and things seized pending adjudication.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_110_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_110_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31013&sectionno=110A&orderno=178&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_110_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[110A. Provisional release of goods, documents and things seized ^2[or bank account`
  line `provisionally attached pending adjudication.--Any goods, documents or things seized ^2[or bank`
  line `account provisionally attached] under section 110, may, pending the order of the ^3[adjudicating`
  line `authority], be released to the owner ^2[or the bank account holder] on taking a bond from him in the proper`
  line `form with such security and conditions as the ^4[adjudicating authority] may require.]`
obj_root_law_sections_110_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2006, s. 26 (w.e.f. 13-7-2006).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 75 (w.e.f. 1-8-2019).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 8 of 2011, s. 47, for "adjudicating officer" (w.e.f. 8-4-2011).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 47, ibid., for "Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 8-4-2011).`
obj_root_law_sections_110_aa:
  sectionId (64791)
  sectionNo 110AA
  orderNo 179
  title `Action subsequent to inquiry, investigation or audit or any other specified purpose`
  content obj_root_law_sections_110_aa_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 6 of 2022, s. 94 (w.e.f. 30-3-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=64791&sectionno=110AA&orderno=179&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_110_aa_content:
  string
  line `^1[110AA. Action subsequent to inquiry, investigation or audit or any other specified purpose.--Where in pursuance of any proceeding, in accordance with Chapter XIIA or this Chapter, if an officer of customs has reasons to believe that--`
  line
  line `(a) any duty has been short-levied, not levied, short-paid or not paid in a case where assessment has already been made;`
  line
  line `(b) any duty has been erroneously refunded;`
  line
  line `(c) any drawback has been erroneously allowed; or`
  line
  line `(d) any interest has been short-levied, not levied, short-paid or not paid, or erroneously refunded,`
  line
  line `then such officer of customs shall, after causing inquiry, investigation, or as the case may be, audit, transfer the relevant documents, along with a report in writing`
  line
  line `(i) to the proper officer having jurisdiction, as assigned under section 5 in respect of assessment of such duty, or to the officer who allowed such refund or drawback; or`
  line
  line `(ii) in case of multiple jurisdictions, to an officer of customs to whom such matter is assigned by the Board, in exercise of the powers conferred under section 5,`
  line
  line `and thereupon, power exercisable under sections 28, 28AAA or Chapter X, shall be exercised by such proper officer or by an officer to whom the proper officer is subordinate in accordance with sub-section (2) of section 5.]`
obj_root_law_sections_111:
  sectionId (31014)
  sectionNo (111)
  orderNo 180
  title `Confiscation of improperly imported goods, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_111_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31014&sectionno=111&orderno=180&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_111_content:
  string
  line `The following goods brought from a place`
  line `outside India shall be liable to confiscation:--`
  line
  line `(a) any goods imported by sea or air which are unloaded or attempted to be unloaded at any place`
  line `other than a customs port or customs airport appointed under clause (a) of section 7 for the unloading`
  line `of such goods;`
  line
  line `(b) any goods imported by land or inland water through any route other than a route specified in a`
  line `notification issued under clause (c) of section 7 for the import of such goods;`
  line
  line `(c) any dutiable or prohibited goods brought into any bay, gulf, creek or tidal river for the purpose`
  line `of being landed at a place other than a customs port;`
  line
  line `(d) any goods which are imported or attempted to be imported or are brought within the Indian`
  line `customs waters for the purpose of being imported, contrary to any prohibition imposed by or under`
  line `this Act or any other law for the time being in force;`
  line
  line `(e) any dutiable or prohibited goods found concealed in any manner in any conveyance;`
  line
  line `(f) any dutiable or prohibited goods required to be mentioned under the regulations in an ^1[arrival`
  line `manifest or import manifest] or import report which are not so mentioned;`
  line
  line `(g) any dutiable or prohibited goods which are unloaded from a conveyance in contravention of`
  line `the provisions of section 32, other than goods inadvertently unloaded but included in the record kept`
  line `under sub-section (2) of section 45;`
  line
  line `(h) any dutiable or prohibited goods unloaded or attempted to be unloaded in contravention of the`
  line `provisions of section 33 or section 34;`
  line
  line `(i) any dutiable or prohibited goods found concealed in any manner in any package either before`
  line `or after the unloading thereof;`
  line
  line `(j) any dutiable or prohibited goods removed or attempted to be removed from a customs area or`
  line `a warehouse without the permission of the proper officer or contrary to the terms of such permission;`
  line
  line `(k) any dutiable or prohibited goods imported by land in respect of which the order permitting`
  line `clearance of the goods required to be produced under section 109 is not produced or which do not`
  line `correspond in any material particular with the specification contained therein;`
  line
  line `(l) any dutiable or prohibited goods which are not included or are in excess of those included in`
  line `the entry made under this Act, or in the case of baggage in the declaration made under section 77;`
  line
  line `(m)`
  line `^2[any goods which do not correspond in respect of value or in any other particular with the`
  line `entry made under this Act or in the case of baggage with the declaration made under section 77 ^3[in`
  line `respect thereof, or in the case of goods under transhipment, with the declaration`
  line `for transhipment referred to in the proviso to sub-section (1) of section 54];`
  line
  line `(n) any dutiable or prohibited goods transited with or without transhipment or attempted to be`
  line `so transited in contravention of the provisions of Chapter VIII;`
  line
  line `(o) any goods exempted, subject to any condition, from duty or any prohibition in respect of the`
  line `import thereof under this Act or any other law for the time being in force, in respect of which the`
  line `condition is not observed unless the non-observance of the condition was sanctioned by the proper`
  line officer;
  line
  line `^4[(p) any notified goods in relation to which any provisions of Chapter IVA or of any rule made`
  line `under this Act for carrying out the purposes of that Chapter have been contravened.]`
  line
  line `^5[(q) any goods imported on a claim of preferential rate of duty which contravenes any provision`
  line `of Chapter VAA or any rule made thereunder.]`
obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 56, for "import manifest" (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 36 of 1973, s. 2, for "any dutiable or prohibited goods which do not correspond in any material particular"`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-9-1973).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 108, for "in respect thereof", (w.e.f. 11-5-1999).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 12 of 1969, s. 4 (w.e.f. 3-1-1969).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 12 of 2020, s. 113 (w.e.f. 27-3-2020).`
obj_root_law_sections_112:
  sectionId (31016)
  sectionNo (112)
  orderNo 181
  title `Penalty for improper importation of goods, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_112_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31016&sectionno=112&orderno=181&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_112_content:
  string
  line `Any person,--`
  line
  line `(a) who, in relation to any goods, does or omits to do any act which act or omission would render`
  line `such goods liable to confiscation under section 111, or abets the doing or omission of such an act, or`
  line
  line `(b) who acquires possession of or is in any way concerned in carrying, removing,`
  line `depositing, harbouring, keeping, concealing, selling or purchasing, or in any other manner dealing`
  line `with any goods which he knows or has reason to believe are liable to confiscation under section 111,`
  line
  line `shall be liable,--`
  line
  line `(i) in the case of goods in respect of which any prohibition is in force under this Act or any other`
  line `law for the time being in force, to a penalty ^1[not exceeding the value of the goods or five thousand`
  line `rupees], whichever is the greater;`
  line
  line `^2[(ii) in the case of dutiable goods, other than prohibited goods, subject to the provisions of`
  line `section 114A, to a penalty not exceeding ten per cent. of the duty sought to be evaded or five`
  line `thousand rupees, whichever is higher:`
  line
  line `Provided that where such duty as determined under sub-section (8) of section 28 and the interest`
  line `payable thereon under section 28AA is paid within thirty days from the date of communication of the`
  line `order of the proper officer determining such duty, the amount of penalty liable to be paid by such`
  line `person under this section shall be twenty-five per cent. of the penalty so determined;]`
  line
  line `^3[(iii) in the case of goods in respect of which the value stated in the entry made under this Act or`
  line `in the case of baggage, in the declaration made under section 77 (in either case hereafter in this`
  line `section referred to as the declared value) is higher than the value thereof, to a penalty ^4[not exceeding`
  line `the difference between the declared value and the value thereof or five thousand rupees], whichever is`
  line `the greater;`
  line
  line `(iv) in the case of goods falling both under clauses (i) and (iii), to a penalty ^5[not exceeding the`
  line `value of the goods or the difference between the declared value and the value thereof or five thousand`
  line `rupees], whichever is the highest;`
  line
  line `(v) in the case of goods falling both under clauses (ii) and (iii), to a penalty ^6[not exceeding the`
  line `duty sought to be evaded on such goods or the difference between the declared value and the value`
  line `thereof or five thousand rupees], whichever is the highest.]`
obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 107, for "not exceeding five times the value of the goods or one thousand rupees"`
  line `(w.e.f. 11-5-2001).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 83, for sub-clause (ii) (w.e.f. 14-5-2015).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 36 of 1973, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-9-1973).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 107, for "not exceeding five times the difference between the declared value and the value thereof`
  line `or one thousand rupees" (w.e.f. 11-5-2001).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 107, ibid., for "not exceeding five times the value of the goods or five times the difference between the declared`
  line `value and the value thereof or one thousand rupees" (w.e.f. 11-5-2001).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 107, ibid., for "not exceeding five times the duty sought to be evaded on such goods or five times the difference`
  line `between the declared value and the value thereof or one thousand rupees" (w.e.f. 11-5-2001).`
obj_root_law_sections_113:
  sectionId (31017)
  sectionNo (113)
  orderNo 182
  title `Confiscation of goods attempted to be improperly exported, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_113_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31017&sectionno=113&orderno=182&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_113_content:
  string
  line `The following export`
  line `goods shall be liable to confiscation:--`
  line
  line `(a) any goods attempted to be exported by sea or air from any place other than a customs port or a`
  line `customs airport appointed for the loading of such goods;`
  line
  line `(b) any goods attempted to be exported by land or inland water through any route other than a`
  line `route specified in a notification issued under clause (c) of section 7 for the export of such goods;`
  line
  line `(c) any ^1*** goods brought near the land frontier or the coast of India or near any bay, gulf, creek`
  line `creek or tidal river for the purpose of being exported from a place other than a land customs station or`
  line `a customs port appointed for the loading of such goods;`
  line
  line `(d) any goods attempted to be exported or brought within the limits of any customs area for the`
  line `purpose of being exported, contrary to any prohibition imposed by or under this Act or any other law`
  line `for the time being in force;`
  line
  line `(e) any ^1*** goods found concealed in a package which is brought within the limits of a customs`
  line `area for the purpose of exportation;`
  line
  line `(f) any ^1*** goods which are loaded or attempted to be loaded in contravention of the provisions`
  line `of section 33 or section 34;`
  line
  line `(g) any ^1*** goods loaded or attempted to be loaded on any conveyance, or water-borne, or`
  line `attempted to be water-borne for being loaded on any vessel, the eventual destination of which is a`
  line `place outside India, without the permission of the proper officer;`
  line
  line `(h) any ^1*** goods which are not included or are in excess of those included in the entry made`
  line `under this Act, or in the case of baggage in the declaration made under section 77;`
  line
  line `^2[(i) any goods entered for exportation which do not correspond in respect of value or in any`
  line `material particular with the entry made under this Act or in the case of baggage with the declaration`
  line `made under section 77;]`
  line
  line `^3[(ii) any goods entered for exportation under claim for drawback which do not correspond in any`
  line `material particular with any information furnished by the exporter or manufacturer under this Act in`
  line `relation to the fixation of rate of drawback under section 75;]`
  line
  line `(j) any goods on which import duty has not been paid and which are entered for exportation under`
  line `a claim for drawback under section 74;`
  line
  line `^4[(ja) any goods entered for exportation under claim of remission or refund of any duty or tax or levy to make a wrongful claim in contravention of the provisions of this Act or any other law for the time being in force;]`
  line
  line `(k) any goods cleared for exportation ^5*** which are not loaded for exportation on account of any`
  line `wilful act, negligence or default of the exporter, his agent or employee, or which after having been`
  line `loaded for exportation are unloaded without the permission of the proper officer;`
  line
  line `^6[(l) any specified goods in relation to which any provisions of Chapter IVB or of any rule made`
  line `under this Act for carrying out the purposes of that Chapter have been contravened.]`
obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words dutiable or prohibited omitted by Act 32 of 2003, s. 116 (w.e.f. 14-5-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 116, for clause (i) (w.e.f. 14-5-2003).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 95 (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 120 (w.e.f. 27-9-1991).`
  line
  line `5. The words under a claim for drawback omitted by Act 32 of 2003, s. 116 (w.e.f. 14-5-2003).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 12 of 1969, s. 5 (w.e.f. 3-1-1969).`
obj_root_law_sections_114:
  sectionId (31018)
  sectionNo (114)
  orderNo 183
  title `Penalty for attempt to export goods improperly, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_114_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_114_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31018&sectionno=114&orderno=183&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_114_content:
  string
  line `Any person who, in relation to any`
  line `goods, does or omits to do any act which act or omission would render such goods liable to confiscation`
  line `under section 113, or abets the doing or omission of such an act, shall be liable,--`
  line
  line `(i) in the case of goods in respect of which any prohibition is in force under this Act or any other`
  line `law for the time being in force, to a penalty ^1[not exceeding three times the value of the goods as`
  line `declared by the exporter or the value as determined under this Act], whichever is the greater;`
  line
  line `^2[(ii) in the case of dutiable goods, other than prohibited goods, subject to the provisions of`
  line `section 114A, to a penalty not exceeding ten per cent. of the duty sought to be evaded or five`
  line `thousand rupees, whichever is higher:`
  line
  line `Provided that where such duty as determined under sub-section (8) of section 28 and the interest`
  line `payable thereon under section 28AA is paid within thirty days from the date of communication of the`
  line `order of the proper officer determining such duty, the amount of penalty liable to be paid by such`
  line `person under this section shall be twenty-five per cent. of the penalty so determined;]`
  line
  line `^3[(iii) in the case of any other goods, to a penalty not exceeding the value of the goods, as`
  line `declared by the exporter or the value as determined under this Act, whichever is the greater.]`
obj_root_law_sections_114_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 117, for not exceeding the value of the goods or five thousand rupees (w.e.f. 14-5-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 84, for clause (ii) (w.e.f. 14-5-2015).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 117, for clause (iii) (w.e.f. 14-5-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_114_a:
  sectionId (31019)
  sectionNo 114A
  orderNo 184
  title `Penalty for short-levy or non-levy of duty in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_114_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_114_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31019&sectionno=114A&orderno=184&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_114_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[114A. Penalty for short-levy or non-levy of duty in certain cases.--Where the duty has not been`
  line `been levied or has been short-levied or the interest has not been charged or paid or has been part paid or`
  line `the duty or interest has been erroneously refunded by reason of collusion or any wilful mis-statement or`
  line `suppression of facts, the person who is liable to pay the duty or interest, as the case may be, as determined`
  line `under ^2[sub-section (8) of section 28] shall, also be liable to pay a penalty equal to the duty or interest so`
  line `determined:]`
  line
  line `^3[Provided that where such duty or interest, as the case may be, as determined under ^2[sub-section (8)`
  line `of section 28], and the interest payable thereon under section ^4[28AA], is paid within thirty days from the`
  line `date of the communication of the order of the proper officer determining such duty, the amount of penalty liable to be paid by such person under this section shall be twenty-five per cent. of the duty or interest, as`
  line `the case may be, so determined:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the benefit of reduced penalty under the first proviso shall be available subject`
  line `to the condition that the amount of penalty so determined has also been paid within the period of thirty`
  line `days referred to in that proviso:`
  line
  line `Provided also that where the duty or interest determined to be payable is reduced or increased by the`
  line `Commissioner (Appeals), the Appellate Tribunal or, as the case may be, the court, then, for the purposes`
  line `of this section, the duty or interest as reduced or increased, as the case may be, shall be taken into`
  line `account:`
  line
  line `Provided also that in a case where the duty or interest determined to be payable is increased by the`
  line `Commissioner (Appeals), the Appellate Tribunal or, as the case may be, the court, then, the benefit of`
  line `reduced penalty under the first proviso shall be available if the amount of the duty or the interest so`
  line `increased, along with the interest payable thereon under section ^5[28AA], and twenty-five per cent. of the`
  line `consequential increase in penalty have also been paid within thirty days of the communication of the`
  line `order by which such increase in the duty or interest takes effect:`
  line
  line `Provided also that where any penalty has been levied under this section, no penalty shall be levied`
  line `under section 112 or section 114.]`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that--`
  line
  line `(i) the provisions of this section shall also apply to cases in which the order determining the duty`
  line `or interest under ^6[sub-section (8) of section 28] relates to notices issued prior to the date on which`
  line `the Finance Act, 2000 (10 of 2000) receives the assent of the President;`
  line
  line `(ii) any amount paid to the credit of the Central Government prior to the date of communication`
  line `of the order referred to in the first proviso or the fourth proviso shall be adjusted against the total`
  line `amount due from such person.]`
obj_root_law_sections_114_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 33 of 1996, s. 64 (w.e.f. 28-9-1996).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 8 of 2011, s. 48, for "sub-section (2) of section 28" (w.e.f. 8-4-2011).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 85, for the first and second provisos (w.e.f. 12-5-2000).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 8 of 2011, s. 48, for "28AB" (w.e.f. 8-4-2011).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 8 of 2011, s. 48, for "28AB" (w.e.f. 8-4-2011).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 48, ibid., for "sub-section (2) of section 28" (w.e.f. 8-4-2011).`
obj_root_law_sections_114_aa:
  sectionId (31020)
  sectionNo 114AA
  orderNo 185
  title `Penalty for use of false and incorrect material.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_114_aa_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2006, s. 27 (w.e.f. 13-7-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31020&sectionno=114AA&orderno=185&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_114_aa_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[114AA. Penalty for use of false and incorrect material.--If a person knowingly or intentionally`
  line `makes, signs or uses, or causes to be made, signed or used, any declaration, statement or document which`
  line `is false or incorrect in any material particular, in the transaction of any business for the purposes of this`
  line `Act, shall be liable to a penalty not exceeding five times the value of goods.]`
obj_root_law_sections_114_ab:
  sectionId (50253)
  sectionNo 114AB
  orderNo 186
  title `Penalty for obtaining instrument by fraud, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_114_ab_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 76 (w.e.f. 1-8-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=50253&sectionno=114AB&orderno=186&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_114_ab_content:
  string
  line `^1[114AB. Penalty for obtaining instrument by fraud, etc.--Where any person has obtained any`
  line `instrument by fraud, collusion, willful misstatement or suppression of facts and such instrument has been`
  line `utilised by such person or any other person for discharging duty, the person to whom the instrument was`
  line `issued shall be liable for penalty not exceeding the face value of such instrument.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, the expression "instrument" shall have the same`
  line `meaning as assigned to it in the Explanation 1 to section 28AAA.]`
obj_root_law_sections_114_ac:
  sectionId (56413)
  sectionNo 114AC
  orderNo 187
  title `Penalty for fraudulent utilisation of input tax credit for claiming refund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_114_ac_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 96 (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=56413&sectionno=114AC&orderno=187&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_114_ac_content:
  string
  line `^1[114AC. Penalty for fraudulent utilisation of input tax credit for claiming refund.Where any`
  line `person has obtained any invoice by fraud, collusion, wilful misstatement or suppression of facts to utilise`
  line `input tax credit on the basis of such invoice for discharging any duty or tax on goods that are entered for`
  line `exportation under claim of refund of such duty or tax, such person shall be liable for penalty not`
  line `exceeding five times the refund claimed.`
  line
  line `Explanation.For the purposes of this section, the expression input tax credit shall have the same`
  line `meaning as assigned to it in clause (63) of section 2 of the Central Goods and Services Tax Act, 2017 (12`
  line `of 2017).]`
obj_root_law_sections_115:
  sectionId (31021)
  sectionNo (115)
  orderNo 188
  title `Confiscation of conveyances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_115_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31021&sectionno=115&orderno=188&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_115_content:
  string
  line `(1) The following conveyances shall be liable to`
  line `confiscation:--`
  line
  line `(a) any vessel which is or has been within the Indian customs waters, any aircraft which is or has`
  line `been in India, or any vehicle which is or has been in a customs area, while constructed, adapted,`
  line `altered or fitted in any manner for the purpose of concealing goods;`
  line
  line `(b) any conveyance from which the whole or any part of the goods is thrown overboard, staved or`
  line `destroyed so as to prevent seizure by an officer of customs;`
  line
  line `(c) any conveyance which having been required to stop or land under section 106 fails to do so,`
  line `except for good and sufficient cause;`
  line
  line `(d) any conveyance from which any warehoused goods cleared for exportation, or any other`
  line `goods cleared for exportation under a claim for drawback, are unloaded, without the permission of the`
  line `proper officer;`
  line
  line `(e) any conveyance carrying imported goods which has entered India and is afterwards found`
  line `with the whole or substantial portion of such goods missing, unless the master of the vessel or aircraft`
  line `is able to account for the loss of, or deficiency in, the goods.`
  line
  line `(2) Any conveyance or animal used as a means of transport in the smuggling of any goods or in the`
  line `carriage of any smuggled goods shall be liable to confiscation, unless the owner of the conveyance or`
  line `animal proves that it was so used without the knowledge or connivance of the owner himself, his agent, if`
  line `any, and the person in charge of the conveyance or animal ^1***:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any such conveyance is used for the carriage of goods or passengers for hire, the`
  line `owner of any conveyance shall be given an option to pay in lieu of the confiscation of the conveyance a`
  line `fine not exceeding the market price of the goods which are sought to be smuggled or the smuggled goods,`
  line `as the case may be.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this section, "market price" means market price at the date when the goods are`
  line seized.
obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "and that each of them had taken all such precautions against such use as are for the time being specified in the`
  line `rules" omitted by Act 26 of 1988, s. 79 (w.e.f. 13-5-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_116:
  sectionId (31022)
  sectionNo (116)
  orderNo 189
  title `Penalty for not accounting for goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_116_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 100, for "Assistant Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 11-5-1999).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31022&sectionno=116&orderno=189&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_116_content:
  string
  line `If any goods loaded in a conveyance for importation`
  line `into India, or any goods transhipped under the provisions of this Act or coastal goods carried in a`
  line `conveyance, are not unloaded at their place of destination in India, or if the quantity unloaded is short of`
  line `the quantity to be unloaded at that destination, and if the failure to unload or the deficiency is not`
  line `accounted for to the satisfaction of the ^1[Assistant Commissioner of Customs or Deputy Commissioner of`
  line `Customs], the person-in-charge of the conveyance shall be liable,--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of goods loaded in a conveyance for importation into India or goods transhipped`
  line `under the provisions of this Act, to a penalty not exceeding twice the amount of duty that would have`
  line `been chargeable on the goods not unloaded or the deficient goods, as the case may be, had such goods`
  line `been imported;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of coastal goods, to a penalty not exceeding twice the amount of export duty that`
  line `would have been chargeable on the goods not unloaded or the deficient goods, as the case may be,`
  line `had such goods been exported.`
obj_root_law_sections_117:
  sectionId (31023)
  sectionNo (117)
  orderNo 190
  title `Penalties for contravention, etc., not expressly mentioned.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_117_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 77, for "one lakh rupees" (w.e.f. 1-8-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31023&sectionno=117&orderno=190&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_117_content:
  string
  line `Any person who contravenes`
  line `any provision of this Act or abets any such contravention or who fails to comply with any provision of`
  line `this Act with which it was his duty to comply, where no express penalty is elsewhere provided for such`
  line `contravention or failure, shall be liable to a penalty not exceeding ^1[four lakh rupees].`
obj_root_law_sections_118:
  sectionId (31024)
  sectionNo (118)
  orderNo 191
  title `Confiscation of packages and their contents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_118_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31024&sectionno=118&orderno=191&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_118_content:
  string
  line `(a) Where any goods imported in a package are`
  line `liable to confiscation, the package and any other goods imported in that package shall also be liable to`
  line confiscation.
  line
  line `(b) Where any goods are brought in a package within the limits of a customs area for the purpose of`
  line `exportation and are liable to confiscation, the package and any other goods contained therein shall also be`
  line `liable to confiscation.`
obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_119:
  sectionId (31025)
  sectionNo (119)
  orderNo 192
  title `Confiscation of goods used for concealing smuggled goods`
  content obj_root_law_sections_119_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31025&sectionno=119&orderno=192&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_119_content:
  string
  line `Any goods used for concealing`
  line `smuggled goods shall also be liable to confiscation.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this section, "goods" does not include a conveyance used as a means of transport.`
obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_120:
  sectionId (31026)
  sectionNo (120)
  orderNo 193
  title `Confiscation of smuggled goods notwithstanding any change in form, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_120_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31026&sectionno=120&orderno=193&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_120_content:
  string
  line `(1) Smuggled`
  line `goods may be confiscated notwithstanding any change in their form.`
  line
  line `(2) Where smuggled goods are mixed with other goods in such manner that the smuggled goods`
  line `cannot be separated from such other goods, the whole of the goods shall be liable to confiscation:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the owner of such goods proves that he had no knowledge or reason to believe`
  line `that they included any smuggled goods, only such part of the goods the value of which is equal to the`
  line `value of the smuggled goods shall be liable to confiscation.`
obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_121:
  sectionId (31027)
  sectionNo (121)
  orderNo 194
  title `Confiscation of sale-proceeds of smuggled goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_121_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_121_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31027&sectionno=121&orderno=194&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_121_content:
  string
  line `Where any smuggled goods are sold by a`
  line `person having knowledge or reason to believe that the goods are smuggled goods, the sale-proceeds`
  line `thereof shall be liable to confiscation.`
obj_root_law_sections_121_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_122:
  sectionId (31028)
  sectionNo (122)
  orderNo 195
  title `Adjudication of confiscations and penalties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_122_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31028&sectionno=122&orderno=195&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_122_content:
  string
  line `In every case under this Chapter in which`
  line `anything is liable to confiscation or any person is liable to a penalty, such confiscation or penalty may be`
  line adjudged,--
  line
  line `(a) without limit, by a ^1[Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs] or`
  line a
  line `^2[Joint Commissioner of Customs];`
  line
  line `^3[(b) up to such limit, by such officers, as the Board may, by notification, specify;]`
obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 78, for "Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 100, for "Deputy Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 11-5-1999).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 93, for clauses (b) and (c) (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_122_a:
  sectionId (31029)
  sectionNo 122A
  orderNo 196
  title `Adjudication Procedure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_122_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 67 (w.e.f. 10-9-2004).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31029&sectionno=122A&orderno=196&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_122_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[122A. Adjudication Procedure.--(1) The adjudicating authority shall, in any proceeding under`
  line `this Chapter or any other provision of this Act, give an opportunity of being heard to a party in a`
  line `proceeding, if the party so desires.`
  line
  line `(2) The adjudicating authority may, if sufficient cause is shown at any stage of proceeding referred to`
  line `in sub-section (1), grant time, from time to time, to the parties or any of them and adjourn the hearing for`
  line `reasons to be recorded in writing:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such adjournment shall be granted more than three times to a party during the`
  line proceeding.]
obj_root_law_sections_123:
  sectionId (31030)
  sectionNo (123)
  orderNo 197
  title `Burden of proof in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_123_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_123_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31030&sectionno=123&orderno=197&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_123_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) Where any goods to which this section applies are`
  line `seized under this Act in the reasonable belief that they are smuggled goods, the burden of proving that`
  line `they are not smuggled goods shall be--`
  line
  line `(a) in a case where such seizure is made from the possession of any person,--`
  line
  line `(i) on the person from whose possession the goods were seized; and`
  line
  line `(ii) if any person, other than the person from whose possession the goods were seized, claims`
  line `to be the owner thereof, also on such other person;`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, on the person, if any, who claims to be the owner of the goods so seized.]`
  line
  line `(2) This section shall apply to gold, ^2[and manufactures thereof], watches, and any other class of`
  line `goods which the Central Government may by notification in the Official Gazette specify.`
obj_root_law_sections_123_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 36 of 1973, s. 4, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 1-9-1973).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 40 of 1989, s. 2, for , "diamonds, manufactures of gold or diamonds" (w.e.f. 26-10-1989).`
obj_root_law_sections_124:
  sectionId (31031)
  sectionNo (124)
  orderNo 198
  title `Issue of show cause notice before confiscation of goods, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_124_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31031&sectionno=124&orderno=198&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_124_content:
  string
  line `No order confiscating any`
  line `goods or imposing any penalty on any person shall be made under this Chapter unless the owner of the`
  line `goods or such person--`
  line
  line `(a) is given a notice in ^1[writing with the prior approval of the officer of Customs not below the`
  line `rank of ^2[an Assistant Commissioner of Customs], informing] him of the grounds on which it is`
  line `proposed to confiscate the goods or to impose a penalty;`
  line
  line `(b) is given an opportunity of making a representation in writing within such reasonable time as`
  line `may be specified in the notice against the grounds of confiscation or imposition of penalty mentioned`
  line `therein; and`
  line
  line `(c) is given a reasonable opportunity of being heard in the matter:`
  line
  line `Provided that the notice referred to in clause (a) and the representation referred to in clause (b)`
  line `may, at the request of the person concerned be oral.`
  line
  line `^3[Provided further that notwithstanding issue of notice under this section, the proper officer may`
  line `issue a supplementary notice under such circumstances and in such manner as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 29 of 2006, s. 28, for "writing informing" (w.e.f. 13-7-2006).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 8 of 2011, s. 49, for "a Deputy Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 8-4-2011).`
  line
  line `3. The proviso ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 94 (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_125:
  sectionId (31032)
  sectionNo (125)
  orderNo 199
  title `Option to pay fine in lieu of confiscation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_125_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_125_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31032&sectionno=125&orderno=199&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_125_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever confiscation of any goods`
  line `is authorised by this Act, the officer adjudging it may, in the case of any goods, the importation or`
  line `exportation whereof is prohibited under this Act or under any other law for the time being in force, and`
  line `shall, in the case of any other goods, give to the owner of the goods ^1[or, where such owner is not known,`
  line `the person from whose possession or custody such goods have been seized,] an option to pay in lieu of`
  line `confiscation such fine as the said officer thinks fit:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that where the proceedings are deemed to be concluded under the proviso to`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 28 or under clause (i) of sub-section (6) of that section in respect of the goods`
  line `which are not prohibited or restricted, ^3[no such fine shall be imposed]:`
  line
  line `Provided further that], without prejudice to the provisions of the proviso to sub-section (2) of section`
  line `115, such fine shall not exceed the market price of the goods confiscated, less in the case of imported`
  line `goods the duty chargeable thereon.`
  line
  line `^4[(2) Where any fine in lieu of confiscation of goods is imposed under sub-section (1), the owner of`
  line `such goods or the person referred to in sub-section (1), shall, in addition, be liable to any duty and charges`
  line `payable in respect of such goods.]`
  line
  line `^5[(3) Where the fine imposed under sub-section (1) is not paid within a period of one hundred and`
  line `twenty days from the date of option given thereunder, such option shall become void, unless an appeal`
  line `against such order is pending.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that in cases where an order under`
  line `sub-section (1) has been passed before the date on which the Finance Bill, 2018 receives the assent of the`
  line `President and no appeal is pending against such order as on that date, the option under said sub-section`
  line `may be exercised within a period of one hundred and twenty days from the date on which such assent is`
  line received.]
obj_root_law_sections_125_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 80 of 1985, s. 9 (w.e.f. 27-12-1985).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 95, for Provided that (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 78, for "the provisions of this section shall not apply" (w.e.f. 1-8-2019).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 80 of 1985, s. 9, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 27-12-1985).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 95 (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_126:
  sectionId (31033)
  sectionNo (126)
  orderNo 200
  title `On confiscation, property to vest in Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_126_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_126_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31033&sectionno=126&orderno=200&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_126_content:
  string
  line `(1) When any goods are`
  line `confiscated under this Act, such goods shall thereupon vest in the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The officer adjudging confiscation shall take and hold possession of the confiscated goods.`
obj_root_law_sections_126_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_127:
  sectionId (31034)
  sectionNo (127)
  orderNo 201
  title `Award of confiscation or penalty by customs officers not to interfere with other punishments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_127_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_127_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31034&sectionno=127&orderno=201&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_127_content:
  string
  line `The award of any confiscation or penalty under this Act by an officer of customs shall`
  line `not prevent the infliction of any punishment to which the person affected thereby is liable under the`
  line `provisions of Chapter XVI of this Act or under any other law.`
obj_root_law_sections_127_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_127_a:
  sectionId (31035)
  sectionNo 127A
  orderNo 202
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_127_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_127_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31035&sectionno=127A&orderno=202&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_127_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[127A. Definitions.--In this Chapter, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Bench" means a Bench of the Settlement Commissioner;`
  line
  line `^2[(b) "case" means any proceeding under this Act or any other Act for the levy, assessment and`
  line `collection of customs duty, pending before an adjudicating authority on the date on which an`
  line `application under sub-section (1) of section 127B is made:`
  line
  line `Provided that when any proceeding is referred back ^3*** by any court, Appellate Tribunal or any`
  line `other authority, to the adjudicating authority for a fresh adjudication or decision, as the case may be,`
  line `then such proceeding shall not be deemed to be a proceeding pending within the meaning of this`
  line clause;]
  line
  line `(c) "Chairman" means the Chairman of the Settlement Commission;`
  line
  line `(d) "Commissioner (Investigation)" means an officer of the customs or a Central Excise Officer`
  line `appointed as such Commissioner to conduct inquiry or investigation for the purposes of this Chapter;`
  line
  line `(e) "Member" means a Member of the Settlement Commission and includes the Chairman and`
  line `the Vice Chairman;`
  line
  line `(f) "Settlement Commission" means the ^4[Customs, Central Excise and Service Tax Settlement`
  line `Commission] constituted under section 32 of the Central Excise Act, 1944 (1 of 1944); and`
  line
  line `(g) "Vice-Chairman" means a Vice-Chairman of the Settlement Commission.]`
obj_root_law_sections_127_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 102 (w.e.f. 1-8-1998).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 100, for clause (b) (w.e.f. 1-6-2007).`
  line
  line `3. The words "in any appeal or revision, as the case may be", omitted by Act 20 of 2015, s. 85 (w.e.f. 14-5-2015).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 83, for "Customs and Central Excise Settlement Commission" (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_127_b:
  sectionId (31036)
  sectionNo 127B
  orderNo 203
  title `Application for settlement of cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_127_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_127_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31036&sectionno=127B&orderno=203&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_127_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[127B. Application for settlement of cases.--^2[(1) Any importer, exporter or any other person`
  line `(hereinafter referred to as the applicant in this Chapter) may, in respect of a case, relating to him make an`
  line `application, before adjudication to the Settlement Commission to have the case settled, in such form and`
  line `in such manner as may be specified by rules, and containing a full and true disclosure of his duty liability`
  line `which has not been disclosed before the proper officer, the manner in which such liability has been`
  line `incurred, the additional amount of customs duty accepted to be payable by him and such other particulars`
  line `as may be specified by rules including the particulars of such dutiable goods in respect of which he`
  line `admits short levy on account of misclassification, under-valuation or inapplicability of exemption`
  line `notification ^3[or otherwise] and such application shall be disposed of in the manner hereinafter provided:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such application shall be made unless,--`
  line
  line `^4[(a) the applicant has filed a bill of entry, or a shipping bill, or a bill of export, or made a`
  line `baggage declaration, or a label or declaration accompanying the goods imported or exported through`
  line `post or courier, as the case may be, and in relation to such document or documents, a show cause`
  line `notice has been issued to him by the proper officer;]`
  line
  line `(b) the additional amount of duty accepted by the applicant in his application exceeds three lakh`
  line `rupees; and`
  line
  line `(c) the applicant has paid the additional amount of customs duty accepted by him along with`
  line `interest due under ^5[section 28AA]:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no application shall be entertained by the Settlement Commission under this`
  line `sub-section in cases which are pending in the Appellate Tribunal or any court:`
  line
  line `Provided also that no application under this sub-section shall be made in relation to goods to which`
  line `section 123 applies or to goods in relation to which any offence under the Narcotic Drugs and`
  line `Psychotropic Substances Act, 1985 (61 of 1985) has been committed:`
  line
  line `Provided also that no application under this sub-section shall be made for the interpretation of the`
  line `classification of the goods under the Customs Tariff Act, 1975 (51 of 1975).`
  line
  line `^6* * * * *]`
  line
  line `^7* * * * *`
  line
  line `(3) Every application made under sub-section (1) shall be accompanied by such fees as may be`
  line `specified by rules.`
  line
  line `(4) An application made under sub-section (1) shall not be allowed to be withdrawn by the applicant.`
  line
  line `^8[(5) Any person, other than an applicant referred to in sub-section (1), may also make an application`
  line `to the Settlement Commission in respect of a show cause notice issued to him in a case relating to the`
  line `applicant which has been settled or is pending before the Settlement Commission and such notice is`
  line `pending before an adjudicating authority, in such manner and subject to such conditions, as may be`
  line `specified by rules.]`
obj_root_law_sections_127_b_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 102 (w.e.f. 1-8-1998).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 101, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 1-6-2007).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 14 of 2010, s. 57, for "but excluding the goods not included in the entry made under this Act" (w.e.f. 8-5-2010).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 84, for clause (a) (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 84, for "section 28AB" (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  line
  line `6. Sub-section (1A) omitted by Act 20 of 2015, s. 86 (w.e.f. 14-5-2015).`
  line
  line `7. Sub-section (2) omitted by Act 25 of 2014, s. 84 (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 106 (w.e.f. 31-3-2017).`
obj_root_law_sections_127_c:
  sectionId (31037)
  sectionNo 127C
  orderNo 204
  title `Procedure on receipt of an application under section 127B`
  content obj_root_law_sections_127_c_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_127_c_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31037&sectionno=127C&orderno=204&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_127_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[127C. Procedure on receipt of an application under section 127B.--(1) On receipt of an`
  line `application under section 127B, the Settlement Commission shall, within seven days from the date of`
  line `receipt of the application, issue a notice to the applicant to explain in writing as to why the application`
  line `made by him should be allowed to be proceeded with and after taking into consideration the explanation`
  line `provided by the applicant, the Settlement Commission, shall, within a period of fourteen days from the`
  line `date of the notice, by an order, allow the application to be proceeded with or reject the application, as the`
  line `case may be, and the proceedings before the Settlement Commission shall abate on the date of rejection:`
  line
  line `Provided that where no notice has been issued or no order has been passed within the aforesaid period`
  line `by the Settlement Commission, the application shall be deemed to have been allowed to be proceeded`
  line with.
  line
  line `(2) A copy of every order under sub-section (1) shall be sent to the applicant and to the ^2`
  line [Principal
  line `Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs] having jurisdiction.`
  line
  line `(3) Where an application is allowed or deemed to have been allowed to be proceeded with under`
  line `sub-section (1), the Settlement Commission shall, within seven days from the date of order under`
  line `sub-section (1), call for a report along with the relevant records from the ^2[Principal Commissioner of`
  line `Customs or Commissioner of Customs] having jurisdiction and the Commissioner shall furnish the report`
  line `within a period of thirty days of the receipt of communication from the Settlement Commission:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the Commissioner does not furnish the report within the aforesaid period of`
  line `thirty days, the Settlement Commission shall proceed further in the matter without the report of the`
  line Commissioner.
  line
  line `(4) Where a report of the Commissioner called for under sub-section (3) has been furnished within the`
  line `period specified in that sub-section, the Settlement Commission may, after examination of such report, if`
  line `it is of the opinion that any further enquiry or investigation in the matter is necessary, direct, for reasons`
  line `to be recorded in writing, the Commissioner (Investigation) within fifteen days of the receipt of the`
  line `report, to make or cause to be made such further enquiry or investigation and furnish a report within a`
  line `period of ninety days of the receipt of the communication from the Settlement Commission, on the`
  line `matters covered by the application and any other matter relating to the case:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the Commissioner (Investigation) does not furnish the report within the aforesaid`
  line `period, the Settlement Commission shall proceed to pass an order under sub-section (5) without such`
  line report.
  line
  line `(5) After examination of the records and the report of the 3^[Principal Commissioner of Customs or`
  line `Commissioner of Customs] received under sub-section (3), and the report, if any, of the Commissioner`
  line `(Investigation) of the Settlement Commission under sub-section (4), and after giving an opportunity to the`
  line `applicant and to the 3^[Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs] having`
  line `jurisdiction to be heard, either in person or through a representative duly authorised in this behalf, and`
  line `after examining such further evidence as may be placed before it or obtained by it, the Settlement`
  line `Commission may, in accordance with the provisions of this Act, pass such order as it thinks fit on the`
  line `matters covered by the application and any other matter relating to the case not covered by the`
  line `application, but referred to in the report of the 3^[Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of`
  line `Customs] and Commissioner (Investigation) under sub-section (3) or sub-section (4).`
  line
  line `4^[(5A) The Settlement Commission may, at any time within three months from the date of passing of`
  line `the order under sub-section (5), amend such order to rectify any error apparent on the face of record,`
  line `either suo motu or when such error is brought to its notice by the jurisdictional Principal Commissioner of`
  line `Customs or Commissioner of Customs or the applicant:`
  line
  line `Provided that no amendment which has the effect of enhancing the liability of the applicant shall be`
  line `made under this sub-section, unless the Settlement Commission has given notice of such intention to the`
  line `applicant and the jurisdictional Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs as the`
  line `case may be, and has given them a reasonable opportunity of being heard.]`
  line
  line `5^* * * * *`
  line
  line `(7) Subject to the provisions of section 32A of the Central Excise Act, 1944 (1 of 1944), the`
  line `materials brought on record before the Settlement Commission shall be considered by the Members of the`
  line `concerned Bench before passing any order under sub-section (5) and, in relation to the passing of such`
  line `order, the provisions of section 32D of the Central Excise Act, 1944 shall apply.`
  line
  line `(8) The order passed under sub-section (5) shall provide for the terms of settlement including any`
  line `demand by way of duty, penalty or interest, the manner in which any sums due under the settlement shall`
  line `be paid and all other matters to make the settlement effective and in case of rejection contain the reasons`
  line `therefore and it shall also provide that the settlement shall be void if it is subsequently found by the`
  line `Settlement Commission that it has been obtained by fraud or misrepresentation of facts:`
  line
  line `Provided that the amount of settlement ordered by the Settlement Commission, shall not be less than`
  line `the duty liability admitted by the applicant under section 127B.`
  line
  line `(9) Where any duty, interest, fine and penalty payable in pursuance of an order under sub-section (5)`
  line `is not paid by the applicant within thirty days of receipt of a copy of the order by him, the amount which`
  line `remains unpaid, shall be recovered along with interest due thereon, as the sums due to the Central`
  line `Government by the proper officer having jurisdiction over the applicant in accordance with the provisions`
  line `of section 142.`
  line
  line `(10) Where a settlement becomes void as provided under sub-section (8), the proceedings with`
  line `respect to the matters covered by the settlement shall be deemed to have been revived from the stage at`
  line `which the application was allowed to be proceeded with by the Settlement Commission and the proper`
  line `officer having jurisdiction may, notwithstanding anything contained in any other provision of this Act,`
  line `complete such proceedings at any time before the expiry of two years from the date of the receipt of`
  line `communication that the settlement became void.]`
obj_root_law_sections_127_c_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 102, for "section 127C" (w.e.f. 1-6-2007).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 78, for "Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 78, for "Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 107 (w.e.f. 31-3-2017).`
  line
  line `5. Sub-section (6) omitted by Act 20 of 2015, s. 87 (w.e.f. 14-5-2015).`
obj_root_law_sections_127_d:
  sectionId (31038)
  sectionNo 127D
  orderNo 205
  title `Power of Settlement Commission to order provisional attachment to protect revenue`
  content obj_root_law_sections_127_d_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_127_d_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31038&sectionno=127D&orderno=205&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_127_d_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where, during the pendency of any proceeding before it, the Settlement Commission is of`
  line `the opinion that for the purpose of protecting the interests of the revenue it is necessary so to do, it may,`
  line `by order, attach provisionally any property belonging to the applicant in such manner as may be specified`
  line `by rules.`
  line
  line `(2) Every provisional attachment made by the Settlement Commission under sub-section (1) shall`
  line `cease to have effect from the date the sums due to the Central Government for which such attachment is`
  line `made are discharged by the applicant and evidence to that effect is submitted to the Settlement`
  line Commission.
obj_root_law_sections_127_d_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_127_e:
  sectionId (31039)
  sectionNo 127E
  orderNo 206
  title Omitted..
  content obj_root_law_sections_127_e_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_127_e_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31039&sectionno=127E&orderno=206&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_127_e_content:
  string
  line `[Power of Settlement Commission to reopen completed proceedings.] Omitted by the Finance`
  line `Act, 2015 (20 of 2015), s. 88 (w.e.f. 14-5-2015).`
obj_root_law_sections_127_e_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_127_f:
  sectionId (31040)
  sectionNo 127F
  orderNo 207
  title `Power and procedure of Settlement Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_127_f_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_127_f_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31040&sectionno=127F&orderno=207&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_127_f_content:
  string
  line `(1) In addition to the powers conferred`
  line `on the Settlement Commission under Chapter V of the Central Excise Act, 1944 (1 of 1944), it shall have`
  line `all the powers which are vested in an officer of the customs under this Act or the rules made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an application made under section 127B has been allowed to be proceeded with under`
  line `section 127C, the Settlement Commission shall, until an order is passed under sub-section ^1[(5)] of`
  line `section 127C, have, subject to the provisions of sub-section ^2[(4)] of that section, exclusive jurisdiction to`
  line `exercise the powers and perform the functions of any officer of customs or Central Excise Officer as the`
  line `case may be, under this Act or in the Central Excise Act, 1944 (1 of 1944), as the case may be, in relation`
  line `to the case.`
  line
  line `(3) In the absence of any express direction by the Settlement Commission to the contrary, nothing in`
  line `this Chapter shall affect the operation of the provisions of this Act in so far as they relate to any matter`
  line `other than those before the Settlement Commission.`
  line
  line `(4) The Settlement Commission shall, subject to the provisions of Chapter V of the Central Excise`
  line `Act, 1944 (1 of 1944) and this Chapter, have power to regulate its own procedure and the procedure of`
  line `Benches thereof in all matters arising out of the exercise of its powers, or of the discharge of its functions,`
  line `including the places at which the Benches shall hold their sittings.`
obj_root_law_sections_127_f_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 104, for (7) (w.e.f. 1-6-2007).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 104, ibid., for (6) (w.e.f. 1-6-2007).`
obj_root_law_sections_127_g:
  sectionId (31041)
  sectionNo 127G
  orderNo 208
  title `Inspection, etc., of reports.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_127_g_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_127_g_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31041&sectionno=127G&orderno=208&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_127_g_content:
  string
  line `No person shall be entitled to inspect, or obtain copies of, any`
  line `report made by any officer of the Customs to the Settlement Commission; but the Settlement Commission`
  line `may, in its discretion, furnish copies thereof to any such person on an application made to it in this behalf`
  line `and on payment of such fee as may be specified by rules:`
  line
  line `Provided that, for the purpose of enabling any person whose case is under consideration to rebut any`
  line `evidence brought on record against him in any such report, the Settlement Commission shall, on an`
  line `application made in this behalf, and on payment by such person of such fee as may be specified by rules,`
  line `furnish him with a certified copy of any such report or part thereof relevant for the purpose.`
obj_root_law_sections_127_g_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_127_h:
  sectionId (31042)
  sectionNo 127H
  orderNo 209
  title `Power of Settlement Commission to grant immunity from prosecution and penalty`
  content obj_root_law_sections_127_h_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_127_h_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31042&sectionno=127H&orderno=209&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_127_h_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `The Settlement Commission may, if it is satisfied that any person who made the application for settlement`
  line `under section 127B has co-operated with the Settlement Commission in the proceedings before it and has`
  line `made a full and true disclosure of his duty liability, grant to such person, subject to such conditions as it may think fit to impose, immunity from prosecution for any offence under this Act ^1`
  line `[and also either`
  line `wholly or in part from the imposition of any penalty and fine] under this Act, with respect to the case`
  line `covered by the settlement:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such immunity shall be granted by the Settlement Commission in cases where the`
  line `proceedings for the prosecution for any such offence have been instituted before the date of receipt of the`
  line `application under section 127B.`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
  line `(2) An immunity granted to a person under sub-section (1) shall stand withdrawn if such person fails`
  line `to pay any sum specified in the order of the settlement passed under ^3[sub-section (5) of section 127C`
  line `within the time specified in such order] or fails to comply with any other condition subject to which the`
  line `immunity was granted and thereupon the provisions of this Act shall apply as if such immunity had not`
  line `been granted.`
  line
  line `(3) An immunity granted to a person under sub-section (1) may, at any time, be withdrawn by the`
  line `Settlement Commission, if it is satisfied that such person had, in the course of the settlement proceedings,`
  line `concealed any particulars, material to the settlement or had given false evidence, and thereupon such`
  line `person may be tried for the offence with respect to which the immunity was granted or for any other`
  line `offence of which he appears to have been guilty in connection with the settlement and shall also become`
  line `liable to the imposition of any penalty under this Act to which such person would have been liable, had`
  line `no such immunity been granted.`
obj_root_law_sections_127_h_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 105, for "or under the Indian Penal Code or under any other Central Act for the time being in force`
  line `and also either wholly or in part from the imposition of any penalty, fine and interest" (w.e.f. 1-6-2007).`
  line
  line `2. The Explanation omitted by Act 20 of 2015, s. 89 (w.e.f. 14-5-2015).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 105, for "sub-section (7) of section 127C within the time specified in such order or within such`
  line `further time as may be allowed by the Settlement Commission" (w.e.f. 1-6-2007).`
obj_root_law_sections_127_i:
  sectionId (31043)
  sectionNo 127I
  orderNo 210
  title `Power of Settlement Commission to send a case back to the proper officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_127_i_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_127_i_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31043&sectionno=127I&orderno=210&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_127_i_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `The Settlement Commission may, if it is of opinion that any person who made an application for`
  line `settlement under section 127B has not co-operated with the Settlement Commission in the proceedings`
  line `before it, send the case back to the proper officer who shall thereupon dispose of the case in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of this Act as if no application under section 127B had been made.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose of sub-section (1), the proper officer shall be entitled to use all the materials and`
  line `other information produced by the assessee before the Settlement Commission or the results of the inquiry`
  line `held or evidence recorded by the Settlement Commission in the course of the proceedings before it as if`
  line `such materials, information, inquiry and evidence had been produced before such proper officer or held or`
  line `recorded by him in the course of the proceedings before him.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of the time limit under section 28 and for the purposes of interest under`
  line `section 28AA, in a case referred to in sub-section (1), the period commencing on and from the date of the`
  line `application to the Settlement Commission under section 127B and ending with the date of receipt by the`
  line `officer of customs of the order of the Settlement Commission sending the case back to the officer of`
  line `customs shall be excluded.`
obj_root_law_sections_127_i_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_127_j:
  sectionId (31044)
  sectionNo 127J
  orderNo 211
  title `Order of Settlement to be conclusive.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_127_j_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 106, ibid., for "(7)" (w.e.f. 1-6-2007).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31044&sectionno=127J&orderno=211&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_127_j_content:
  string
  line `Every order of settlement passed under`
  line `sub-section ^1[(5)] of section 127C shall be conclusive as to the matters stated therein and no matter`
  line `covered by such order shall, save as otherwise provided in this Chapter, be reopened in any proceeding`
  line `under this Act or under any other law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_127_k:
  sectionId (31045)
  sectionNo 127K
  orderNo 212
  title `Recovery of sums due under order of settlement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_127_k_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 107, for "(7)" (w.e.f. 1-6-2007).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31045&sectionno=127K&orderno=212&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_127_k_content:
  string
  line `Any sum specified in an order of`
  line `settlement passed under sub-section ^1[(5)] of section 127C may, subject to such conditions, if any, as may`
  line `be specified therein, be recovered, and any penalty for default in making payment of such sum may be`
  line `imposed and recovered as sums due to the Central Government in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `section 142, by the proper officer having jurisdiction over the applicant.`
obj_root_law_sections_127_l:
  sectionId (31046)
  sectionNo 127L
  orderNo 213
  title `Bar on subsequent application for settlement in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_127_l_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_127_l_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31046&sectionno=127L&orderno=213&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_127_l_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] ^2[Where ^3***]`
  line
  line `(i) an order of settlement ^4*** provides for the imposition of a penalty on the applicant under`
  line `section 127B for settlement, on the ground of concealment of particulars of his duty liability; or`
  line
  line `^5[Explanation.--In this clause, the concealment of particulars of duty liability relates to any such`
  line `concealment made from the officer of customs.]`
  line
  line `(ii) after the passing of an order of settlement ^4*** in relation to a case, such person is convicted`
  line `of any offence under this Act in relation to that case; or`
  line
  line `(iii) the case of such person is sent back to the proper officer by the Settlement Commission`
  line `under section 127-I,`
  line
  line `then such person shall not be entitled to apply for settlement under section 127B in relation to any other`
  line matter.
  line
  line `^6* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_127_l_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 127L renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof by s. 108, ibid. (w.e.f. 11-5-2007).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 108, ibid., for "where" (w.e.f. 11-5-2007).`
  line
  line `3. The words, figures and letters "before the 1st day of June, 2007" omitted by Act 14 of 2010, s. 59 (w.e.f. 8-5-2010).`
  line
  line `4. The certain words, brackets, figures and letters omitted by Act 20 of 2015, s. 90 (w.e.f. 14-5-2015).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 85 (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  line
  line `6. Sub-section (2) omitted by 14 of 2010, s. 59 (w.e.f. 8-5-2010).`
obj_root_law_sections_127_m:
  sectionId (31047)
  sectionNo 127M
  orderNo 214
  title `Proceedings before Settlement Commission to be judicial proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_127_m_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_127_m_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31047&sectionno=127M&orderno=214&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_127_m_content:
  string
  line `Any proceedings`
  line `under this Chapter before the Settlement Commission shall be deemed to be a judicial proceeding within`
  line `the meaning of sections 193 and 228, and for the purposes of section 196, of the Indian Penal Code (45 of`
  line `1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_127_m_footnotes:
  string
  line
