obj_root_law_sections_127_n:
  sectionId (31049)
  sectionNo 127N
  orderNo 216
  title `Applications of certain provisions of Central Excise Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_127_n_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_127_n_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31049&sectionno=127N&orderno=216&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_127_n_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of Chapter V of`
  line `the Central Excise Act, 1944 (1 of 1944) in so far as it is not inconsistent with the provisions of this`
  line `Chapter shall apply in relation to proceedings before the Settlement Commission under this Chapter.]`
obj_root_law_sections_127_n_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_128:
  sectionId (31050)
  sectionNo (128)
  orderNo 217
  title `Appeals to Commissioner (Appeals).`
  content obj_root_law_sections_128_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_128_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31050&sectionno=128&orderno=217&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_128_content:
  string
  line `^1[128. Appeals to ^2[Commissioner (Appeals)].--(1) Any person aggrieved by any decision or order`
  line `passed under this Act by an officer of customs lower in rank than a ^3[Principal Commissioner of`
  line `Customs or Commissioner of Customs] may appeal to the ^2[Commissioner (Appeals)] ^4[within sixty`
  line `days] from the date of the communication to him of such decision or order:`
  line
  line `^5@[Provided that the Commissioner (Appeals) may, if he is satisfied that the appellant was prevented`
  line `by sufficient cause from presenting the appeal within the aforesaid period of sixty days, allow it to be`
  line `presented within a further period of thirty days.]`
  line
  line `6^[(1A) The Commissioner (Appeals) may, if sufficient cause is shown at any stage of hearing of an`
  line `appeal, grant time, from time to time, to the parties or any of them and adjourn the hearing of the appeal`
  line `for reasons to be recorded in writing:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such adjournment shall be granted more than three times to a party during hearing of`
  line `the appeal.]`
  line
  line `(2) Every appeal under this section shall be in such form and shall be verified in such manner as may`
  line `be specified by rules made in this behalf.]`
obj_root_law_sections_128_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 44 of 1980, s. 50 and The Fifth Schedule, for Chapter XV (w.e.f. 11-10-1982).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 50, for "Collector (Appeals)" (w.e.f. 26-5-1995).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 78, for "Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 109, for "within three months" (w.e.f. 11-5-2001).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 109, ibid., for the proviso (w.e.f. 11-5-2001).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 68 (w.e.f. 10-9-2004).`
obj_root_law_sections_128_a:
  sectionId (31051)
  sectionNo 128A
  orderNo 218
  title `Procedure in appeal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_128_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_128_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31051&sectionno=128A&orderno=218&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_128_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[128A. Procedure in appeal.--(1) The ^2[Commissioner (Appeals)] shall give an opportunity to the`
  line `appellant to be heard if he so desires.`
  line
  line `(2) The ^2[Commissioner (Appeals)] may, at the hearing of an appeal, allow the appellant to go into`
  line `any ground of appeal not specified in the grounds of appeal, if the ^2[Commissioner (Appeals)] is satisfied`
  line `that the omission of that ground from the grounds of appeal was not wilful or unreasonable.`
  line
  line `(3) ^3[The Commissioner (Appeals)] shall, after making such further inquiry as may be necessary, pass`
  line `pass such order, as he thinks ^4[just and proper,--`
  line
  line `(a) confirming, modifying or annulling the decision or order appealed against; or`
  line
  line `(b) referring the matter back to the adjudicating authority with directions for fresh adjudication or`
  line `decision, as the case may be, in the following cases, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) where an order or decision has been passed without following the principles of natural`
  line `justice; or`
  line
  line `(ii) where no order or decision has been passed after re-assessment under section 17; or`
  line
  line `(iii) where an order of refund under section 27 has been issued by crediting the amount to`
  line `Fund without recording any finding on the evidence produced by the applicant]:]`
  line
  line `Provided that an order enhancing any penalty or fine in lieu of confiscation or confiscating goods of`
  line `greater value or reducing the amount of refund shall not be passed unless the appellant has been given a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of showing cause against the proposed order:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where the ^2[Commissioner (Appeals)] is of opinion that any duty has not been`
  line `levied or has been short-levied or erroneously refunded, no order requiring the appellant to pay any duty`
  line `not levied, short-levied or erroneously refunded shall be passed unless the appellant is given notice within`
  line `the time-limit specified in section 28 to show cause against the proposed order.`
  line
  line `(4) The order of the ^2[Commissioner (Appeals)] disposing of the appeal shall be in writing and shall`
  line `state the points for determination, the decision thereon and the reasons for the decision.`
  line
  line `^5[(4A) The Commissioner (Appeals) shall, where it is possible to do so, hear and decide every appeal`
  line `within a period of six months from the date on which it is filed.]`
  line
  line `(5) On the disposal of the appeal, the ^2[Commissioner (Appeals)] shall communicate the order passed`
  line `by him to the appellant, the adjudicating authority ^6[, the ^7[Principal Chief Commissioner of Customs or`
  line `Chief Commissioner of Customs] and the ^8[Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of`
  line Customs]].
obj_root_law_sections_128_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 44 of 1980, s. 50 and The Fifth Schedule, for Chapter XV (w.e.f. 11-10-1982).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 50, for "Collector (Appeals)" (w.e.f. 26-5-1995).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 110, for certain words and brackets (w.e.f. 11-5-2001).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 96, for "just and proper, confirming, modifying or annulling the decision or order appealed`
  line `against" (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 110 (w.e.f. 11-5-2001).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 69, for "and the Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 13-5-2005).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 78, for "Chief Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by s. 78, ibid., for "Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_129:
  sectionId (31052)
  sectionNo (129)
  orderNo 219
  title `Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_129_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31052&sectionno=129&orderno=219&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_129_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall constitute an Appellate Tribunal to be`
  line `called the Customs, Excise and ^1[Service Tax] Appellate Tribunal consisting of as many judicial and`
  line `technical members as it thinks fit to exercise the powers and discharge the functions conferred on the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal by this Act.`
  line
  line `^2[(2) A judicial member shall be a person who has for at least ten years held a judicial office in the`
  line `territory of India or who has been a member of the ^3[Indian Legal Service] and has held a post in Grade I`
  line `of that service or any equivalent or higher post for at least three years, or who has been an advocate for at`
  line `least ten years.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section,--`
  line
  line `(i) in computing the period during which a person has held judicial office in the territory of India,`
  line `there shall be included any period, after he has held any judicial office, during which the person has`
  line `been an advocate or has held the office of a member of a tribunal or any post, under the Union or a`
  line `State, requiring special knowledge of law;`
  line
  line `(ii) in computing the period during which a person has been an advocate, there shall be included`
  line `any period during which the person has held a judicial office, or the office of a member of a tribunal`
  line `or any post, under the Union or a State, requiring special knowledge of law after he became an`
  line advocate.]
  line
  line `(2A) A technical member shall be a person who has been a member of the Indian Customs and`
  line `Central Excise Service, Group A, and has held the post of ^4[Principal Commissioner of Customs or`
  line `Commissioner of Customs] or Central Excise or any equivalent or higher post for at least three years.]`
  line
  line `^5[(3) The Central Government shall appoint--`
  line
  line `(a) a person who is or has been a Judge of a High Court; or`
  line
  line `(b) one of the members of the Appellate Tribunal,`
  line
  line `to be the President thereof.]`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government may appoint one or more members of the Appellate Tribunal to be the`
  line `Vice-President, or, as the case may be, Vice-Presidents, thereof.`
  line
  line `^6* * * * *`
  line
  line `(5)`
  line `^7[A Vice-President] shall exercise such of the powers and perform such of the functions of the`
  line `President as may be delegated to him by the President by a general or special order in writing.`
  line
  line `^8[(6) On ceasing to hold office, the President, Vice-President or other Member shall not be entitled to`
  line `appear, act or plead before the Appellate Tribunal.]`
  line
  line `^9[(7) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, the qualifications, appointment, term of office,`
  line `salaries and allowances, resignation, removal and the other terms and conditions of service of the`
  line `President, Vice-President or other Members of the Appellate Tribunal appointed after the commencement`
  line `of ^10[the Tribunal Reforms Act, 2021, shall be governed by the provisions of Chapter II of the said Act]:`
  line
  line `Provided that the President. Vice-President and Member appointed before the commencement of Part`
  line `XIV of Chapter VI of the Finance Act, 2017 (7 of 2017), shall continue to be governed by the provisions`
  line `of this Act, and the rules made thereunder as if the provisions of section 184 of the Finance Act, 2017 had`
  line `not come into force.]`
obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 119, for Gold (Control) (w.e.f. 14-5-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 21 of 1984, s. 39, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 11-5-1984).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 119, for Central Legal Service (w.e.f. 14-5-2003).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 78, for Commissioner of Customs (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 33 of 1996, s. 65, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 28-9-1996).`
  line
  line `6. Sub-section (4A) omitted by Act 32 of 2003, s. 119 (w.e.f. 14-5-2003).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by s. 119, ibid., for The Senior Vice-President or a Vice-President (w.e.f. 14-5--2003).`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 110 (w.e.f. 11-5-2007).`
  line
  line `9. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 175 (w.e.f. 26-5-2017) vide Notification S. O. No. 1696(E), dated (26-5-2017).`
  line
  line `10. Subs. by Act 33 of 2021, s. 12, for “Part XIV of Chapter VI of the Finance Act, 2017 (7 of 2017), shall be governed by the provisions of section 184 of that Act” (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_129_a:
  sectionId (31053)
  sectionNo 129A
  orderNo 220
  title `Appeals to the Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_129_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_129_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31053&sectionno=129A&orderno=220&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_129_a_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved by any of the following`
  line `orders may appeal to the Appellate Tribunal against such order--`
  line
  line `(a) a decision or order passed by the ^1[Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of`
  line `Customs] as an adjudicating authority;`
  line
  line `(b) an order passed by the ^2[Commissioner (Appeals)] under section 128A;`
  line
  line `(c) an order passed by the Board or the Appellate ^3[Commissioner of Customs] under Section`
  line `128, as it stood immediately before the appointed day;`
  line
  line `(d) an order passed by the Board or the ^1[Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner`
  line `of Customs], either before or after the appointed day, under section 130, as it stood immediately`
  line `before that day:`
  line
  line `^4[Provided that no appeal shall lie to the Appellate Tribunal and the Appellate Tribunal shall not have`
  line `have jurisdiction to decide any appeal in respect of any order referred to in clause (b) if such order relates`
  line to,--
  line
  line `(a) any goods imported or exported as baggage;`
  line
  line `(b) any goods loaded in a conveyance for importation into India, but which are not unloaded at`
  line `their place of destination in India, or so much of the quantity of such goods as has not been unloaded`
  line `at any such destination if goods unloaded at such destination are short of the quantity required to be`
  line `unloaded at that destination;`
  line
  line `(c) payment of drawback as provided in Chapter X, and the rules made thereunder:`
  line
  line `Provided further that] the Appellate Tribunal may, in its discretion, refuse to admit an appeal in`
  line `respect of an order referred to in clause (b) or clause (c) or clause (d) where--`
  line
  line `(i) the value of the goods confiscated without option having been given to the owner of the goods`
  line `to pay a fine in lieu of confiscation under section 125; or`
  line
  line `(ii) in any disputed case, other than a case where the determination of any question having a`
  line `relation to the rate of duty of customs or to the value of goods for purposes of assessment is in issue`
  line `or is one of the points in issue, the difference in duty involved or the duty involved; or`
  line
  line `(iii) the amount of fine or penalty determined by such order,`
  line
  line `does not exceed ^5[two lakh rupees].`
  line
  line `^6[(1A) Every appeal against any order of the nature referred to in the first proviso to sub-section (1),`
  line `which is pending immediately before the commencement of section 40 of the Finance Act, 1984`
  line `(21 of 1984), before the Appellate Tribunal and any matter arising out of or connected with such appeal`
  line `and which is so pending shall stand transferred on such commencement to the Central Government and`
  line `the Central Government shall deal with such appeal or matter under section 129DD as if such appeal or`
  line `matter were an application or a matter arising out of an application made to it under that section.]`
  line
  line `^7[(1B) (i) The Board may, ^8[by order], constitute such Committees as may be necessary for the`
  line `purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(ii) Every Committee constituted under clause (i) shall consist of two Chief Commissioners of`
  line `Customs or two Commissioners of Customs, as the case may be.]`
  line
  line `(2)`
  line `^9[The Committee of Commissioners of Customs may, if it is] of opinion that an order passed by`
  line `the Appellate ^10[Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs] under section 128, as`
  line `it stood immediately before the appointed day, or by the ^11[Commissioner (Appeals)] under section 128A,`
  line `is not legal or proper, direct the proper officer to appeal ^12[on its behalf] to the Appellate Tribunal against`
  line `such order:`
  line
  line `^13[Provided that where the Committee of ^10[Principal Commissioners of Customs or Commissioners of`
  line `Customs] differs in its opinion regarding the appeal against the order of the Commissioner (Appeals), it`
  line `shall state the point or points on which it differs and make a reference to the jurisdictional ^14[Principal`
  line `Chief Commissioner of Customs or Chief Commissioner of Customs] who shall, after considering the`
  line `facts of the order, if is of the opinion that the order passed by the Commissioner (Appeals) is not legal or`
  line `proper, direct the proper officer to appeal to the Appellate Tribunal against such order.`
  line
  line `Explanation@-i@.--For the purposes of this sub-section, "jurisdictional Chief Commissioner" means`
  line `the ^14[Principal Chief Commissioner of Customs or Chief Commissioner of Customs] having jurisdiction`
  line `over the adjudicating authority in the matter.]`
  line
  line `(3) Every appeal under this section shall be filed within three months from the date on which the`
  line `order sought to be appealed against is communicated to the ^10[Principal Commissioner of Customs or`
  line `Commissioner of Customs], or as the case may be, the other party preferring the appeal.`
  line
  line `(4) On receipt of notice that an appeal has been preferred under this section, the party against whom`
  line `the appeal has been preferred may, notwithstanding that he may not have appealed against such order or`
  line `any part thereof, file, within forty-five days of the receipt of the notice, a memorandum of crossobjections verified in such manner as may be specified by rules made in this behalf against any part of the`
  line `order appealed against and such memorandum shall be disposed of by the Appellate Tribunal as if it were`
  line `an appeal presented within the time specified in sub-section (3).`
  line
  line `(5) The Appellate Tribunal may admit an appeal or permit the filing of a memorandum of crossobjections after the expiry of the relevant period referred to in sub-section (3) or sub-section (4), if it is`
  line `satisfied that there was sufficient cause for not presenting it within that period.`
  line
  line `^15[(6) An appeal to the Appellate Tribunal shall be in such form and shall be verified in such manner`
  line `as may be specified by rules made in this behalf and shall, irrespective of the date of demand of duty and`
  line `interest or of levy of penalty in relation to which the appeal is made, be accompanied by a fee of,--`
  line
  line `(a) where the amount of duty and interest demanded and penalty levied by any officer of customs`
  line `in the case to which the appeal relates is five lakh rupees or less, one thousand rupees;`
  line
  line `(b) where the amount of duty and interest demanded and penalty levied by any officer of customs`
  line `in the case to which the appeal relates is more than five lakh rupees but not exceeding fifty lakh`
  line `rupees, five thousand rupees;`
  line
  line `(c) where the amount of duty and interest demanded and penalty levied by any officer of customs`
  line `in the case to which the appeal relates is more than fifty lakh rupees, ten thousand rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such fee shall be payable in the case of an appeal referred to in sub-section (2) or a`
  line `memorandum of cross-objections referred to in sub-section (4).`
  line
  line `(7) Every application made before the Appellate Tribunal,--`
  line
  line `(a) in an appeal ^16*** for rectification of mistake or for any other purpose; or`
  line
  line `(b) for restoration of an appeal or an application,`
  line
  line `shall be accompanied by a fee of five hundred rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such fee shall be payable in the case of an application filed by or on behalf of`
  line `the ^17[Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs] under this sub-section.]`
obj_root_law_sections_129_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 78, for "Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 50, for "Collector (Appeals)" (w.e.f. 26-5-1995).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 50, ibid., for "Collector of Customs" (w.e.f. 26-5-1995).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 21 of 1984, s. 40, for "Provided that" (w.e.f. 11-5-1984).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 86, for "fifty thousand rupees" (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 21 of 1984, s. 40 (w.e.f. 11-5-1984).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 70 (w.e.f. 13-5-2005).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 86, for "by notification in the Official Gazette" (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 70, for "The Commissioner of Customs may, if he is" (w.e.f. 13-5-2005).`
  line
  line `10. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 78, for "Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  line
  line `11. Subs. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 50, for "Collector (Appeals)" (w.e.f. 26-5-1995).`
  line
  line `12. Subs. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 70, for "on his behalf" (w.e.f. 13-5-2005).`
  line
  line `13. The proviso ins. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 71 (w.e.f. 10-5-2008).`
  line
  line `14. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 78, for "Chief Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  line
  line `15. Subs. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 69 for sub section (6) (w.e.f. 1-11-2004) vide Notification No. 120/2004-Cus. (N. T.), dated 25-10-`
  line 2004.
  line
  line `16. The words "for grant of stay or" omitted by Act 25 of 2014, s. 86 (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  line
  line `17. Subs. by s. 78, ibid., for "Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_129_b:
  sectionId (31054)
  sectionNo 129B
  orderNo 221
  title `Orders of Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_129_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_129_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31054&sectionno=129B&orderno=221&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_129_b_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Appellate Tribunal may, after giving the parties to`
  line `the appeal, an opportunity of being heard, pass such orders thereon as it thinks fit, confirming, modifying`
  line `or annulling the decision or order appealed against or may refer the case back to the authority which`
  line `passed such decision or order with such directions as the Appellate Tribunal may think fit, for a fresh`
  line `adjudication or decision, as the case may be, after taking additional evidence, if necessary.`
  line
  line `^2[(1A) The Appellate Tribunal may, if sufficient cause is shown, at any stage of hearing of an appeal,`
  line `grant time to the parties or any of them and adjourn the hearing of the appeal for reasons to be recorded`
  line `in writing:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such adjournment shall be granted more than three times to a party during hearing`
  line `of the appeal.]`
  line
  line `(2) The Appellate Tribunal may, at any time within ^3[six months] from the date of the order, with a`
  line `view to rectifying any mistake apparent from the record, amend any order passed by it under`
  line `sub-section (1) and shall make such amendments if the mistake is brought to its notice by the ^1[Principal`
  line `Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs] or the other party to the appeal:`
  line
  line `Provided that an amendment which has the effect of enhancing the assessment or reducing a refund or`
  line `otherwise increasing the liability of the other party shall not be made under this sub-section, unless the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal has given notice to him of its intention to do so and has allowed him a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `^4[(2A) The Appellate Tribunal shall, where it is possible to do so, hear and decide every appeal within`
  line `within a period of three years from the date on which such appeal is filed:`
  line
  line `^5* * * * *]`
  line
  line `(3) The Appellate Tribunal shall send a copy of every order passed under this section to`
  line `the ^1[Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs] and the other party to the appeal.`
  line
  line `(4) Save as otherwise provided in section 130 or section 130E, orders passed by the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal on appeal shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_129_b_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 78, ibid., for "Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 70 (w.e.f. 10-9-2004).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 20 of 2002, s, 127, for "four years" (w.e.f. 11-5-2002).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by s. 127, ibid. (w.e.f. 11-5-2002).`
  line
  line `5. The first, second and third provisos omitted by Act 25 of 2014, s. 87 (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_129_c:
  sectionId (31055)
  sectionNo 129C
  orderNo 222
  title `Procedure of Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_129_c_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_129_c_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31055&sectionno=129C&orderno=222&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_129_c_content:
  string
  line `(1) The powers and functions of the Appellate Tribunal`
  line `may be exercised and discharged by Benches constituted by the President from amongst the members`
  line thereof.
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions contained in ^1`
  line `[sub-section (4)], a Bench shall consist of one judicial`
  line `member and one technical member.`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
  line
  line `(4) The President or any other member of the Appellate Tribunal authorised in this behalf by the`
  line `President may, sitting singly, dispose of any case which has been allotted to the Bench of which he is a`
  line `member where--`
  line
  line `(a) the value of the goods confiscated without option having been given to the owner of the goods`
  line `to pay a fine in lieu of confiscation under section 125; or`
  line
  line `(b) in any disputed case, other than a case where the determination of any question having a`
  line `relation to the rate of duty of customs or to the value of goods for purposes of assessment is in issue`
  line `or is one of the points in issue, the difference in duty involved or the duty involved; or`
  line
  line `(c) the amount of fine or penalty involved,`
  line
  line `does not exceed ^3`
  line `[fifty lakh rupees].`
  line
  line ^4
  line `[(5) If the members of a Bench differ in opinion on any point, the point shall be decided according to`
  line `to the opinion of the majority, if there is a majority; but if the members are equally divided, they shall`
  line `state the point or points on which they differ and make a reference to the President who shall either hear`
  line `the point or points himself or refer the case for hearing on such point or points by one or more of the other`
  line `members of the Appellate Tribunal and such point or points shall be decided according to the opinion of`
  line `the majority of these members of the Appellate Tribunal who have heard the case, including those who`
  line `first heard it.]`
  line
  line `(6) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Appellate Tribunal shall have power to regulate its own`
  line `procedure and the procedure of the Benches thereof in all matters arising out of the exercise of its powers`
  line `or of the discharge of its functions, including the places at which the Benches shall hold their sittings.`
  line
  line `(7) The Appellate Tribunal shall, for the purposes of discharging its functions, have the same powers`
  line `as are vested in a court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), when trying a suit in respect`
  line `of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) discovery and inspection;`
  line
  line `(b) enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(c) compelling the production of books of account and other documents; and`
  line
  line `(d) issuing commissions.`
  line
  line `(8) Any proceeding before the Appellate Tribunal shall be deemed to be a judicial proceeding within`
  line `the meaning of sections 193 and 228 and for the purpose of section 196 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of`
  line `1860), and the Appellate Tribunal shall be deemed to be a Civil Court for all the purposes of section 195`
  line `and Chapter XXVI of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_129_c_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 65, for sub-sections (3) and (4) (w.e.f. 26-5-1995).`
  line
  line `2. Sub-section (3) omitted by s. 65, ibid. (w.e.f. 26-5-1995).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 77, for "ten lakh rupees" (w.e.f. 10-5-2013).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 12 of 1990, s. 62, for sub-section (5) (w.e.f. 31-5-1990).`
obj_root_law_sections_129_d:
  sectionId (31056)
  sectionNo 129D
  orderNo 223
  title `Powers of Committee of Principal Chief Commissioner of Customs or Chief Commissioner of Customs or Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs to pass certain orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_129_d_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_129_d_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31056&sectionno=129D&orderno=223&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_129_d_content:
  string
  line `129D. Powers of ^1[Committee of ^2[Principal Chief Commissioner of Customs or Chief`
  line `Commissioner of Customs]] or ^3[Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs]`
  line `Customs] to pass certain orders.--(1) The ^1[Committee of ^2[Principal Chief Commissioner of Customs`
  line `or Chief Commissioner of Customs]] may, of its own motion, call for and examine the record of any`
  line `proceeding in which a ^3[Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs] as an`
  line `adjudicating authority has passed any decision or order under this Act for the purpose of satisfying itself`
  line `as to the legality or propriety of any such decision or order and may, by order, direct`
  line `such ^4[Commissioner] ^5[or any other Commissioner] to apply to the Appellate Tribunal for the`
  line `determination of such points arising out of the decision or order as may be specified by the ^1[Committee`
  line `of ^2[Principal Chief Commissioners of Customs or Chief Commissioners of Customs]] in its order:`
  line
  line `^6[Provided that where the Committee of ^7[Principal Chief Commissioners of Customs or Chief`
  line `Commissioner of Customs] differs in its opinion as to the legality or propriety of the decision or order of`
  line `the ^8[Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs], it shall state the point or points`
  line `on which it differs and make a reference to the Board which, after considering the facts of the decision or`
  line `order passed by the ^8[Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs], if is of the`
  line `opinion that the decision or order passed by the ^8[Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner`
  line `of Customs] is not legal or proper, may, by order, direct such Commissioner or any other Commissioner`
  line `to apply to the Appellate Tribunal for the determination of such points arising out of the decision or order,`
  line `as may be specified in its order.]`
  line
  line `(2) The ^8[Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs] may, of his own motion,`
  line `call for and examine the record of any proceeding in which an adjudicating authority subordinate to him`
  line `has passed any decision or order under this Act for the purpose of satisfying himself as to the legality or`
  line `propriety of any such decision or order and may, by order, direct ^9[such authority or any officer of`
  line `Customs subordinate to him] to apply to the ^10[Commissioner (Appeals)] for the determination of such`
  line `points arising out of the decision or order as may be specified by the ^8[Principal Commissioner of`
  line `Customs or Commissioner of Customs] in his order.`
  line
  line `^11[(3) Every order under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), as the case may be, shall be made within a`
  line `period of three months from the date of communication of the decision or order of the adjudicating`
  line authority.]
  line
  line `^12[Provided that the Board may, on sufficient cause being shown, extend the said period by another`
  line `thirty days.]`
  line
  line `(4) Where in pursuance of an order under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), the adjudicating authority`
  line `or any officer of customs authorised in this behalf by the ^8[Principal Commissioner of Customs or`
  line `Commissioner of Customs], makes an application to the Appellate Tribunal or the ^10[Commissioner`
  line `(Appeals)] within a period of ^13[one month] from the date of communication of the order under`
  line `sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) to the adjudicating authority, such application shall be heard by the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal or the ^10`
  line `[Commissioner (Appeals)], as the case may be, as if such application were an`
  line `appeal made against the decision or order of the adjudicating authority and the provisions of this Act`
  line `regarding appeals, including the provisions of sub-section (4) of section 129A shall, so far as may be,`
  line `apply to such application.`
  line
  line `^14[(5) The provisions of this section shall not apply to any decision or order in which the determination`
  line `determination of any question having a relation to the rate of duty or to the value of goods for the`
  line `purposes of assessment of any duty is in issue or is one of the points in issue.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, the determination of a rate or duty in relation to`
  line `any goods or valuation of any goods for the purposes of assessment of duty includes the determination of`
  line `a question--`
  line
  line `(a) relating to the rate of duty for the time being in force, whether under the Customs Tariff Act,`
  line `1975 (51 of 1975) or under any other Central Act providing for the levy and collection of any duty of`
  line `customs in relation to any goods on or after the 28th day of February, 1986; or`
  line
  line `(b) relating to the value of goods for the purposes of assessment of any duty in cases where the`
  line `assessment is made on or after the 28th day of February, 1986; or`
  line
  line `(c) whether any goods fall under a particular heading or sub-heading of the First Schedule or the`
  line `Second Schedule to the Customs Tariff Act, 1975 (51 of 1975), or that any goods are or not covered`
  line `by a particular notification or order issued by the Central Government granting total or partial`
  line `exemption from duty; or`
  line
  line `(d) whether the value of any goods for the purposes of assessment of duty shall be enhanced or`
  line `reduced by the addition or reduction of the amounts in respect of such matters as are specifically`
  line `provided in this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_129_d_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 71, for Board (w.e.f. 13-5-2005).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by 25 of 2014, s. 78, for Chief Commissioner of Customs (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 78, ibid., for Commissioner of Customs (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 50, for Collector (w.e.f. 26-5-1995).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 111 (w.e.f. 11-5-2001).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 72 (w.e.f. 10-5-2008).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 78, for "Chief Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by s. 78, ibid., for "Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by Act 29 of 2006, s. 29, for "such authority" (w.e.f. 13-7-2006).`
  line
  line `10. Subs. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 50, for "Collector (Appeals)" (w.e.f. 26-5-1995).`
  line
  line `11. Subs. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 72, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 10-5-2008).`
  line
  line `12. Ins. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 88 (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  line
  line `13. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 111, for "three month" (w.e.f. 11-5-2007).`
  line
  line `14. Ins. by Act 29 of 1988, s. 4 (w.e.f. 18-5-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_129_da:
  sectionId (31057)
  sectionNo 129DA
  orderNo 224
  title `Powers of revision of Board or Collector of Customs in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_129_da_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 1988, s. 5 (w.e.f. 18-5-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31057&sectionno=129DA&orderno=224&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_129_da_content:
  string
  line `^1[129DA. Powers of revision of Board or Collector of Customs in certain cases.--(1) The Board`
  line `may, of its own motion or on the application of any aggrieved person or otherwise, call for and examine`
  line `the record of any proceeding in which a Collector of Customs has passed any decision or order not being`
  line `a decision or order passed under sub-section (2) of this section of the nature referred to in sub-section (5)`
  line `of section 129D for the purpose of satisfying itself as to the correctness, legality or propriety of such`
  line `decision or order and may pass such order thereon as it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(2) The Collector of Customs may, of his own motion or on the application of any aggrieved person`
  line `or otherwise, call for and examine the record of any proceeding in which an adjudicating authority`
  line `subordinate to him has passed any decision or order of the nature referred to in sub-section (5) of section`
  line `129D for the purpose of satisfying himself as to the correctness, legality or propriety of such decision or`
  line `order and may pass such order thereon as he thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(3) (a) No decision or order under this section shall be made so as to prejudicially affect any person`
  line `unless such person is given a reasonable opportunity of making representation and if, he so desires, of`
  line `being heard in his defence.`
  line
  line `(b) Where the Board or, as the case may be, the Collector of Customs is of the opinion that any duty`
  line `has not been levied or has been short-levied or short-paid or erroneously refunded, no order requiring the`
  line `affected person to pay any duty not levied or paid, short-levied or short-paid or erroneously refunded shall`
  line `be passed under this section unless such person is given notice within the time limit specified in section`
  line `28 to show cause against the proposed order.`
  line
  line `(4) No proceeding shall be initiated under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) in respect of any decision`
  line `or order after the expiry of a period of six months from the date of communication of such decision or`
  line `order:`
  line
  line `Provided that in respect of any decision or order passed before the commencement of the Customs`
  line `and Central Excises Laws (Amendment) Act, 1988 (29 of 1988), the provisions of this sub-section shall`
  line `have effect as if for the words "six month"s, the words "one year" were substituted.`
  line
  line `(5) Any person aggrieved by any decision or order passed under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2)`
  line `may appeal to the Customs and Excise Revenues Appellate Tribunal established under section 3 of the`
  line `Customs and Excise Revenues Appellate Tribunal Act, 1986 (62 of 1986), against such decision or`
  line order.
obj_root_law_sections_129_dd:
  sectionId (31058)
  sectionNo 129DD
  orderNo 225
  title `Revision by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_129_dd_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_129_dd_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31058&sectionno=129DD&orderno=225&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_129_dd_content:
  string
  line `^1[129DD. Revision by Central Government.--(1) The Central Government may, on the application`
  line `of any person aggrieved by any order passed under section 128A, where the order is of the nature referred`
  line `to in the first proviso to sub-section (1) of section 129A, annul or modify such order.`
  line `^2[Provided that the Central Government may in its discretion, refuse to admit an application in respect`
  line `respect of an order where the amount of duty or fine or penalty, determined by such order does not exceed`
  line `five thousand rupees.]`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, "order passed under section 128A" includes an`
  line `order passed under that section before the commencement of section 40 of the Finance Act, 1984`
  line `(21 of 1984), against which an appeal has not been preferred before such commencement and could have`
  line `been, if the said section had not come into force, preferred after such commencement, to the Appellate`
  line Tribunal.
  line
  line ^3
  line `[(1A) The ^4`
  line `[Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs] may, if he is of the`
  line `opinion that an order passed by the Commissioner (Appeals) under section 128A is not legal or proper,`
  line `direct the proper officer to make an application on his behalf to the Central Government for revision of`
  line `such order.]`
  line
  line `(2) An application under sub-section (1) shall be made within three months from the date of the`
  line `communication to the applicant of the order against which the application is being made:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, if it is satisfied that the applicant was prevented by`
  line `sufficient cause from presenting the application within the aforesaid period of three months, allow it to be`
  line `presented within a further period of three months.`
  line
  line ^5
  line `[(3) An application under sub-section (1) shall be in such form and shall be verified in such manner`
  line `as may be specified by rules made in this behalf and shall be accompanied by a fee of,--`
  line
  line `(a) two hundred rupees, where the amount of duty and interest demanded, fine or penalty levied`
  line `by an officer of customs in the case to which the application relates is one lakh rupees or less;`
  line
  line `(b) one thousand rupees, where the amount of duty and interest demanded, fine or penalty levied`
  line `by an officer of customs in the case to which the application relates is more than one lakh rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such fee shall be payable in the case of an application referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1A).]`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government may, of its own motion, annul or modify any order referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(5) No order enhancing any penalty or fine in lieu of confiscation or confiscating goods of greater`
  line `value shall be passed under this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) in any case in which an order passed under section 128A has enhanced any penalty or fine in`
  line `lieu of confiscation or has confiscated goods of greater value, and`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, unless the person affected by the proposed order has been given notice to`
  line `show cause against it within one year from the date of the order sought to be annulled or modified.`
  line
  line `(6) Where the Central Government is of opinion that any duty of customs has not been levied or has`
  line `been short-levied, no order levying or enhancing the duty shall be made under this section unless the`
  line `person affected by the proposed order is given notice to show cause against it within the time limit`
  line `specified in section 28.]`
obj_root_law_sections_129_dd_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1984, s. 43 (w.e.f. 11-5-1984).`
  line
  line `2. The proviso ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 110 (w.e.f. 11-5-1999).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 110 (w.e.f. 11-5-1999).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 78, for "Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 110, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 11-5-1999).`
obj_root_law_sections_129_e:
  sectionId (31059)
  sectionNo 129E
  orderNo 226
  title `Deposit of certain percentage of duty demanded or penalty imposed before filing appeal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_129_e_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_129_e_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31059&sectionno=129E&orderno=226&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_129_e_content:
  string
  line `^2[129E. Deposit of certain percentage of duty demanded or penalty imposed before filing`
  line `appeal.--The Tribunal or the Commissioner (Appeals), as the case may be, shall not entertain any`
  line appeal,--
  line
  line `(i) under sub-section (1) of section 128, unless the appellant has deposited seven and a half per`
  line `cent. of the duty, in case where duty or duty and penalty are in dispute, or penalty, where such penalty`
  line `is in dispute, in pursuance of a decision or an order passed by an officer of customs lower in rank than`
  line `the ^1`
  line `[Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs];`
  line
  line `(ii) against the decision or order referred to in clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 129A,`
  line `unless the appellant has deposited seven and a half per cent. of the duty, in case where duty or duty`
  line `and penalty are in dispute, or penalty, where such penalty is in dispute, in pursuance of the decision`
  line `or order appealed against;`
  line
  line `(iii) against the decision or order referred to in clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 129A,`
  line `unless the appellant has deposited ten per cent. of the duty, in case where duty or duty and penalty are`
  line `in dispute, or penalty, where such penalty is in dispute, in pursuance of the decision or order appealed`
  line `against:`
  line
  line `Provided that the amount required to be deposited under this section shall not exceed rupees ten`
  line `rores:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the provisions of this section shall not apply to the stay applications and appeals`
  line `pending before any appellate authority prior to the commencement of the Finance (No. 2) Act, 2014`
  line `(25 of 2014).]`
obj_root_law_sections_129_e_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 78, for "Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 89, for section 129E (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_129_ee:
  sectionId (31060)
  sectionNo 129EE
  orderNo 227
  title `Interest on delayed refund of amount deposited under section 129E.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_129_ee_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 90, for section 129EE (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31060&sectionno=129EE&orderno=227&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_129_ee_content:
  string
  line `^1[129EE. Interest on delayed refund of amount deposited under section 129E.--Where an`
  line `amount deposited by the appellant under section 129E is required to be refunded consequent upon the`
  line `order of the appellate authority, there shall be paid to the appellant interest at such rate, not below five per`
  line `cent. and not exceeding thirty-six per cent. per annum as is for the time being fixed by the Central`
  line `Government, by notification in the Official Gazette, on such amount from the date of payment of the`
  line `amount till, the date of refund of such amount:`
  line
  line `Provided that the amount deposited under section 129E, prior to the commencement of the Finance`
  line `(No. 2) Act, 2014 (25 of 2014), shall continue to be governed by the provisions of section 129EE as it`
  line `stood before the commencement of the said Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_130:
  sectionId (31061)
  sectionNo (130)
  orderNo 228
  title `Appeal to High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_130_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_130_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31061&sectionno=130&orderno=228&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_130_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[130. Appeal to High Court.--(1) An appeal shall lie to the High Court from every order passed in`
  line `appeal by the Appellate Tribunal on or after the 1st day of July, 2003 (not being an order relating, among`
  line `other things, to the determination of any question having a relation to the rate of duty of customs or to the`
  line `value of goods for the purposes of assessment), if the High Court is satisfied that the case involves a`
  line `substantial question of law.`
  line
  line `(2) The ^2`
  line `[Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs] or the other party`
  line `aggrieved by any order passed by the Appellate Tribunal may file an appeal to the High Court and such`
  line `appeal under this sub-section shall be--`
  line
  line `(a) filed within one hundred and eighty days from the date on which the order appealed against is`
  line `received by the ^2`
  line `[Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs] or the other`
  line party;
  line
  line `(b) accompanied by a fee of two hundred rupees where such appeal is filed by the other party;`
  line
  line `(c) in the form of a memorandum of appeal precisely stating therein the substantial question of`
  line `law involved.`
  line
  line ^3
  line `[(2A) The High Court may admit an appeal after the expiry of the period of one hundred and eighty`
  line `days referred to in clause (a) of sub-section (2), if it is satisfied that there was sufficient cause for not`
  line `filing the same within that period.]`
  line
  line `(3) Where the High Court is satisfied that a substantial question of law is involved in any case, it shall`
  line `formulate that question.`
  line
  line `(4) The appeal shall be heard only on the question so formulated, and the respondents shall, at the`
  line `hearing of the appeal, be allowed to argue that the case does not involve such question:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall be deemed to take away or abridge the power of the`
  line `Court to hear, for reasons to be recorded, the appeal on any other substantial question of law not`
  line `formulated by it, if it is satisfied that the case involves such question.`
  line
  line `(5) The High Court shall decide the question of law so formulated and deliver such judgment thereon`
  line `containing the grounds on which such decision is founded and may award such cost as it deems fit.`
  line
  line `(6) The High Court may determine any issue which--`
  line
  line `(a) has not been determined by the Appellate Tribunal; or`
  line
  line `(b) has been wrongly determined by the Appellate Tribunal, by reason of a decision on such`
  line `question of law as is referred to in sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(7) When an appeal has been filed before the High Court, it shall be heard by a bench of not less than`
  line `two Judges of the High Court, and shall be decided in accordance with the opinion of such Judges or of`
  line `the majority, if any, of such Judges.`
  line
  line `(8) Where there is no such majority, the Judges shall state the point of law upon which they differ and`
  line `the case shall, then, be heard upon that point only by one or more of the other Judges of the High Court`
  line `and such point shall be decided according to the opinion of the majority of the Judges who have heard the`
  line `case including those who first heard it.`
  line
  line `(9) Save as otherwise provided in this Act, the provisions of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908`
  line `(5 of 1908) relating to appeals to the High Court shall, as far as may be, apply in the case of appeals under`
  line `this section.]`
obj_root_law_sections_130_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 120, for section 130 (w.e.f. 14-5-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 78, for "Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 87 (w.e.f. 1-7-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_130_a:
  sectionId (31062)
  sectionNo 130A
  orderNo 229
  title `Application to High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_130_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_130_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31062&sectionno=130A&orderno=229&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_130_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[130A. Application to High Court.--(1) The ^2[Principal Commissioner of Customs or`
  line `Commissioner of Customs] or the other party may, within one hundred and eighty days of the date upon`
  line `which he is served with notice of an order under section 129B passed ^3[before the 1st day of July, 2003]`
  line `(not being an order relating, among other things, to the determination of any question having a relation to`
  line `the rate of duty of customs or to the value of goods for purposes of assessment), by application in the`
  line `prescribed form, accompanied, where the application is made by the other party, by a fee of two hundred`
  line `rupees, apply to the High Court to direct the Appellate Tribunal to refer to the High Court any question of`
  line `law arising from such order of the Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(2) The ^2[Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs] or the other party`
  line `applying to the High Court under sub-section (1) shall clearly state the question of law which he seeks to`
  line `be referred to the High Court and shall also specify the paragraph in the order of the Appellate Tribunal`
  line `relevant to the question sought to be referred.`
  line
  line `(3) On receipt of notice that an application has been made under sub-section (1), the person against`
  line `whom such application has been made, may, notwithstanding that he may not have filed such application,`
  line `file, within forty-five days of the receipt of the notice, a memorandum of cross-objections verified in the`
  line `prescribed manner against any part of the order in relation to which an application for reference has been`
  line `made and such memorandum shall be disposed of by the High Court as if it were an application presented`
  line `within the time specified in sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `^4[(3A) The High Court may admit an application or permit the filing of a memorandum of crossobjections after the expiry of the relevant period referred to in sub-section (1) or sub-section (3), if it is`
  line `satisfied that there was sufficient cause for not filing the same within that period.]`
  line
  line `(4) If, on an application made under sub-section (1), the High Court directs the Appellate Tribunal to`
  line `refer the question of law raised in the application, the Appellate Tribunal shall, within one hundred and`
  line `twenty days of the receipt of such direction, draw up a statement of the case and refer it to the High`
  line Court.]
obj_root_law_sections_130_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 112, for section 130A (w.e.f. 11-5-1999).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 78, for "Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 121, for "on or after the 1st day of July, 1999" (w.e.f. 14-5-2003).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 88 (w.e.f. 1-7-1999).`
obj_root_law_sections_130_b:
  sectionId (31063)
  sectionNo 130B
  orderNo 230
  title `Power of High Court or Supreme Court to require statement to be amended.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_130_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_130_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31063&sectionno=130B&orderno=230&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_130_b_content:
  string
  line `^1130B. Power of High Court or Supreme Court to require statement to be amended.--If the`
  line `High Court or the Supreme Court is not satisfied that the statements in a case referred to it are sufficient`
  line `to enable it to determine the questions raised thereby, the Court may refer the case back to the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal for the purpose of making such additions thereto or alterations therein as it may direct in that`
  line behalf.
obj_root_law_sections_130_b_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 130B to be omitted by Act 49 of 2005, s. 30 (28-12-2005). This amendment has been struck down by the Supreme`
  line `Court's order dated 25th September, 2014 in the Madras Bar Association Vs Union of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_130_c:
  sectionId (31064)
  sectionNo 130C
  orderNo 231
  title `Case before High Court to be heard by not less than two judges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_130_c_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_130_c_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31064&sectionno=130C&orderno=231&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_130_c_content:
  string
  line `^1130C. Case before High Court to be heard by not less than two judges.--(1) When any case has`
  line `been referred to the High Court ^2[under section 130 or section 130A] it shall be heard by a Bench of not`
  line `less than two judges of the High Court and shall be decided in accordance with the opinion of such judges`
  line `or of the majority, if any, of such judges.`
  line
  line `(2) Where there is no such majority, the judges shall state the point of law upon which they differ and`
  line `the case shall then be heard upon that point only by one or more of the other judges of the High Court,`
  line `and such point shall be decided according to the opinion of the majority of the judges who have heard the`
  line `case including those who first heard it.`
obj_root_law_sections_130_c_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 130C to be omitted by Act 49 of 2005, s. 30 and the Schedule (28-12-2005). This amendment has been struck down by`
  line `the Supreme Court's order dated 25th September, 2014 in the Madras Bar Association Vs Union of India.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 113, for "under section 130" (w.e.f. 11-5-1999).`
obj_root_law_sections_130_d:
  sectionId (31065)
  sectionNo 130D
  orderNo 232
  title `Decision of High Court or Supreme Court on the case stated.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_130_d_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_130_d_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31065&sectionno=130D&orderno=232&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_130_d_content:
  string
  line `^1130D. Decision of High Court or Supreme Court on the case stated.--(1) The High Court or the`
  line `Supreme Court hearing any such case shall decide the questions of law raised therein, and shall deliver its`
  line `judgment thereon containing the grounds on which such decision is founded and a copy of the judgment`
  line `shall be sent under the seal of the Court and the signature of the Registrar to the Appellate Tribunal which`
  line `shall pass such orders as are necessary to dispose of the case in conformity with such judgment.`
  line
  line `^2[(1A) Where the High Court delivers a judgment in an appeal filed before it under section 130, effect`
  line `shall be given to the order passed on the appeal by the proper officer on the basis of a certified copy of the`
  line judgment.]
  line
  line `(2) The costs of any ^3[reference to the High Court or an appeal to the High Court or the Supreme`
  line `Court as the case may be] which shall not include the fee for making the reference shall be in the`
  line `discretion of the Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_130_d_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 130D to be omitted by Act 49 of 2005, s. 30 and the Schedule (28-12-2005). This amendment has been struck down by`
  line `the Supreme Court's order dated 25th September, 2014 the Madras Bar in Association Vs Union of India.`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 122 (w.e.f. 1-7-2003).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 122, ibid., for "reference to the High Court or the Supreme Court" (w.e.f. 14-5-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_130_e:
  sectionId (31066)
  sectionNo 130E
  orderNo 233
  title `Appeal to Supreme Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_130_e_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_130_e_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31066&sectionno=130E&orderno=233&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_130_e_content:
  string
  line `An appeal shall lie to the Supreme Court from--`
  line
  line `^1[(a) any judgment of the High Court delivered--`
  line
  line `(i) in an appeal made under section 130; or`
  line
  line `(ii) on a reference made under section 130 by the Appellate Tribunal before the 1st day of`
  line `July, 2003;`
  line
  line `(iii) on a reference made under section 130A,`
  line
  line `in any case which, on its own motion or on an oral application made by or on behalf of the party`
  line `aggrieved, immediately after passing of the judgment, the High Court certifies to be a fit one for appeal to`
  line `the Supreme Court; or]`
  line
  line `(b) any order passed ^2[before the establishment of the National Tax Tribunal] by the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal relating, among other things, to the determination of any question having a relation to the`
  line `rate of duty of customs or to the value of goods for purposes of assessment.`
obj_root_law_sections_130_e_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 123, ibid., for clause (a) (w.e.f. 14-5-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 49 of 2005, s. 30 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 28-12-2005). This amendment has been struck down by the Supreme`
  line `Court's order dated 25th September, 2014 in the Madras Bar Association Vs Union of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_130_f:
  sectionId (31067)
  sectionNo 130F
  orderNo 234
  title `Hearing before Supreme Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_130_f_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_130_f_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31067&sectionno=130F&orderno=234&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_130_f_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908`
  line `(5 of 1908), relating to appeals to the Supreme Court shall, so far as may be, apply in the case of appeals`
  line `under section 130E as they apply in the case of appeals from decrees of a High Court:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall be deemed to affect the provisions of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 130D or section 131.`
  line
  line `(2) The costs of the appeal shall be in the discretion of the Supreme Court.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the judgment of the High Court is varied or reversed in the appeal, effect shall be given to`
  line `the order of the Supreme Court in the manner provided in section 130D in the case of a judgment of the`
  line `High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_130_f_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_131:
  sectionId (31068)
  sectionNo (131)
  orderNo 235
  title `Sums due to be paid notwithstanding reference, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_131_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31068&sectionno=131&orderno=235&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_131_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding that a reference has`
  line `been made to the High Court or the Supreme Court or an appeal has been preferred to the Supreme`
  line `Court, ^1[under this Act before the commencement of the National Tax Tribunal Act, 2005] sums due to`
  line `the Government as a result of an order passed under sub-section (1) of section 129B shall be payable in`
  line `accordance with the order so passed.`
obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 49 of 2005, s. 30 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 28-12-2005). This amendment has been struck down by the Supreme`
  line `Court's order dated 25th September, 2014 in the Madras Bar Association Vs Union of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_131_a:
  sectionId (31069)
  sectionNo 131A
  orderNo 236
  title `Exclusion of time taken for copy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_131_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_131_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31069&sectionno=131A&orderno=236&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_131_a_content:
  string
  line `In computing the period of limitation specified for an`
  line `appeal or application under this Chapter, the day on which the order complained of was served, and if the`
  line `party preferring the appeal or making the application was not furnished with a copy of the order when the`
  line `notice of the order was served upon him, the time requisite for obtaining a copy of such order shall be`
  line excluded.
obj_root_law_sections_131_a_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_131_b:
  sectionId (31070)
  sectionNo 131B
  orderNo 237
  title `Transfer of certain pending proceedings and transitional provisions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_131_b_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 78, for "Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31070&sectionno=131B&orderno=237&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_131_b_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every appeal`
  line `which is pending immediately before the appointed day before the Board under section 128, as it stood`
  line `immediately before that day, and any matter arising out of or connected with such appeal and which is so`
  line `pending shall stand transferred on that day to the Appellate Tribunal and the Appellate Tribunal may`
  line `proceed with such appeal or matter from the stage at which it was on that day:`
  line
  line `Provided that the appellant may demand that before proceeding further with that appeal or matter, he`
  line `may be re-heard.`
  line
  line `(2) Every proceeding which is pending immediately before the appointed day before the Central`
  line `Government under section 131, as it stood immediately before that day, and any matter arising out of or`
  line `connected with such proceeding and which is so pending shall stand transferred on that day to the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal and the Appellate Tribunal may proceed with such proceeding or matter from the`
  line `stage at which it was on that day as if such proceeding or matter were an appeal filed before it:`
  line
  line `Provided that if any such proceeding or matter relates to an order where--`
  line
  line `(a) the value of the goods confiscated without option having been given to the owner of the goods`
  line `to pay a fine in lieu of confiscation under section 125; or`
  line
  line `(b) in any disputed case, other than a case where the determination of any question having a`
  line `relation to the rate of duty of customs or to the value of goods for purposes of assessment is in issue`
  line `or is one of the points in issue, the difference in duty involved or the duty involved; or`
  line
  line `(c) the amount of fine or penalty determined by such order,`
  line
  line `does not exceed ten thousand rupees, such proceeding or matter shall continue to be dealt with by the`
  line `Central Government as if the said section 131 had not been substituted:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the applicant or the other party may make a demand to the Appellate Tribunal`
  line `that before proceeding further with that proceeding or matter, he may be re-heard.`
  line
  line `(3) Every proceeding which is pending immediately before the appointed day before the Board or`
  line `the ^1[Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs] under section 130, as it stood`
  line `immediately before that day, and any matter arising out of or connected with such proceeding and which`
  line `is so pending shall continue to be dealt with by the Board or the ^1[Principal Commissioner of Customs or`
  line `Commissioner of Customs], as the case may be, as if the said section had not been substituted.`
  line
  line `(4) Any person who immediately before the appointed day was authorised to appear in any appeal or`
  line `proceeding transferred under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) shall, notwithstanding anything contained`
  line `in section 146A, have the right to appear before the Appellate Tribunal in relation to such appeal or`
  line proceeding.
obj_root_law_sections_131_ba:
  sectionId (31071)
  sectionNo 131BA
  orderNo 238
  title `Appeal not to be filed in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_131_ba_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_131_ba_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31071&sectionno=131BA&orderno=238&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_131_ba_content:
  string
  line `^1[131BA. Appeal not to be filed in certain cases.--(1) The Board may, from time to time, issue`
  line `orders or instructions or directions fixing such monetary limits, as it may deem fit, for the purposes of`
  line `regulating the filing of appeal, application, revision or reference by the ^2[Principal Commissioner of`
  line `Customs or Commissioner of Customs] under the provisions of this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) Where, in pursuance of the orders or instructions or directions, issued under sub-section (1),`
  line `the ^2[Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs] has not filed an appeal,`
  line `application, revision or reference against any decision or order passed under the provisions of this Act, it`
  line `shall not preclude such ^2[Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs] from filing`
  line `any appeal, application, revision or reference in any other case involving the same or similar issues or`
  line `questions of law.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding the fact that no appeal, application, revision or reference has been filed by`
  line `the ^2[Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs] pursuant to the orders or`
  line `instructions or directions issued under sub- section (1), no person, being a party in appeal, application,`
  line `revision or reference shall contend that the ^2[Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of`
  line `Customs] has acquiesced in the decision on the disputed issue by not filing appeal, application, revision`
  line `or reference.`
  line
  line `(4)`
  line `^3[The Commissioner (Appeals) or the Appellate Tribunal or the court] hearing an appeal,`
  line `application, revision or reference shall have regard to the circumstances under which the appeal,`
  line `application, revision or reference was not filed by the ^2[Principal Commissioner of Customs or`
  line `Commissioner of Customs] in pursuance of orders or instructions or directions issued under`
  line `sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(5) Every order or instruction or direction issued by the Board on or after the 20th day of October,`
  line `2010, but before the date on which the Finance Bill, 2011 receives the assent of the President, fixing`
  line `monetary limits for filing appeal, application, revision or reference shall be deemed to have been issued`
  line `under sub-section (1), and the provisions of sub-sections (2), (3) and (4) shall apply accordingly.]`
obj_root_law_sections_131_ba_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 8 of 2011, s. 50 (w.e.f. 20-10-2008).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 78, for "Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 91, ibid., for "The Appellate Tribunal or court" (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_131_c:
  sectionId (31072)
  sectionNo 131C
  orderNo 239
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_131_c_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_131_c_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31072&sectionno=131C&orderno=239&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_131_c_content:
  string
  line `In this Chapter--`
  line
  line `(a) "appointed day" means the date of coming into force of the amendments to this Act specified`
  line `in Part I of the Fifth Schedule to the Finance (No. 2) Act, 1980 (44 of 1980);`
  line
  line `^1[(b) High Court" means,--`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to any State, the High Court for that State;`
  line
  line `(ii) in relation to a Union territory to which the jurisdiction of the High Court of a State has`
  line `been extended by law, that High Court;`
  line
  line `(iii) in relation to the Union territories of Dadra and Nagar Haveli and ^2[Daman and Diu], the`
  line `High Court at Bombay;`
  line
  line `(iv) in relation to any other Union territory, the highest court of civil appeal for that territory`
  line `other than the Supreme Court of India;]`
  line
  line `(c) "President" means the President of the Appellate Tribunal.`
obj_root_law_sections_131_c_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Clause (b) shall be omitted by Act 49 of 2005, s. 30 and the Schedule (28-12-2005). This amendment has been struck down by`
  line `the Supreme Court's order dated 25th September, 2014 in the Madras Bar Association Vs Union of India.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 18 of 1987, s. 5, for "Goa, Daman and Diu" (w.e.f. 30-5-1987).`
obj_root_law_sections_132:
  sectionId (31073)
  sectionNo (132)
  orderNo 240
  title `False declaration, false documents, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_132_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 29 of 2006, s. 30, for "six months" (w.e.f. 13-7-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31073&sectionno=132&orderno=240&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_132_content:
  string
  line `Whoever makes, signs or uses, or causes to be`
  line `made, signed or used, any declaration, statement or document in the transaction of any business relating`
  line `to the customs, knowing or having reason to believe that such declaration, statement or document is false`
  line `in any material particular, shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to ^1[two`
  line `years], or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_133:
  sectionId (31074)
  sectionNo (133)
  orderNo 241
  title `Obstruction of officer of customs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_133_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 31, ibid., for "six months" (w.e.f. 13-7-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31074&sectionno=133&orderno=241&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_133_content:
  string
  line `If any person intentionally obstructs any officer of`
  line `customs in the exercise of any powers conferred under this Act, such person shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to ^1[two years], or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_134:
  sectionId (31075)
  sectionNo (134)
  orderNo 242
  title `Refusal to be X-rayed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_134_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_134_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31075&sectionno=134&orderno=242&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_134_content:
  string
  line `If any person--`
  line
  line `(a) resists or refuses to allow a radiologist to screen or to take X-ray picture of his body in`
  line `accordance with an order made by a Magistrate under section 103, or`
  line
  line `(b) resists or refuses to allow suitable action being taken on the advice and under the supervision`
  line `of a registered medical practitioner for bringing out goods liable to confiscation secreted inside his`
  line `body, as provided in section 103,`
  line
  line `he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine, or`
  line `with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_134_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_135:
  sectionId (31076)
  sectionNo (135)
  orderNo 243
  title `Evasion of duty or prohibitions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_135_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_135_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31076&sectionno=135&orderno=243&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_135_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) Without prejudice to any action that may be taken`
  line `under this Act, if any person--`
  line
  line `(a) is in relation to any goods in any way knowingly concerned in misdeclaration of value or in`
  line `any fraudulent evasion or attempt at evasion of any duty chargeable thereon or of any prohibition for`
  line `the time being imposed under this Act or any other law for the time being in force with respect to`
  line `such goods; or`
  line
  line `(b) acquires possession of or is in any way concerned in carrying, removing,`
  line `depositing, harbouring, keeping, concealing, selling or purchasing or in any other manner dealing`
  line `with any goods which he knows or has reason to believe are liable to confiscation under Section 111`
  line `or Section 113, as the case may be; or`
  line
  line `(c) attempts to export any goods which he knows or has reason to believe are liable to`
  line `confiscation under Section 113; or`
  line
  line `(d) fraudulently avails of or attempts to avail of drawback or any exemption from duty provided`
  line `under this Act in connection with ^2[export of goods; or]`
  line
  line `^3[(e) obtains an instrument from any authority by fraud, collusion, willful misstatement or`
  line `suppression of facts and such instrument has been utilised by such person or any other person,],`
  line
  line `he shall be punishable,--`
  line
  line `(i) in the case of an offence relating to,--`
  line
  line `(A) any goods the market price of which exceeds one crore of rupees; or`
  line
  line `(B) the evasion or attempted evasion of duty exceeding ^4[fifty lakh] of rupees; or`
  line
  line `(C) such categories of prohibited goods as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, specify; or`
  line
  line `(D) fraudulently availing of or attempting to avail of drawback or any exemption from duty`
  line `referred to in clause (d), if the amount of drawback or exemption from duty exceeds ^5[fifty lakh] ^6[of`
  line `rupees; or] with imprisonment for a term which may extend to seven years and with fine:`
  line
  line `^7[(E) obtaining an instrument from any authority by fraud, collusion, willful misstatement or`
  line `suppression of facts and such instrument has been utilised by any person, where the duty relatable to`
  line `utilisation of the instrument exceeds fifty lakh rupees.]`
  line
  line `Provided that in the absence of special and adequate reasons to the contrary to be recorded in the`
  line `judgment of the court, such imprisonment shall not be for less than one year;`
  line `(ii) in any other case, with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years, or with fine,`
  line `or with both.]`
  line
  line `^8[(2) If any person convicted of an offence under this section or under sub-section (1) of section 136`
  line `is again convicted of an offence under this section, then, he shall be punishable for the second and for`
  line `every subsequent offence with imprisonment for a term which may extend to seven years and with fine:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the absence of special and adequate reasons to the contrary to be recorded in the`
  line `judgment of the court such imprisonment shall not be for less than ^9[one year].`
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of sub-sections (1) and (2), the following shall not be considered as special and`
  line `adequate reasons for awarding a sentence of imprisonment for a term of less than ^9[one year], namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) the fact that the accused has been convicted for the first time for an offence under this Act;`
  line
  line `(ii) the fact that in any proceeding under this Act, other than a prosecution, the accused has been`
  line `ordered to pay a penalty or the goods which are the subject matter of such proceedings have been`
  line `ordered to be confiscated or any other action has been taken against him for the same act which`
  line `constitutes the offence;`
  line
  line `(iii) the fact that the accused was not the principal offender and was acting merely as a carrier of`
  line `goods or otherwise was a secondary party to the commission of the offence;`
  line
  line `(iv) the age of the accused.]`
  line
  line `^7[Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, the expression "instrument" shall have the same`
  line `meaning as assigned to it in the Explanation 1 to section 28AAA.]`
obj_root_law_sections_135_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 112, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 11-5-2007).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 79, for "export of goods" (w.e.f. 1-8-2019).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 79, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-8-2019).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 78, for "thirty lakh" (w.e.f. 10-5-2013).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 78, for "thirty lakh" (w.e.f. 10-5-2013).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 79, for "of rupees," (w.e.f. 1-8-2019).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by s. 79, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-8-2019).`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by Act 36 of 1973, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-9-1973).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by Act 25 of 1978, s. 16, for "six months" (w.e.f. 1-7-1978).`
obj_root_law_sections_135_a:
  sectionId (31077)
  sectionNo 135A
  orderNo 244
  title Preparation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_135_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 36 of 1973, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-9-1973).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31077&sectionno=135A&orderno=244&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_135_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[135A. Preparation.--If a person makes preparation to export any goods in contravention of the`
  line `provisions of this Act, and from the circumstances of the case it may be reasonably inferred that if not`
  line `prevented by circumstances independent of his will, he is determined to carry out his intention to commit`
  line `the offence, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years, or with`
  line `fine, or with both.]`
obj_root_law_sections_135_aa:
  sectionId (64792)
  sectionNo 135AA
  orderNo 245
  title `Protection of data`
  content obj_root_law_sections_135_aa_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 6 of 2022, s. 95 (w.e.f. 30-3-2022)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=64792&sectionno=135AA&orderno=245&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_135_aa_content:
  string
  line `^1[135AA. Protection of data.-- (1) If a person publishes any information, that is furnished to customs by an exporter or importer under this Act, relating to the value or classification or quantity of goods entered for export from India, or import into India, along with the identity of the persons involved or in a manner that leads to disclosure of such identity, unless required so to do under any law for the time being in force or by specific authorisation of such exporter or importer, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a`
  line `term which may extend to six months, or with fine which may extend to fifty thousand rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing contained in this section shall apply to--`
  line
  line `(a) any publication made by or on behalf of the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) data sourced from any publication made by or on behalf of the Central Government for analysis of trends in India's international trade and dissemination thereof.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, the expression publishes includes reproducing the information in printed or electronic form and making it available for the public.]`
obj_root_law_sections_135_b:
  sectionId (31078)
  sectionNo 135B
  orderNo 246
  title `Power of court to publish name, place of business, etc., of persons convicted under the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_135_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 36 of 1973, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-9-1973).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31078&sectionno=135B&orderno=246&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_135_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[135B. Power of court to publish name, place of business, etc., of persons convicted under the`
  line `Act.--(1) Where any person is convicted under this Act for contravention of any of the provisions`
  line `thereof, it shall be competent for the court convicting the person to cause the name and place of business`
  line `or residence of such person, nature of the contravention, the fact that the person has been so convicted`
  line `and such other particulars as the court may consider to be appropriate in the circumstances of the case, to`
  line `be published at the expense of such person in such newspapers or in such manner as the court may direct.`
  line
  line `(2) No publication under sub-section (1) shall be made until the period for preferring an appeal`
  line `against the orders of the court has expired without any appeal having been preferred, or such an appeal,`
  line `having been preferred, has been disposed of.`
  line
  line `(3) The expenses of any publication under sub-section (1) shall be recoverable from the convicted`
  line `person as if it were a fine imposed by the court.]`
obj_root_law_sections_136:
  sectionId (31079)
  sectionNo (136)
  orderNo 247
  title `Offences by officers of customs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_136_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31079&sectionno=136&orderno=247&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_136_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any officer of customs enters into or acquiesces in any`
  line `agreement to do, abstains from doing, permits, conceals or ^1[connives at any act or thing, whereby any`
  line `fraudulent export is effected or] any duty of customs leviable on any goods, or any prohibition for the time being in force under this Act or any other law for the time being in force with respect to any goods is`
  line `or may be evaded, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to`
  line ^2[three
  line `years], or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) If any officer of customs,--`
  line
  line `(a) requires any person to be searched for goods liable to confiscation or any document relating`
  line `thereto, without having reason to believe that he has such goods or document secreted about his`
  line `person; or`
  line
  line `(b) arrests any person without having reason to believe that he has been guilty of an offence`
  line `punishable under section 135; or`
  line
  line `(c) searches or authorises any other officer of customs to search any place without having reason`
  line `to believe that any goods, documents or things of the nature referred to in section 105 are secreted in`
  line `that place,`
  line
  line `he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine which`
  line `may extend to one thousand rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `(3) If any officer of customs, except in the discharge in good faith of his duty as such officer or in`
  line `compliance with any requisition made under any law for the time being in force, discloses any particulars`
  line `learnt by him in his official capacity in respect of any goods, he shall be punishable with imprisonment`
  line `for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees, or`
  line `with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 125, for "connives at any act or thing whereby" (w.e.f. 14-5-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 36 of 1973, s. 7, for "two years" (w.e.f. 1-9-1973).`
obj_root_law_sections_137:
  sectionId (31080)
  sectionNo (137)
  orderNo 248
  title `Cognizance of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_137_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_137_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31080&sectionno=137&orderno=248&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_137_content:
  string
  line `(1) No court shall take cognizance of any offence under section 132, section 133, section 134 or ^1[section 135 or section 135A], ^2[or section 135AA] ] except with the previous sanction of the ^3[Principal Commissioner of Custom or Commissioner of Customs].`
  line
  line `(2) No court shall take cognizance of any offence under section 136,--`
  line `(a) where the offence is alleged to have been committed by an officer of customs not lower in rank than ^4[Assistant Commissioner of Customs or Deputy Commissioner of Customs], except with the previous sanction of the Central Government;`
  line `(b) where the offence is alleged to have been committed by an officer of customs lower in rank than ^4[Assistant Commissioner of Customs or Deputy Commissioner of Customs] except with the previous sanction of the ^3[Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs].`
  line
  line `^5[(3) Any offence under this Chapter may, either before or after the institution of prosecution, be compounded by the ^6[Principal Chief Commissioner of Customs or Chief Commissioner of Customs] on payment, by the person accused of the offence to the Central Government, of ^7[such compounding amount and in such manner of compounding] as may be specified by rules.]`
  line
  line `^8[Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall apply to--`
  line
  line `(a) a person who has been allowed to compound once in respect of any offence under sections 135 and 135A;`
  line `(b) a person who has been accused of committing an offence under this Act which is also an offence under any of the following Acts, namely:--`
  line `(i) the Narcotic Drugs and Psychotropic Substances Act, 1985 (61 of 1985);`
  line `(ii) the Chemical Weapons Convention Act, 2000 (34 of 2000);`
  line `(iii) the Arms Act, 1959 (54 of 1959);`
  line `(iv) the Wild Life (Protection) Act, 1972 (53 of 1972);`
  line `(c) a person involved in smuggling of goods falling under any of the following, namely:--`
  line `(i) goods specified in the list of Special Chemicals, Organisms, Materials, Equipment and Technology in Appendix 3 to Schedule 2 (Export Policy) of ITC (HS) Classification of Export and Import Items of the Foreign Trade Policy, as amended from time to time, issued under section 5 of the Foreign Trade (Development and Regulation) Act, 1992 (22 of 1992);`
  line `(ii) goods which are specified as prohibited items for import and export in the ITC (HS) Classification of Export and Import Items of the Foreign Trade Policy, as amended from time to time, issued under section 5 of the Foreign Trade (Development and Regulation) Act, 1992 (22 of 1992);`
  line `(iii) any other goods or documents, which are likely to affect friendly relations with a foreign State or are derogatory to national honour;`
  line `(d) a person who has been allowed to compound once in respect of any offence under this Chapter for goods of value exceeding rupees one crore;`
  line `(e) a person who has been convicted under this Act on or after the 30th day of December, 2005.]`
obj_root_law_sections_137_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 29 of 2006, s. 32, for section 135 (w.e.f. 13-7-2006).`
  line
  line `2.Ins. by Act 6 of 2022, s. 96 (w.e.f. 30-3-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 78, for Commissioner of Customs (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 50, for Assistant Collector of Customs (w.e.f. 26.5.1995). Again Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 100,`
  line `for Assistant Commissioner of Customs (w.e.f. 11-5-1999).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 71 (w.e.f. 10-9-2004).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 78, for Chief Commissioner of Customs (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 89, for such compounding amount (w.e.f. 19-8-2009).`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by s. 89, ibid. (w.e.f. 19-8-2009).`
obj_root_law_sections_138:
  sectionId (31081)
  sectionNo (138)
  orderNo 249
  title `Offences to be tried summarily`
  content obj_root_law_sections_138_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 36 of 1973, s. 8, for "under clause (i) of section 135" (w.e.f. 1-9-1973).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31081&sectionno=138&orderno=249&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_138_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898), an offence under this Chapter other than an offence`
  line `punishable ^1[under clause (i) of sub-section (1) of section 135 or under sub-section (2) of that section]`
  line `may be tried summarily by a Magistrate.`
obj_root_law_sections_138_a:
  sectionId (31082)
  sectionNo 138A
  orderNo 250
  title `Presumption of culpable mental state`
  content obj_root_law_sections_138_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-1973).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31082&sectionno=138A&orderno=250&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_138_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[138A. Presumption of culpable mental state.--(1) In any prosecution for an offence under this`
  line `Act which requires a culpable mental state on the part of the accused, the court shall presume the`
  line `existence of such mental state but it shall be a defence for the accused to prove the fact that he had no`
  line `such mental state with respect to the act charged as an offence in that prosecution.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this section, culpable mental state includes intention, motive, knowledge of a fact`
  line `and belief in, or reason to believe, a fact.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of this section, a fact is said to be proved only when the court believes it to exist`
  line `beyond reasonable doubt and not merely when its existence is established by a preponderance of`
  line probability.]
obj_root_law_sections_138_b:
  sectionId (31083)
  sectionNo 138B
  orderNo 251
  title `Relevancy of statements under certain circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_138_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-1973).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31083&sectionno=138B&orderno=251&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_138_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[138B. Relevancy of statements under certain circumstances.--(1) A statement made and signed`
  line `by a person before any gazetted officer of customs during the course of any inquiry or proceeding under`
  line `this Act shall be relevant, for the purpose of proving, in any prosecution for an offence under this Act, the`
  line `truth of the facts which it contains,--`
  line
  line `(a) when the person who made the statement is dead or cannot be found, or is incapable of giving`
  line `evidence, or is kept out of the way by the adverse party, or whose presence cannot be obtained`
  line `without an amount of delay or expense which, under the circumstances of the case, the court`
  line `considers unreasonable; or`
  line
  line `(b) when the person who made the statement is examined as a witness in the case before the court`
  line `and the court is of opinion that, having regard to the circumstances of the case, the statement should`
  line `be admitted in evidence in the interests of justice.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sub-section (1) shall, so far as may be, apply in relation to any proceeding under`
  line `this Act, other than a proceeding before a court, as they apply in relation to a proceeding before a court.]`
obj_root_law_sections_138_c:
  sectionId (31084)
  sectionNo 138C
  orderNo 252
  title `Admissibility of micro films, facsimile copies of documents and computer print outs as documents and as evidence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_138_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 1988, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-7-1988) vide Notification No. 18/88-C.E. (N.T.), dated 29-6-1988.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31084&sectionno=138C&orderno=252&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_138_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[138C. Admissibility of micro films, facsimile copies of documents and computer print outs as`
  line `documents and as evidence.--(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time`
  line `being in force,--`
  line
  line `(a) a micro film of a document or the reproduction of the image or images embodied in such`
  line `micro film (whether enlarged or not); or`
  line
  line `(b) a facsimile copy of a document; or`
  line
  line `(c) a statement contained in a document and included in a printed material produced by a`
  line `computer (hereinafter referred to as a "computer print out"), if the conditions mentioned in`
  line `sub-section (2) and the other provisions contained in this section are satisfied in relation to the`
  line `statement and the computer in question,`
  line
  line `shall be deemed to be also a document for the purposes of this Act and the rules made thereunder and`
  line `shall be admissible in any proceedings thereunder, without further proof or production of the original, as`
  line `evidence of any contents of the original or of any fact stated therein of which direct evidence would be`
  line admissible.
  line
  line `(2) The conditions referred to in sub-section (1) in respect of a computer printout shall be the`
  line `following, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the computer printout containing the statement was produced by the computer during the`
  line `period over which the computer was used regularly to store or process information for the purposes of`
  line `any activities regularly carried on over that period by the person having lawful control over the use of`
  line `the computer;`
  line
  line `(b) during the said period, there was regularly supplied to the computer in the ordinary course of`
  line `the said activities, information of the kind contained in the statement or of the kind from which the`
  line `information so contained is derived;`
  line
  line `(c) throughout the material part of the said period, the computer was operating properly or, if not,`
  line `then any respect in which it was not operating properly or was out of operation during that part of that`
  line `period was not such as to affect the production of the document or the accuracy of the contents; and`
  line
  line `(d) the information contained in the statement reproduces or is derived from information supplied`
  line `to the computer in the ordinary course of the said activities.`
  line
  line `(3) Where over any period, the function of storing or processing information for the purposes of any`
  line `activities regularly carried on over that period as mentioned in clause (a) of sub-section (2) was regularly`
  line `performed by computers, whether--`
  line
  line `(a) by a combination of computers operating over that period; or`
  line
  line `(b) by different computers operating in succession over that period; or`
  line
  line `(c) by different combinations of computers operating in succession over that period; or`
  line
  line `(d) in any other manner involving the successive operation over that period, in whatever order, of`
  line `one or more computers and one or more combinations of computers,`
  line
  line `all the computers used for that purpose during that period shall be treated for the purposes of this section`
  line `as constituting a single computer; and references in this section to a computer shall be construed`
  line accordingly.
  line
  line `(4) In any proceedings under this Act and the rules made thereunder where it is desired to give a`
  line `statement in evidence by virtue of this section, a certificate doing any of the following things, that is to`
  line say,--
  line
  line `(a) identifying the document containing the statement and describing the manner in which it was`
  line produced;
  line
  line `(b) giving such particulars of any device involved in the production of that document as may be`
  line `appropriate for the purpose of showing that the document was produced by a computer;`
  line
  line `(c) dealing with any of the matters to which the conditions mentioned in sub-section (2) relate,`
  line
  line `and purporting to be signed by a person occupying a responsible official position in relation to the`
  line `operation of the relevant device or the management of the relevant activities (whichever is appropriate)`
  line `shall be evidence of any matter stated in the certificate; and for the purposes of this sub-section it shall be`
  line `sufficient for a matter to be stated to the best of the knowledge and belief of the person stating it.`
  line
  line `(5) For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) information shall be taken to be supplied to a computer if it is supplied thereto in any`
  line `appropriate form and whether it is so supplied directly or (with or without human intervention) by`
  line `means of any appropriate equipment;`
  line
  line `(b) whether in the course of activities carried on by any official, information is supplied with a`
  line `view to its being stored or processed for the purposes of those activities by a computer operated`
  line `otherwise than in the course of those activities, that information, if duly supplied to that computer,`
  line `shall be taken to be supplied to it in the course of those activities;`
  line
  line `(c) a document shall be taken to have been produced by a computer whether it was produced by it`
  line `directly or (with or without human intervention) by means of any appropriate equipment.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "computer" means any device that receives, stores and processes data, applying stipulated`
  line `processes to the information and supplying results of these processes; and`
  line
  line `(b) any reference to information being derived from other information shall be a reference to`
  line `its being derived there from by calculation, comparison or any other process.]`
obj_root_law_sections_139:
  sectionId (31085)
  sectionNo (139)
  orderNo 253
  title `Presumption as to documents in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_139_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_139_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31085&sectionno=139&orderno=253&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_139_content:
  string
  line `^1[139. Presumption as to documents in certain cases.--Where any document--`
  line
  line `(i) is produced by any person or has been seized from the custody or control of any person, in`
  line `either case, under this Act or under any other law, or`
  line
  line `(ii) has been received from any place outside India in the course of investigation of any offence`
  line `alleged to have been committed by any person under this Act,`
  line
  line `and such document is tendered by the prosecution in evidence against him or against him and any other`
  line `person who is tried jointly with him, the court shall--`
  line
  line `(a) presume, unless the contrary is proved, that the signature and every other part of such`
  line `document which purports to be in the handwriting of any particular person or which the court may`
  line `reasonably assume to have been signed by, or to be in the handwriting of, any particular person, is in that`
  line `person's handwriting, and in the case of a document executed or attested, that it was executed or attested`
  line `by the person by whom it purports to have been so executed or attested;`
  line
  line `(b) admit the document in evidence, notwithstanding that it is not duly stamped, if such document`
  line `is otherwise admissible in evidence;`
  line
  line `(c) in a case falling under clause (i) also presume, unless the contrary is proved, the truth of the`
  line `contents of such document.]`
  line
  line `^2[Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, document includes inventories, photographs and`
  line `lists certified by ^3[a Magistrate under sub-section (1C), or Commissioner (Appeals) under sub-section (1D), of section 110] a Magistrate under sub-section (1C) of section 110.]`
obj_root_law_sections_139_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 36 of 1973, s. 10 for section 139 (w.e.f. 1-9-1973).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 80 of 1985, s. 11 (w.e.f. 27-12-1985).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 97, for "a Magistrate under sub-section (1C) of section 110" (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_140:
  sectionId (31086)
  sectionNo (140)
  orderNo 254
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_140_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_140_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31086&sectionno=140&orderno=254&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_140_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the person committing an offence under this Chapter is a`
  line `company, every person who, at the time the offence was committed was in charge of, and was responsible`
  line `to, the company for the conduct of business of the company, as well as the company, shall be deemed to`
  line `be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to such`
  line `punishment provided in this Chapter if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge`
  line `or that he exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Chapter has`
  line `been committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to any negligence on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be`
  line `guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means a body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_140_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_140_a:
  sectionId (31087)
  sectionNo 140A
  orderNo 255
  title `Application of section 562 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898, and of the Probation of Offenders Act, 1958.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_140_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 36 of 1973, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1-9-1973).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31087&sectionno=140A&orderno=255&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_140_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[140A. Application of section 562 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898, and of the`
  line `Probation of Offenders Act, 1958.--(1) Nothing contained in section 562 of the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898), or in the Probation of Offenders Act, 1958 (20 of 1958), shall apply to a`
  line `person convicted of an offence under this Act unless that person is under eighteen years of age.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sub-section (1) shall have effect notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 135.]`
obj_root_law_sections_141:
  sectionId (31088)
  sectionNo (141)
  orderNo 256
  title `Conveyances and goods in a customs area subject to control of officers of customs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_141_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_141_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31088&sectionno=141&orderno=256&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_141_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)]`
  line `All conveyances and goods in a customs area shall, for the purpose of enforcing the provisions of this`
  line `Act, be subject to the control of officers of customs.`
  line
  line `^2[(2) The imported or export goods may be received, stored, delivered, despatched or otherwise`
  line `handled in a customs area in such manner as may be prescribed and the responsibilities of persons`
  line `engaged in the aforesaid activities shall be such as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_141_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 141 numbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 18 of 2008, s. 74 (w.e.f. 10-5-2008).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 74, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-5-2008).`
obj_root_law_sections_142:
  sectionId (31089)
  sectionNo (142)
  orderNo 257
  title `Recovery of sums due to Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_142_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_142_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31089&sectionno=142&orderno=257&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_142_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `^1[Where any sum payable by any person] under`
  line `this Act ^2[including the amount required to be paid to the credit of the Central Government under section`
  line `28B] is not paid,--`
  line
  line `(a) the proper officer may deduct or may require any other officer of customs to deduct the`
  line `amount so payable from any money owing to such person which may be under the control of the`
  line `proper officer or such other officer of customs; or`
  line
  line `(b) the ^3[Assistant Commissioner of Customs or Deputy Commissioner of Customs] may recover`
  line `or may require any other officer of customs to recover the amount so payable by detaining and selling`
  line `any goods belonging to such person which are under the control of the ^3[Assistant Commissioner of`
  line `Customs or Deputy Commissioner of Customs] or such other officer of customs; or`
  line
  line `^4[(c) if the amount cannot be recovered from such person in the manner provided in clause (a) or`
  line `clause (b)--`
  line
  line `(i) the ^3[Assistant Commissioner of Customs or Deputy Commissioner of Customs] may`
  line `prepare a certificate signed by him specifying the amount due from such person and send it to the`
  line `Collector of the district in which such person owns any property or resides or carries on his`
  line `business and the said Collector on receipt of such certificate shall proceed to recover from such`
  line `person the amount specified there under as if it were an arrear of land revenue; or`
  line
  line `(ii) the proper officer may, on an authorisation by ^5[Principal Commissioner of Customs or`
  line `Commissioner of Customs] and in accordance with the rules made in this behalf, distrain any`
  line `movable or immovable property belonging to or under the control of such person, and detain the`
  line `same until the amount payable is paid; and in case, any part of the said amount payable or of the`
  line `cost of the distress or keeping of the property, remains unpaid for a period of thirty days next`
  line `after any such distress, may cause the said property to be sold and with the proceeds of such sale,`
  line `may satisfy the amount payable and the costs including cost of sale remaining unpaid and shall`
  line `render the surplus, if any, to such person;]`
  line
  line `^6[Provided that where the person (hereinafter referred to as predecessor), by whom any sum`
  line `payable under this Act including the amount required to be paid to the credit of the Central`
  line `Government under section 28B is not paid, transfers or otherwise disposes of his business or trade in`
  line `whole or in part, or effects any change in the ownership thereof, in consequence of which he is`
  line `succeeded in such business or trade by any other person, all goods, materials, preparations, plants,`
  line `machineries, vessels, utensils, implements and articles in the custody or possession of the person so`
  line `succeeding may also be attached and sold by the proper officer, after obtaining written approval from`
  line `the ^5[Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs], for the purposes of`
  line `recovering the amount so payable by such predecessor at the time of such transfer or otherwise`
  line `disposal or change.]`
  line
  line `^7[(d) (i) the proper officer may, by a notice in writing, require any other person from whom`
  line `money is due to such person or may become due to such person or who holds or may subsequently`
  line `hold money for or on account of such person, to pay to the credit of the Central Government either`
  line `forthwith upon the money becoming due or being held, or at or within the time specified in the notice`
  line `not being before the money becomes due or is held, so much of the money as is sufficient to pay the`
  line `amount due from such person or the whole of the money when it is equal to or less than that amount;`
  line
  line `(ii) every person to whom the notice is issued under this section shall be bound to comply with`
  line `such notice, and in particular, where any such notice is issued to a post office, banking company or an`
  line `insurer, it shall not be necessary to produce any pass book, deposit receipt, policy or any other`
  line `document for the purpose of any entry, endorsement or the like being made before the payment is`
  line `made, notwithstanding any rule, practice or requirement to the contrary;`
  line
  line `(iii) in case the person to whom a notice under this section has been issued, fails to make the`
  line `payment in pursuance thereof to the Central Government, he shall be deemed to be a defaulter in`
  line `respect of the amount specified in the notice and all the consequences of this Chapter shall follow.]`
  line
  line `(2) Where the terms of any bond or other instrument executed under this Act or any rules or`
  line `regulations made thereunder provide that any amount due under such instrument may be recovered in the`
  line `manner laid down in sub-section (1), the amount may, without prejudice to any other mode of recovery,`
  line `be recovered in accordance with the provisions of that sub-section.`
obj_root_law_sections_142_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 66, for certain words (w.e.f. 26-5-1995).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 88 (w.e.f. 12-5-2000).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 100, for "Assistant Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 11-5-1999).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 66, for clause (c) (w.e.f. 26-5-1995).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 78, for "Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 72 (w.e.f. 10-9-2004).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 79 (w.e.f. 10-5-2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_142_a:
  sectionId (31090)
  sectionNo 142A
  orderNo 258
  title `Liability under Act to be first charge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_142_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_142_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31090&sectionno=142A&orderno=258&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_142_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[142A. Liability under Act to be first charge.--Notwithstanding anything to the contrary`
  line `contained in any Central Act or State Act, any amount of duty, penalty, interest or any other sum payable`
  line `by an assessee or any other person under this Act, shall, save as otherwise provided in section 529A of the`
  line `Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), the Recovery of Debts Due to Banks and the Financial Institutions Act,`
  line `1993 (51 of 1993) and ^2[the Securitisation and Reconstruction of Financial Assets and the Enforcement of`
  line `Security Interest Act, 2002 (54 of 2002) and the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code, 2016 (31 of 2016).]]`
obj_root_law_sections_142_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 8 of 2011, s. 51 (w.e.f. 8-4-2011).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 31 of 2016, s. 248, for "and the Securitisation and Reconstruction of Financial Assets and the Enforcement of`
  line `Security Interest Act, 2002 (54 of 2002)" (w.e.f. 1-11-2016) vide Notification S.O. No. 3355(E), dated 1-11-2016.`
obj_root_law_sections_143:
  sectionId (31091)
  sectionNo (143)
  orderNo 259
  title `Power to allow import or export on execution of bonds in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_143_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 100, for "Assistant Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 11-5-1999).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31091&sectionno=143&orderno=259&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_143_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where this`
  line `Act or any other law requires anything to be done before a person can import or export any goods or clear`
  line `any goods from the control of officers of customs and the ^1[Assistant Commissioner of Customs or`
  line `Deputy Commissioner of Customs] is satisfied that having regard to the circumstances of the case, such`
  line `thing cannot be done before such import, export or clearance without detriment to that person,`
  line `the ^1[Assistant Commissioner of Customs or Deputy Commissioner of Customs] may, notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in this Act or such other law, grant leave for such import, export or clearance on the`
  line `person executing a bond in such amount, with such surety or security and subject to such conditions as`
  line `the ^1[Assistant Commissioner of Customs or Deputy Commissioner of Customs] approves, for the doing`
  line `of that thing within such time after the import, export or clearance as may be specified in the bond.`
  line
  line `(2) If the thing is done within the time specified in the bond, the ^1[Assistant Commissioner of`
  line `Customs or Deputy Commissioner of Customs] shall cancel the bond as discharged in full and shall, on`
  line `demand, deliver it, so cancelled, to the person who has executed or who is entitled to receive it; and in`
  line `such a case that person shall not be liable to any penalty provided in this Act or, as the case may be, in`
  line `such other law for the contravention of the provisions thereof relating to the doing of that thing.`
  line
  line `(3) If the thing is not done within the time specified in the bond, the ^1[Assistant Commissioner of`
  line `Customs or Deputy Commissioner of Customs] shall, without prejudice to any other action that may be`
  line `taken under this Act or any other law for the time being in force, be entitled to proceed upon the bond in`
  line `accordance with law.`
obj_root_law_sections_143_a:
  sectionId (31092)
  sectionNo 143A
  orderNo 260
  title Omitted..
  content `[Duty deferment.]Omitted by The Finance Act, 2013 (17 of 2013), s. 80 (w.e.f. 10-5-2013).`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_143_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31092&sectionno=143A&orderno=260&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_143_a_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_143_aa:
  sectionId (31093)
  sectionNo 143AA
  orderNo 261
  title `Power to simplify or provide different procedure, etc., to facilitate trade.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_143_aa_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 97 (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31093&sectionno=143AA&orderno=261&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_143_aa_content:
  string
  line `^1[143AA. Power to simplify or provide different procedure, etc., to facilitate trade.--Notwithstanding anything contained in any other provision of this Act, the Board may, for the purposes of`
  line `facilitation of trade, take such measures or prescribe separate procedure or documentation for a class of`
  line `importers or exporters or for categories of goods or on the basis of the modes of transport of goods, in`
  line `order to,--`
  line
  line `(a) maintain transparency in the import and export documentation; or`
  line
  line `(b) expedite clearance or release of goods entered for import or export; or`
  line
  line `(c) reduce the transaction cost of clearance of importing or exporting goods; or`
  line
  line `(d) maintain balance between customs control and facilitation of legitimate trade.]`
obj_root_law_sections_144:
  sectionId (31094)
  sectionNo (144)
  orderNo 262
  title `Power to take samples.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_144_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_144_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31094&sectionno=144&orderno=262&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_144_content:
  string
  line `(1) The proper officer may, on the entry or clearance of any goods or`
  line `at any time while such goods are being passed through the customs area, take samples of such goods in`
  line `the presence of the owner thereof, for examination or testing, or for ascertaining the value thereof, or for`
  line `any other purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) After the purpose for which a sample was taken is carried out, such sample shall, if practicable, be`
  line `restored to the owner, but if the owner fails to take delivery of the sample within three months of the date`
  line `on which the sample was taken, it may be disposed of in such manner as the ^1[Principal Commissioner of`
  line `Customs or Commissioner of Customs] may direct.`
  line
  line `(3) No duty shall be chargeable on any sample of goods taken under this section which is consumed`
  line `or destroyed during the course of any test or examination thereof, ^2***.`
obj_root_law_sections_144_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 78, for "Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  line
  line `2. The words ", if such duty amounts to five rupees or more" omitted by Act 17 of 2013, s. 81 (w.e.f. 10-5-2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_145:
  sectionId (31095)
  sectionNo (145)
  orderNo 263
  title `Owner, etc., to perform operations incidental to compliance with customs law.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_145_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_145_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31095&sectionno=145&orderno=263&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_145_content:
  string
  line All
  line `operations necessary for making any goods available for examination by the proper officer or for`
  line `facilitating such examination shall be performed by, or at the expense of, the owner, importer or exporter`
  line `of the goods, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_145_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_146:
  sectionId (31096)
  sectionNo (146)
  orderNo 264
  title `Licence for Customs brokers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_146_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 82, for section 146 (w.e.f. 10-5-2013).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31096&sectionno=146&orderno=264&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_146_content:
  string
  line `^1[146. Licence for customs brokers.--(1) No person shall carry on business as a customs broker`
  line `relating to the entry or departure of a conveyance or the import or export of goods at any customs station`
  line `unless such person holds a licence granted in this behalf in accordance with the regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board may make regulations for the purpose of carrying out the provisions of this section`
  line `and, in particular, such regulations may provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the authority by which a licence may be granted under this section and the period of validity`
  line `of such licence;`
  line
  line `(b) the form of the licence and the fees payable therefor;`
  line
  line `(c) the qualifications of persons who may apply for a licence and the qualifications of persons to`
  line `be employed by a licensee to assist him in his work as a customs broker;`
  line
  line `(d) the manner of conducting the examination;`
  line
  line `(e) the restrictions and conditions (including the furnishing of security by the licensee) subject to`
  line `which a licence may be granted;`
  line
  line `(f) the circumstances in which a licence may be suspended or revoked; and`
  line
  line `(g) the appeals, if any, against an order of suspension or revocation of a licence, and the period`
  line `within which such appeal may be filed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_146_a:
  sectionId (31097)
  sectionNo 146A
  orderNo 265
  title `Appearance by authorised representative.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_146_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_146_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31097&sectionno=146A&orderno=265&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_146_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[146A. Appearance by authorised representative.--(1) Any person who is entitled or required to`
  line `appear before an officer of customs or the Appellate Tribunal in connection with any proceedings under`
  line `this Act, otherwise than when required under section 108 to attend personally for examination on oath or`
  line `affirmation, may, subject to the other provisions of this section, appear by an authorised representative.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of this section, "authorised representative" means a person authorised by the`
  line `person referred to in sub-section (1) to appear on his behalf, being--`
  line
  line `(a) his relative or regular employee; or`
  line
  line `(b) a`
  line `^5[custom broker] licensed under section 146; or`
  line
  line `(c) any legal practitioner who is entitled to practise in any civil court in India; or`
  line
  line `(d) any person who has acquired such qualifications as the Central Government may specify by`
  line `rules made in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, no person who was a member of the Indian`
  line `Customs and Central Excise Service-Group A and has retired or resigned from such Service after having`
  line `served for not less than three years in any capacity in that Service shall be entitled to appear as`
  line `an authorised representative in any proceedings before an officer of customs for a period of two years`
  line `from the date of his retirement or resignation, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(4) No person,--`
  line
  line `(a) who has been dismissed or removed from Government service; or`
  line
  line `^3[(b) who is convicted of an offence connected with any proceeding under this Act, the Central`
  line `Excise and Salt Act, 1944 (1 of 1944), or the Gold (Control) Act, 1968 (45 of 1968) or the Finance`
  line `Act, 1994 (32 of 1994); or]`
  line
  line `(c) who has become an insolvent,`
  line
  line `shall be qualified to represent any person under sub-section (1), for all times in the case of a person`
  line `referred to in clause (a), and for such time as the ^4[Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner`
  line `of Customs] or the competent authority under the ^5[Central Excise and Salt Act, 1944 (1 of 1944), or the`
  line `Gold (Control) Act, 1968 (45 of 1968) or the Finance Act, 1994 (32 of 1994)], as the case may be, may,`
  line `by order, determine in the case of a person referred to in clause (b), and for the period during which the`
  line `insolvency continues in the case of a person referred to in clause (c).`
  line
  line `(5) If any person,--`
  line
  line `(a) who is a legal practitioner, is found guilty of misconduct in his professional capacity by any`
  line `authority entitled to institute proceedings against him, an order passed by that authority shall have`
  line `effect in relation to his right to appear before an officer of customs or the Appellate Tribunal as it has`
  line `in relation to his right to practice as a legal practitioner;`
  line
  line `(b) who is not a legal practitioner, is found guilty of misconduct in connection with any`
  line `proceedings under this Act by such authority as may be specified by rules made in this behalf, that`
  line `authority may direct that he shall thenceforth be disqualified to represent any person under`
  line `sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(6) Any order or direction under clause (b) of sub-section (4) or clause (b) of sub-section (5) shall be`
  line `subject to the following conditions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) no such order or direction shall be made in respect of any person unless he has been given a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard;`
  line
  line `(b) any person against whom any such order or direction is made may, within one month of the`
  line `making of the order or direction, appeal to the Board to have the order or direction cancelled; and`
  line
  line `(c) no such order or direction shall take effect until the expiration of one month from the making`
  line `thereof, or, where an appeal has been preferred, until the disposal of the appeal.]`
obj_root_law_sections_146_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 44 of 1980, s. 50 and The Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 11-10-1982).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 83, for "customs house agent" (w.e.f. 10-5-2013).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 83, for clause (b) (w.e.f. 10-5-2013).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 78, for "Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 83, for "Central Excises and Salt Act, 1944 (1 of 1944) or the Gold (Control) Act, 1968" (45 of`
  line `1968) (w.e.f. 10-5-2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_147:
  sectionId (31098)
  sectionNo (147)
  orderNo 266
  title `Liability of principal and agent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_147_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_147_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31098&sectionno=147&orderno=266&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_147_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where this Act requires anything to be done by the`
  line `owner, importer or exporter of any goods, it may be done on his behalf by his agent.`
  line
  line `(2) Any such thing done by an agent of the owner, importer or exporter of any goods shall, unless the`
  line `contrary is proved, be deemed to have been done with the knowledge and consent of such owner, importer or exporter, so that in any proceedings under this Act, the owner, importer or exporter of the`
  line `goods shall also be liable as if the thing had been done by himself.`
  line
  line `(3) When any person is expressly or impliedly authorised by the owner, importer or exporter of any`
  line `goods to be his agent in respect of such goods for all or any of the purposes of this Act, such person shall,`
  line `without prejudice to the liability of the owner, importer or exporter, be deemed to be the owner, importer`
  line `or exporter of such goods for such purposes ^1[including liability therefor under this Act]:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any duty is not levied or is short-levied or erroneously refunded on account of`
  line `any reason other than any wilful act, negligence or default of the agent, such duty shall not be recovered`
  line `from the agent unless in the opinion of ^2[Assistant Commissioner of Customs or Deputy Commissioner of`
  line `Customs] the same cannot be recovered from the owner, importer or exporter.`
obj_root_law_sections_147_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 84 (w.e.f. 10-5-2013).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 100, for "Assistant Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 11-5-1999).`
obj_root_law_sections_148:
  sectionId (31099)
  sectionNo (148)
  orderNo 267
  title `Liability of agent appointed by the person in charge of a conveyance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_148_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_148_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31099&sectionno=148&orderno=267&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_148_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where this Act`
  line `requires anything to be done by the person in charge of a conveyance, it may be done on his behalf by his`
  line agent.
  line
  line `(2) An agent appointed by the person in charge of a conveyance and any person who represents`
  line `himself to any officer of customs as an agent of any such person in charge, and is accepted as such by that`
  line `officer, shall be liable for the fulfilment in respect of the matter in question of all obligations imposed on`
  line `such person in charge by or under this Act or any law for the time being in force, and to penalties and`
  line `confiscations which may be incurred in respect of that matter.`
obj_root_law_sections_148_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_149:
  sectionId (31100)
  sectionNo (149)
  orderNo 268
  title `Amendment of documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_149_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 80 (w.e.f. 1-8-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31100&sectionno=149&orderno=268&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_149_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided in sections 30 and 41, the proper`
  line `officer may, in his discretion, authorise any document, after it has been presented in the custom house to`
  line `be amended ^1[in such form and manner, within such time, subject to such restrictions and conditions, as`
  line `may be prescribed]:`
  line
  line `Provided that no amendment of a bill of entry or a shipping bill or bill of export shall be`
  line `so authorised to be amended after the imported goods have been cleared for home consumption or`
  line `deposited in a warehouse, or the export goods have been exported, except on the basis of documentary`
  line `evidence which was in existence at the time the goods were cleared, deposited or exported, as the case`
  line `may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_150:
  sectionId (31101)
  sectionNo (150)
  orderNo 269
  title `Procedure for sale of goods and application of sale proceeds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_150_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_150_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31101&sectionno=150&orderno=269&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_150_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any goods not`
  line `being confiscated goods are to be sold under any provisions of this Act, they shall, after notice to the`
  line `owner thereof, be sold by public auction or by tender or with the consent of the owner in any other`
  line manner.
  line
  line `(2) The proceeds of any such sale shall be applied--`
  line
  line `(a) firstly to the payment of the expenses of the sale,`
  line
  line `(b) next to the payment of the freight and other charges, if any, payable in respect of the goods`
  line `sold, to the carrier, if notice of such charges has been given to the person having custody of the`
  line goods,
  line
  line `(c) next to the payment of the duty, if any, on the goods sold,`
  line
  line `(d) next to the payment of the charges in respect of the goods sold due to the person having the`
  line `custody of the goods,`
  line
  line `(e) next to the payment of any amount due from the owner of the goods to the Central`
  line `Government under the provisions of this Act or any other law relating to customs,`
  line
  line `and the balance, if any, shall be paid to the owner of the goods.`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that where it is not possible to pay the balance of sale proceeds, if any, to the owner of the`
  line `goods within a period of six months from the date of sale of such goods or such further period as`
  line `the ^2[Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of Customs] may allow, such balance of sale`
  line `proceeds shall be paid to the Central Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_150_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The proviso ins. by Act 8 of 2011, s. 52 (w.e.f. 8-4-2011).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 78, for "Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_151:
  sectionId (31102)
  sectionNo (151)
  orderNo 270
  title `Certain officers required to assist officers of customs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_151_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_151_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31102&sectionno=151&orderno=270&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_151_content:
  string
  line `The following officers are hereby`
  line `empowered and required to assist officers of customs in the execution of this Act, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) officers of the Central Excise Department;`
  line
  line `(b) officers of the Navy;`
  line
  line `(c) officers of Police;`
  line
  line `(d) officers of the Central or State Governments employed at any port or airport;`
  line
  line `(e) such other officers of the Central or State Governments or a local authority as are specified by`
  line `the Central Government in this behalf by notification in the Official Gazette.`
obj_root_law_sections_151_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_151_a:
  sectionId (31103)
  sectionNo 151A
  orderNo 271
  title `Instructions to officers of customs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_151_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_151_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31103&sectionno=151A&orderno=271&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_151_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[151A. Instructions to officers of customs.--The Board may, if it considers it necessary or`
  line `expedient so to do for the purpose of uniformity in the classification of goods or with respect to the levy`
  line `of duty thereon, ^2[or for the implementation of any other provisions of this Act or of any other law for the`
  line `time being in force, insofar as they relate to any prohibition, restriction or procedure for import or export`
  line `of goods] issue such orders, instructions and directions to officers of customs as it may deem fit and such`
  line `officers of customs and all other persons employed in the execution of this Act shall observe and follow`
  line `such orders, instructions and directions of the Board:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such orders, instructions or directions shall be issued--`
  line
  line `(a) so as to require any such officer of customs to make a particular assessment or to dispose of a`
  line `particular case in a particular manner; or`
  line
  line `(b) so as to interfere with the discretion of the ^3[Commissioner of Customs] (Appeals) in the`
  line `exercise of his appellate functions.]`
obj_root_law_sections_151_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 80 of 1985, s. 12 (w.e.f. 27-12-1985).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 8 of 2011, s. 53 (w.e.f. 8-4-2011).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 50, for "Collector of Customs" (w.e.f. 26-5-1995).`
obj_root_law_sections_151_b:
  sectionId (31104)
  sectionNo 151B
  orderNo 272
  title `Reciprocal arrangement for exchange of information facilitating trade.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_151_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 98 (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31104&sectionno=151B&orderno=272&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_151_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[151B. Reciprocal arrangement for exchange of information facilitating trade.--(1) The Central`
  line `Government may enter into an agreement or any other arrangement with the Government of any country`
  line `outside India or with such competent authorities of that country, as it deems fit, for facilitation of trade,`
  line `enforcing the provisions of this Act and exchange of information for trade facilitation, effective risk analysis,`
  line `verification of compliance and prevention, combating and investigation of offences under the provisions of`
  line `this Act or under the corresponding laws in force in that country.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, by notification, direct that the provisions of this section shall apply`
  line `to the contracting State with which reciprocal agreement or arrangements have been made, subject to such`
  line `conditions, exceptions or qualifications as may be specified in that notification.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (2), the information received under sub-section (1) may`
  line `also be used as evidence in investigations and proceedings under this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the Central Government has entered into a multilateral agreement for exchange of information`
  line `or documents for the purpose of verification of compliance in identified cases, the Board shall specify the`
  line `procedure for such exchange, the conditions subject to which such exchange shall be made and designation of`
  line `the person through whom such information shall be exchanged.`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) or sub-section (3),`
  line `anything done or any action taken or purported to have been done or taken, in pursuance to any agreement`
  line `entered into or any other arrangement made by the Central Government prior to the date on which the`
  line `Finance Bill, 2018 receives the assent of the President, shall be deemed to have been done or taken under`
  line `the provisions of this section.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, the expressions,--`
  line
  line `(i) "contracting State" means any country outside India in respect of which agreement or`
  line `arrangements have been made by the Central Government with the Government or authority of such`
  line `country through an agreement or otherwise;`
  line
  line `(ii) "corresponding law" means any law in force in the contracting State corresponding to any of`
  line `the provisions of this Act or dealing with offences in that country corresponding to any of the`
  line `offences under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_152:
  sectionId (31105)
  sectionNo (152)
  orderNo 273
  title `Delegation of powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_152_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_152_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31105&sectionno=152&orderno=273&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_152_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `direct that subject to such conditions, if any, as may be specified in the notification--`
  line
  line `(a) any power exercisable by the Board under this Act shall be exercisable also by ^1[a ^2[Principal`
  line `Chief Commissioner of Customs or Chief Commissioner of Customs] or a`
  line `^3[Principal Commissioner`
  line `of Customs or Commissioner of Customs]] empowered in this behalf by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) any power exercisable by a ^3[Principal Commissioner of Customs or Commissioner of`
  line `Customs] under this Act may be exercisable also by a ^4[Joint Commissioner of Customs] or`
  line `an ^5[Assistant Commissioner of Customs or Deputy Commissioner of Customs] empowered in this`
  line `behalf by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(c) any power exercisable by a ^4[Joint Commissioner of Customs] under this Act may be`
  line `exercisable also by an ^5[Assistant Commissioner of Customs or Deputy Commissioner of Customs]`
  line `empowered in this behalf by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(d) any power exercisable by an ^5[Assistant Commissioner of Customs or Deputy Commissioner`
  line `of Customs] under this Act may be exercisable also by a Gazetted Officer of Customs empowered in`
  line `this behalf by the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_152_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs by Act 29 of 1988, s. 7, for "a Collector of Customs" (w.e.f. 1-7-1988) vide Notification No. 18/88 (N.T.)-C.E., dated`
  line 29-6-1988.
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 78, for "Chief Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 78, ibid., for "Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 100, for "Deputy Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 11-5-1999).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 100, ibid., for "Assistant Commissioner of Customs" (w.e.f. 11-5-1999).`
obj_root_law_sections_153:
  sectionId (31106)
  sectionNo (153)
  orderNo 274
  title `Modes for service of notice, order, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_153_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 99, for section 153 (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31106&sectionno=153&orderno=274&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_153_content:
  string
  line `^1153. Modes for service of notice order, etc.--(1) An order, decision, summons, notice or any`
  line `other communication under this Act or the rules made thereunder may be served in any of the`
  line `following modes, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) by giving or tendering it directly to the addressee or importer or exporter or his customs`
  line `broker or his authorised representative including employee, advocate or any other person or to any`
  line `adult member of his family residing with him;`
  line
  line `(b) by a registered post or speed post or courier with acknowledgement due, delivered to the`
  line `person for whom it is issued or to his authorised representative, if any, at his last known place of`
  line `business or residence;`
  line
  line `(c) by sending it to the e-mail address as provided by the person to whom it is issued, or to the`
  line `e-mail address available in any official correspondence of such person;`
  line
  line `(d) by publishing it in a newspaper widely circulated in the locality in which the person to`
  line `whom it is issued is last known to have resided or carried on business; or`
  line
  line `(e) by affixing it in some conspicuous place at the last known place of business or residence of`
  line `the person to whom it is issued and if such mode is not practicable for any reason, then, by`
  line `affixing a copy thereof on the notice board of the office or uploading on the official website, if`
  line any.
  line
  line `(2) Every order, decision, summons, notice or any communication shall be deemed to have been`
  line `served on the date on which it is tendered or published or a copy thereof is affixed or uploaded in the`
  line `manner provided in sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) When such order, decision, summons, notice or any communication is sent by registered post`
  line `or speed post, it shall be deemed to have been received by the addressee at the expiry of the period`
  line `normally taken by such post in transit unless the contrary is proved.]`
obj_root_law_sections_154:
  sectionId (31107)
  sectionNo (154)
  orderNo 275
  title `Correction of clerical errors, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_154_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_154_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31107&sectionno=154&orderno=275&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_154_content:
  string
  line `Clerical or arithmetical mistakes in any decision or order`
  line `passed by the Central Government, the Board or any officer of customs under this Act, or errors arising`
  line `therein from any accidental slip or omission may, at any time, be corrected by the Central Government,`
  line `the Board or such officer of customs or the successor in office of such officer, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_154_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_154_a:
  sectionId (31108)
  sectionNo 154A
  orderNo 276
  title `Rounding off of duty, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_154_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 12 of 1990, s. 62 (w.e.f. 31-5-1990).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31108&sectionno=154A&orderno=276&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_154_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[154A. Rounding off of duty, etc.--The amount of duty, interest, penalty, fine or any other sum`
  line `payable, and the amount of refund, drawback or any other sum due, under the provisions of this Act shall`
  line `be rounded off to the nearest rupee and, for this purpose, where such amount contains a part of a rupee`
  line `consisting of paise then, if such part is fifty paise or more, it shall be increased to one rupee and if such`
  line `part is less than fifty paise it shall be ignored.]`
obj_root_law_sections_154_b:
  sectionId (31109)
  sectionNo 154B
  orderNo 277
  title `Publication of information respecting persons in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_154_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2006, s. 33 (w.e.f. 13-7-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31109&sectionno=154B&orderno=277&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_154_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[154B. Publication of information respecting persons in certain cases.--(1) If the Central`
  line `Government is of opinion that it is necessary or expedient in the public interest to publish the names of`
  line `any person and any other particulars relating to any proceedings or prosecutions under this Act in respect`
  line `of such person, it may cause to be published such names and particulars in such manners as it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(2) No publication under this section shall be made in relation to any penalty imposed under this Act`
  line `until the time for presenting an appeal to the Commissioner (Appeals) under section 128 or the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal under section 129A, as the case may be, has expired without an appeal having been presented or`
  line `the appeal, if presented, has been disposed of.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In the case of a firm, company or other association of persons, the names of the`
  line `partners of the firm, directors, managing agents, secretaries and treasures or managers of the company, or`
  line `the members of the association, as the case may be, may also be published if, in the opinion of the Central`
  line `Government, circumstances of the case justify it.]`
obj_root_law_sections_154_c:
  sectionId (56414)
  sectionNo 154C
  orderNo 278
  title `Common Customs Electronic Portal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_154_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 100 (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=56414&sectionno=154C&orderno=278&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_154_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[154C. Common Customs Electronic Portal.--The Board may notify a common portal, to be`
  line `called the Common Customs Electronic Portal, for facilitating registration, filing of bills of entry,`
  line `shipping bills, other documents and forms prescribed under this Act or under any other law for the time`
  line `being in force or the rules or regulations made there under, payment of duty and for such other purposes,`
  line `as the Board may, by notification, specify.]`
obj_root_law_sections_155:
  sectionId (31110)
  sectionNo (155)
  orderNo 279
  title `Protection of action taken under the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_155_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_155_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31110&sectionno=155&orderno=279&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_155_content:
  string
  line `(1) No suit, prosecution or other legal`
  line `proceedings shall lie against the Central Government or any officer of the Government or a local`
  line `authority for anything which is done, or intended to be done in good faith, in pursuance of this Act or the`
  line `rules or regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) No proceeding other than a suit shall be commenced against the Central Government or any`
  line `officer of the Government or a local authority for anything purporting to be done in pursuance of this Act`
  line `without giving the Central Government or such officer a month's previous notice in writing of the`
  line `intended proceeding and of the cause thereof, or after the expiration of three months from the accrual of`
  line `such cause.`
obj_root_law_sections_155_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_156:
  sectionId (31111)
  sectionNo (156)
  orderNo 280
  title `General power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_156_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_156_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31111&sectionno=156&orderno=280&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_156_content:
  string
  line `(1) Without prejudice to any power to make rules contained`
  line `elsewhere in this Act, the Central Government may make rules consistent with this Act generally to carry`
  line `out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `^1[(a) the manner of determining the transaction value of the imported goods and export goods`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 14;]`
  line
  line `(b) the conditions subject to which accessories of, and spare parts and maintenance and repairing`
  line `implements for, any article shall be chargeable at the same rate of duty as that article;`
  line
  line `^2[(c) the due date and the manner of making deferred payment of duties, taxes, cesses or any other`
  line `charges under sections 47 and 51.]`
  line
  line `(d) the detention and confiscation of goods the importation of which is prohibited and the`
  line `conditions, if any, to be fulfilled before such detention and confiscation and the information, notices`
  line `and security to be given and the evidence requisite for the purposes of such detention or confiscation`
  line `and the mode of verification of such evidence;`
  line
  line `(e) the reimbursement by an informant to any public officer of all expenses and damages incurred`
  line `in respect of any detention of any goods made on his information and of any proceedings consequent`
  line `on such detention;`
  line
  line `(f) the information required in respect of any goods mentioned in a shipping bill or bill of export`
  line `which are not exported or which are exported and are afterwards re-landed;`
  line
  line `^3[(g) the publication, subject to such conditions as may be specified therein, of names and other`
  line `particulars of persons who have been found guilty of contravention of any of the provisions of this`
  line `Act or the rules.]`
  line
  line `^4[(h) the amount to be paid ^5[for compounding and the manner of compounding] under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 137.]`
  line
  line `^6[(i) the form, time limit, manner, circumstances, conditions, restrictions and such other matters`
  line `for carrying out the provisions of Chapter VAA.]`
obj_root_law_sections_156_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 113, for clause (a) (w.e.f. 10-10-2007) vide Notification No. 93/2007-Cus. (N.T.), dated`
  line 10-9-2007.
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 138 (w.e.f. 14-5-2016).`
  line
  line `3. Added by Act 36 of 1973, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-9-1973).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 73 (w.e.f. 10-9-2004).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 90, for "for compounding" (w.e.f. 19-8-2009).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 12 of 2020, s. 114 (w.e.f. 27-3-2020).`
obj_root_law_sections_157:
  sectionId (31112)
  sectionNo (157)
  orderNo 281
  title `General power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_157_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_157_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31112&sectionno=157&orderno=281&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_157_content:
  string
  line `(1) Without prejudice to any power to make regulations`
  line `contained elsewhere in this Act, the Board may make regulations consistent with this Act and the rules,`
  line `generally to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the form ^1[and manner to deliver or present] of a bill of entry, shipping bill, bill of export,`
  line `^2[arrival manifest or import manifest], import report, ^3[departure manifest or export manifest], export`
  line `report, ^4[bill of transhipment, declaration for transhipment] boat note and bill of coastal goods;`
  line
  line `^5[(ai) the manner of export of goods, relinquishment of title to the goods and abandoning them to`
  line `customs and destruction or rendering of goods commercially valueless in the presence of the proper`
  line `officer under clause (d) of sub-section (1) of section 26A;`
  line
  line `(aii) the form and manner of making application for refund of duty under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 26A;]`
  line
  line `^6[(aa) the ^7[form and manner] in which an application for refund shall be made under`
  line `section 27;]`
  line
  line `^8[(ab) the form, the particulars, the manner and the time of delivering the passenger and crew`
  line `manifest for arrival and departure and passenger name record information and the penalty for delay in`
  line `delivering such information under sections 30A and 41A;]`
  line
  line `(b) the conditions subject to which the transhipment of all or any goods under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 54, the transportation of all or any goods under section 56 and the removal of warehoused`
  line `goods from one warehouse to another under section 67, may be allowed without payment of duty;`
  line
  line `(c) the conditions subject to which any manufacturing process or other operations may be carried`
  line `on in a warehouse under section 65.`
  line
  line `^9[(d) the time and manner of finalisation of provisional assessment;`
  line
  line `(e) the manner of conducting pre-notice consultation;`
  line
  line `(f) the circumstances under which, and the manner in which, supplementary notice may be issued;`
  line
  line `(g) the form and manner in which an application for advance ruling or appeal shall be made, and`
  line `the procedure for the Authority, under Chapter VB;`
  line
  line `(h) the manner of clearance or removal of imported or export goods;`
  line
  line `(i) the documents to be furnished in relation to imported goods;`
  line
  line `(j) the conditions, restrictions and the manner of making deposits in electronic cash ledger, the`
  line `utilisation and refund therefrom and the manner of maintaining such ledger;`
  line
  line `^10[(ja) the manner of maintaining electronic duty credit ledger, making payment from such ledger,`
  line `transfer of duty credit from ledger of one person to the ledger of another and the conditions,`
  line `restrictions and time limit relating thereto;]`
  line
  line `(k) the manner of conducting audit;`
  line
  line `^11[(ka) the manner of authentication and the time limit for such authentication, the document or`
  line `information to be furnished and the manner of submitting such document or information and the time`
  line `limit for such submission, the form and the manner of furnishing alternative means of identification`
  line `and the time limit for furnishing such identification, person or class of persons to be exempted and`
  line `conditions subject to which suspension may be made, under Chapter XIIB;]`
  line
  line `(l) the goods for controlled delivery and the manner thereof;`
  line
  line `(m) the measures and separate procedure or documentation for a class of importers or exporters or`
  line `categories of goods or on the basis of the modes of transport of goods.]`
  line
  line `^12[(n) the form and manner, the time limit and the restrictions and conditions for amendment of`
  line `any document under section 149.]`
obj_root_law_sections_157_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 100 (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 56, ibid., for "import manifest" (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 56, ibid., for "export manifest" (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 115, for "bill of transhipment" (w.e.f. 11-9-1999).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 91 (w.e.f. 19-8-2009).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 40 of 1991, s. 14 (w.e.f. 20-9-1991).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 67, for "form" (w.e.f. 26-5-1995).`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 108 (w.e.f. 31-3-2017).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 100, for clause (d) (w.e.f. 28-3-2018).`
  line
  line `10. Ins. by Act 12 of 2020, s. 115 (w.e.f. 27-3-2020).`
  line
  line `11. Ins. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 81 (w.e.f. 1-8-2019).`
  line
  line `12. Ins. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 81 (w.e.f. 1-8-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_158:
  sectionId (31113)
  sectionNo (158)
  orderNo 282
  title `Provisions with respect to rules and regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_158_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_158_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31113&sectionno=158&orderno=282&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_158_content:
  string
  line `(1) All rules and regulations made under`
  line `this Act shall be published in the Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(2) Any rule or regulation which the Central Government or the Board is empowered to make under`
  line `this Act may provide--`
  line
  line `(i) for the levy of fees in respect of applications, amendment of documents, furnishing of`
  line `duplicates of documents, issue of certificates, and supply of statistics, and for rendering of any`
  line `services by officers of customs under this Act;`
  line
  line `^1[(ii) that any person who contravenes any provision of a rule or regulation or abets such`
  line `contravention or who fails to comply with any provision of a rule or regulation with which it was his`
  line `duty to comply, shall be liable to a penalty which may extend to ^2[two lakh rupees].]`
obj_root_law_sections_158_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 75, for clause (ii) (w.e.f. 10-5-2008).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 82, for "fifty thousand rupees" (w.e.f. 1-8-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_159:
  sectionId (31114)
  sectionNo (159)
  orderNo 283
  title `Rules, certain notifications and orders to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_159_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 68, for section 159 (w.e.f. 26-5-1995).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31114&sectionno=159&orderno=283&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_159_content:
  string
  line `^1[159. Rules, certain notifications and orders to be laid before Parliament.--Every rule or`
  line `regulation made under this Act, every notification issued under sections 11, 11B, 11H, 11-I, 11K, 11N,`
  line `14, 25, 28A, 43, 66, 69, 70, 74, 75, 76, 98, 98A, 101 and 123 and every order made under sub-section (2)`
  line `of section 25, other than an order relating to goods of strategic, secret, individual or personal nature, shall`
  line `be laid, as soon as may be after it is made or issued, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session, or in two or more`
  line `successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the`
  line `successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or regulation or`
  line `notification or order, or both Houses agree that the rule or regulation should not be made or notification or`
  line `order should not be issued or made, the rule or regulation or notification or order shall thereafter have`
  line `effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such`
  line `modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under`
  line `that rule or regulation or notification or order.]`
obj_root_law_sections_159_a:
  sectionId (31115)
  sectionNo 159A
  orderNo 284
  title `Effect of amendments, etc., of rules, regulations, notifications or orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_159_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 113 (w.e.f. 11-5-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31115&sectionno=159A&orderno=284&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_159_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[159A. Effect of amendments, etc., of rules, regulations, notifications or orders.--Where any`
  line `rule, regulation, notification or order made or issued under this Act or any notification or order issued`
  line `under such rule or regulation, is amended, repealed, superseded or rescinded, then, unless a different`
  line `intention appears, such amendment, repeal, supersession or rescinding shall not--`
  line
  line `(a) revive anything not in force or existing at the time at which the amendment, repeal,`
  line `supersession or rescinding takes effect; or`
  line
  line `(b) affect the previous operation of any rule, regulation, notification or order so amended,`
  line `repealed, superseded or rescinded or anything duly done or suffered thereunder; or`
  line
  line `(c) affect any right, privilege, obligation or liability acquired, accrued or incurred under any rule,`
  line `regulation, notification or order so amended, repealed, superseded or rescinded; or`
  line
  line `(d) affect any penalty, forfeiture or punishment incurred in respect of any offence committed`
  line `under or in violation of any rule, regulation, notification or order so amended, repealed, superseded or`
  line `rescinded; or`
  line
  line `(e) affect any investigation, legal proceeding or remedy in respect of any such right, privilege,`
  line `obligation, liability, penalty, forfeiture or punishment as aforesaid,`
  line
  line `and any such investigation, legal proceeding or remedy may be instituted, continued or enforced and any`
  line `such penalty, forfeiture or punishment may be imposed as if the rule, regulation, notification or order, as`
  line `the case may be, had not been amended, repealed, superseded or rescinded.]`
obj_root_law_sections_160:
  sectionId (31116)
  sectionNo (160)
  orderNo 285
  title `Repeal and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_160_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_160_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31116&sectionno=160&orderno=285&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_160_content:
  string
  line `(1) The enactments specified in the Schedule are hereby repealed to the`
  line `extent mentioned in the fourth column thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) In the Indian Tariff Act, 1934 (32 of 1934)--`
  line
  line `(a) for section 2, the following section shall be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"2. Duties specified in the Schedules to be levied.--The rates at which duties of customs`
  line `shall be levied under the Customs Act, 1962, are specified in the First and Second`
  line Schedules.
  line
  line `(b) sections 5 and 6 shall stand repealed.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding the repeal of any enactment by this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) any notification, rule, regulation, order or notice issued or any appointment or declaration`
  line `made or any licence, permission or exemption granted for any assessment made, confiscation`
  line `adjudged or any duty levied or any penalty or fine imposed or any forfeiture, cancellation or`
  line `discharge of any bond ordered or any other thing done or any other action taken under any repealed`
  line `enactment shall, so far as it is not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, be deemed to have been`
  line `done or taken under the corresponding provision of this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) any document referring to any enactment hereby repealed shall be construed as referring to`
  line `this Act or to the corresponding provision of this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) This Act shall apply to all goods which are subject to the control of customs at the commencement`
  line `of this Act notwithstanding that the goods were imported before such commencement.`
  line
  line `(5) Where the period prescribed for any application, appeal, revision or other proceeding under any`
  line `repealed enactment had expired on or before the commencement of this Act, nothing in this Act shall be`
  line `construed as enabling any such application, appeal or revision to be made or a proceeding to be instituted`
  line `under this Act by reason only of the fact that a longer period therefore is prescribed or provision is made`
  line `for extension of time in suitable cases by the appropriate authority.`
  line
  line `(6) The provisions of section 65 shall apply to goods warehoused before the commencement of this`
  line `Act if the operations permissible under that section were carried on after such commencement.`
  line
  line `(7) Any duty or penalty payable under any repealed enactment may be recovered in a manner`
  line `provided under this Act but without prejudice to any action already taken for the recovery of such duty or`
  line `penalty under the repealed enactment.`
  line
  line `(8) The mention of particular matters in sub-sections (4), (5), (6) and (7) shall not be held to prejudice`
  line `or affect the general application of section 6 of the General Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897), with regard to`
  line `the effect of repeals.`
  line
  line `(9) Nothing in this Act shall affect any law for the time being in force relating to the constitution and`
  line `powers of any Port authority in a major port as defined in the Indian Ports Act, 1908 (15 of 1908).`
obj_root_law_sections_160_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_161:
  sectionId (31117)
  sectionNo (161)
  orderNo 286
  title `Removal of difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_161_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_161_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423&sectionId=31117&sectionno=161&orderno=286&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_196252_1534829466423
obj_root_law_sections_161_content:
  string
  line `If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this Act,`
  line `particularly in relation to the transition from the enactments repealed by this Act to the provisions of this`
  line `Act, the Central Government may, by general or special order, do anything not inconsistent with such`
  line `provisions which appears to be necessary or expedient for the purpose of removing the difficulty.`
obj_root_law_sections_161_footnotes:
  string
  line
